For example, (completeExtentAsserted CanonicalizerDirective) holds, and so does (completeByCycConvention CanonicalizerDirective). Cf. completeByExternalConvention.
label: Complete By Cyc Convention
completeByCycConvention

comment: (causes_SitTypeRolePlayingSitTypeRolePlaying SCRIPT SCENE1 ROLE1 SCENE2 ROLE2) means that in any instance of #$ScriptedEventType SCRIPT, something's playing ROLE1 in SCENE1 causes something's playing ROLE2 in SCENE2.
label: Causes Sit Type Role Playing Sit Type Role Playing
causes-SitTypeRolePlayingSitTypeRolePlaying
Number Of Arty On With Alleg To
numberOfArtyOnWithAllegTo
Has Positive Value For Within Interval
hasPositiveValueForWithinInterval

comment: (decileForQuantity OBJ GROUP PRED N) means that the corresponding value when applying the functional binary predicate PRED to OBJ appears in the Nth decile of the result of applying PRED to each member of GROUP.
label: Decile For Quantity
decileForQuantity

comment: A CycInferenceHeuristicRelevancePredicate. (irrelevantTerm TERM) states that the CycLClosedDenotationalTerm TERM should be heuristically considered less relevant to inferences made in the current Microtheory. See also other instances of CycInferenceHeuristicRelevancePredicate.
label: Irrelevant Term
irrelevantTerm

comment: (relationMemberInstance PRED GROUP INST) states that for every MEMBER of GROUP the following is true: (PRED MEMBER INST). This predicate enables one to make claims about the members of a group by referencing only the group itself.
label: Relation Member Instance
relationMemberInstance

comment: (objectsInRelativeMotion EVT OBJ1 OBJ2) means that OBJ1 and OBJ2 move relative to each other during EVT. In other words, the vector from one object to the other is not a constant throughout EVT.
label: Objects In Relative Motion
objectsInRelativeMotion
Stop Word String
stopWordString
comment: (stopWordString ?STRING) means that the string ?STRING should not be treated as having any meaning in contexts which can see the stopWordString assertion.

label: Represents Sentence Within Sentence
representsSentenceWithinSentence
comment: An assertion of the form (representsSentenceWithinSentence REP ATOM SENT-REP) states that that the (CycLObjectTypeFn CycLAtomicSentence) REP represents the CycLAtomicSentence ATOM in relation to the CycLSentence represented by the (CycLObjectTypeFn SENT). Specifically, ATOM is a syntactic element of SENT and REP does not represent ATOM per se, but represents ATOM as an element of SENT. This is the corresponding predicate of the function SubSentenceFn. NOTE: The third argument of this predicate is not quoted so that it is possible to use a term to denote the relevant CycLSentence SENT without the actual symbols of ATOM appearing within SENT.

label: Will Be Sometime During Nth Date
willBe-SometimeDuring-NthDate

comment: This instance of TernaryPredicate is used to specify the salient characteristics of a particular kind of option available to an agent in a specific context. Specifically, (optionAvailableToAgent_SitType AGENT SIT_TYPE ROLE) means that playing the role ROLE in a Situation of type SIT_TYPE is an option available to AGENT in the context in which the assertion is made. Ordinarily GAFs which use this predicate will be asserted in fairly constrained contexts in which a limited number of contingent options exist. Also, because of CollectionSubsetFn, it is possible to state the conditions that SIT_TYPE must satisfy to an arbitrary degree of precision.
label: Option Available To Agent Sit Type
optionAvailableToAgent-SitType

comment: (canPerformWithLevelOfEffectiveness AGENTTYPE ACTIONTYPE LEVEL) means that, other things being equal, the skillLevel with which a given instance of AGENTTYPE can effectively perform an action of type ACTIONTYPE is LEVEL.
label: Can Perform With Level Of Effectiveness
canPerformWithLevelOfEffectiveness

comment: A ternary RelativeLocationalPredicate that relates a SpatialThing to a CartesianCoordinateSystem to a ScalarInterval. (positionAlongYAxisInCoordinateSystem OBJECT SYSTEM POSITION) means that the position of OBJECT along the y axis of SYSTEM (see yAxisPredicateOfSystem) is POSITION.
label: Position Along Y Axis In Coordinate System
positionAlongYAxisInCoordinateSystem

comment: (precedesInSeries ITEM1 ITEM2 SERIES) means that ITEM1 comes before ITEM2 in the series, SERIES.
label: Precedes In Series
precedesInSeries

comment: (offerInExchangeFor_NotRoleInSitType OFFER OBJ SIT-TYPE ROLE) means that OFFER has a conditional form, in which something is offered to the recipientOfInfo_Intended in exchange for her refraining from an action of a certain sort. More specifically, what is asked in exchange is that the recipientOfInfo_Intended refrain (for some period of time) from bringing about any instance of SIT-TYPE in which OBJ plays ROLE. For example, if AGT1 offers to give AGT2 candy in exchange for AGT2 ceasing to complain, then (offerInExchangeFor_NotRoleInSitType OFFER AGT2 Complaining senderOfInfo)
label: Offer In Exchange For Not Role In Sit Type
offerInExchangeFor-NotRoleInSitType

comment: A QueryDedicatedPredicate used for finding all of the scenes in a script with respect to which a specified actor type is not known to play a role.
label: Query Negative Roles In Script
queryNegativeRolesInScript

comment: (commonalities CORR MAP COMMON DIFF-1 DIFF-2) states a justification for the analogy between the two objects in the AnalogyCorrespondence CORR for AnalogyMapping MAP. COMMON indicates a justification for what is in common between the two objects. DIFF-1 states what is different about the first object, while DIFF-2 states what is different about the second object.
label: Commonalities
commonalities

comment: In a generated English phrase, the Cyc term arg1 corresponds best with the word arg3 used as part of speech arg2.
label: Preferred Gen Unit
preferredGenUnit

comment: '(atLeastAsCloseTo THING1 THING2 THING3)' means that THING1 is at least as close in space to THING2 as it is to THING3, and THING1 may be closer to THING2 than to THING3. See closerTo.
label: At Least As Close To
atLeastAsCloseTo

comment: (inheritRolePlayersOfType_SitTypeToSubSitType SIT-TYPE ROLE1 SUBSIT-TYPE ROLE2 TYPE) means any instance of TYPE playing ROLE1 in an instance of SIT-TYPE plays ROLE2 in the instance of SUBSIT-TYPE that is a subsituation of SIT-TYPE (cf. also onlyTypePlaysRoleInSubSituationType). This predicate allows us to track the identity of script participants by role into the scenes of a given script. For a similar relation tracking identity of participants from scenes to scripts, cf. inheritRolePlayersOfType_SubSitTypeToSitType.
label: Inherit Role Players Of Type Sit Type To Sub Sit Type
inheritRolePlayersOfType-SitTypeToSubSitType

comment: A unary predicate which pertains to instances of CycLSentence. (contradictorySentence FORMULA) states that FORMULA is a CycL formula which although being both syntactically and semantically well-formed is known to be false because it contradicts existing knowledge. Note that this is stronger than unknownSentence, which states that a formula is not currently known to be true. For example, (contradictorySentence (isa Canada Person)). See also trueSentence and rejectedSentence.
label: Contradictory Sentence
contradictorySentence

comment: An assertion of the form (subSituationTypeConditionedOn SITTYPE SIT-TYPE QUERY) is used to represent the conditions under which an instance of SITTYPE will have an instance of SIT-TYPE, some sub-collection of Situation as a subSituations. Specifically, the conditions for the realization of of the instance of SIT-TYPE are represented via QUERY, some sub-collection of CycLQuerySpecification, and the InferenceSentenceParameter of the softwareParameterValueInSpecification associated with QUERY.
label: Sub Situation Type Conditioned On
subSituationTypeConditionedOn

comment: (cycVariableBindingSelectionGoalOfType QUOTED-SENTENCE SET-OR-COLLECTION GOAL-CATEGORY) means that Cyc has the goal of type GOAL-CATEGORY of knowing what elements of SET-OR-COLLECTION can be substituted for the single open variable in the quoted SENTENCE to result in a true sentence.
label: Cyc Variable Binding Selection Goal Of Type
cycVariableBindingSelectionGoalOfType

comment: (compoundSemTrans WORD LIST PART FRAME TRANS) means that the translation of the multi-word phrase containing both WORD and the word-strings in LIST, when the part of speech is PART and the subcategorization frame is FRAME, is TRANS.
label: Compound Sem Trans
compoundSemTrans
Use Reformulation Rule For Guided Knowledge Entry
useReformulationRuleForGuidedKnowledgeEntry
comment: (useReformulationRuleForGuidedKnowledgeEntry RULE) tells the GKE that it should use RULE to reformulate formulae during term replacement, so as to produce WFF results without bothering the user.

(qaFollowupsForbidden PRED X Y) means that qaFollowupConcepts will not be generated from X to Y for simple assertions using PRED. It is designed to be used in stating exceptions to rules that conclude (qaFollowupConcepts FORT FORMAT-STRING FOLLOWUP). For example, (qaFollowupsForbidden highestPointInRegion 1 2) would ensure that a query on Oregon_State would not yield MountHood as a followup, but would still allow Oregon_State as a followup for MountHood. Note that this does not affect followups that are generated on the basis of RuleMacroPredicates.
label: Qa Followups Forbidden
qaFollowupsForbidden

comment: (predHoldsBetweenRolePlayers_SubSitTypeToSitType SCRIPT SCRIPT_ROLE SCENE SCENE_ROLE BIN_PRED) means that in an instantiation of SCRIPT the agent playing the role SCENE_ROLE in the instantiation of the SCENE scene will be related to the agent playing the role SCRIPT_ROLE in the overall script-instantiation by the relation BIN_PRED.
label: Pred Holds Between Role Players Sub Sit Type To Sit Type
predHoldsBetweenRolePlayers-SubSitTypeToSitType

comment: (dutiesOfAgentInJob AGT WORKERTYPE EVENT) means that agent AGT is obligated to perform at least some actions of type EVENT by virtue of being a worker of type WORKERTYPE. The obligation may derive directly from an explicit provision in an instance of WorkAgreement for WORKERTYPE to which AGT is bound or it may stem from more general norms and institutions governing the behavior of agents of type WORKERTYPE. The fact that AGT is an instance of WORKERTYPE must be at least one source, however, of the duty in question, in order for (dutiesOfAgentInJob AGT WORKERTYPE EVENT) to be true or taken to be true by agents within the relevant normative system.
label: Duties Of Agent In Job
dutiesOfAgentInJob

comment: Which leg a certain runner runs in a relay race
label: Leg Relayer Order
legRelayerOrder
Needed Until Predicate Strengthener Patch
neededUntilPredicateStrengthenerPatch
comment: This predicate is used for documentation purposes, so that we can identify reformulator rules that were added as a work-around until <font color="#ff0000">#$DaveS</font> and <font color="#ff0000">#$Hagen</font> are able to patch their improvements to the predicate-strengthening code.

label: Requires Closing Tag
requiresClosingTag
comment: (requiresClosingTag TAG) means that the MarkupLanguageTag TAG, when used in documents written in the appropriate markup language, requires that TextStrings designated by the tag be bounded by both opening and closing tags (see OpenTagFn and CloseTagFn).

(someTypePlaysRoleInSubSituationType SIT-TYPE TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE ROLE) means that for any instance of SIT-TYPE, there exists an instance of TYPE that plays the role ROLE in the sub-situation that instantiates SUBSIT-TYPE.
label: Some Type Plays Role In Sub Situation Type
someTypePlaysRoleInSubSituationType

comment: A predicate relating collections of ComputerProgram_CW with the port numbers (and transport layer protocols) with which they are conventionally associated. (portForProgramType PROGTYPE PROTOCOL PORT) means that, as a matter of custom, running copies of instances of PROGTYPE run on PORT on computers, listening for packets that conform to PROTOCOL. For example, (portForProgramType FTPServerProgram TransmissionControlProtocol 21) means that copies of FTP programs usually run on TCP port 21. See also portForProgram.
label: Port For Program Type
portForProgramType

comment: (cutNodeBetweenInSystem NODE X Y SYS) means that NODE is a node somewhere between the points X and Y in the ConnectedPathSystem SYS, the removal of which would leave X and Y in disconnected components. That is to say, (cutNodeBetweenInSystem NODE X Y SYS) holds if and only if (nodeCutSetBetweenInSystem (TheSet NODE) X Y SYS) holds.
label: Cut Node Between In System
cutNodeBetweenInSystem

comment: (generateArgOfRelnWithForm ARGNUM RELN FORM) means that the ARGNUMth argument to RELN should be paraphrased in natural language using a phrase with the syntactic agreement specified by FORM.
label: Generate Arg Of Reln With Form
generateArgOfRelnWithForm

comment: (fundsOrganization AGENT ORG N) means that AGENT provides N x 100 percent of the total funding for the organization ORG, throughout the duration of ORG. Embedding an assertion of this form in a 'holdsIn T' context, generates an assertion which states that AGENT provides N x 100 percent of the total funding for ORG, in T, of the total funding for ORG in T. So if a corporation has a total of 1 million dollars in funding for 1999, and .5 million dollars of all of its funding for 1999 comes from AGENT01, then (holdsIn 1999 (fundsOrganization AGENT01 CORPORATION .5)).
label: Funds Organization
fundsOrganization

comment: A predicate that relates a given tuple -- which is essentially a set whose members are indexed in some way -- and one of its members (see memberOfTuple) to the member's associated index (see tupleIndexSet). (tupleMemberIndex TUPLE MEMBER INDEX) means that INDEX serves to index or represent the position of MEMBER in TUPLE. Each element of TUPLE is associated with at least one element of the index set, and no element of the index set is associated with more than one member of TUPLE. Note that MEMBER might be indexed by more than one element of the index set, as a given member can have more than one "appearance" within a tuple. The complete predicate extent of tupleMemberIndex with respect to TUPLE in effect represents a function (TUPLE's "indexing function") from the index set onto the set of TUPLE's members.
label: Tuple Member Index
tupleMemberIndex

comment: This quaternary predicate is used to indicate that a particular agent is required to play a particular role in a particular kind of situation under the terms of a particular agreement. (agreementRequires AGREEMENT AGENT SIT-TYPE ROLE) means that the Agreement AGREEMENT specifies that the IntelligentAgent AGENT is required to play the Role ROLE in some situation that is an instance of the subcollection of Situation SIT-TYPE. For example, a peace accord agreementRequires the signatories to withdraw their troops behind specified boundaries.
label: requirement
agreementRequires

comment: This is the "third-party perspective" way of saying that a LookingForSomething_Indefinite has succeeded, incrementally or totally (cf objectFound_Indefinite). `(objectFound_IndefiniteDeRe SEARCH SEEKER OBJECT)' means that SEEKER has found OBJECT in SEARCH and that OBJECT is an instance of the type of thing for which they were looking. This predicate is useful in cases where we don't know how the searcher conceives of the sort of object sought. Compare this to objectFound_Indefinite, whose third argument position is opaque.
label: Object Found Indefinite De Re
objectFound-IndefiniteDeRe

comment: (parserRunToSpecificationWithInputStringReturnsCyclification PARSER SPECIFICATION STRING CYCL) means that CYCL is the CycL output from the instance PARSER of CyclificationParser with the string input STRING when PARSER is set to run according to the instance SPECIFICATION of ProgramSpecification.
label: Parser Run To Specification With Input String Returns Cyclification
parserRunToSpecificationWithInputStringReturnsCyclification

comment: (interArgNotIsa2_5 PRED COL1 COL2) means that, when an instance of COL1 appears as the second argument to PRED, the fifth argument in that assertion is constrained to not be an instance of COL2 and vice versa.
label: Inter Arg Not Isa 2 5
interArgNotIsa2-5

comment: (denotesArgInReln NOUN POS PRED ARG) says that (#$denotation-New NOUN POS TERM), where TERM is the collection of things that are the arg ARG of PRED for any true sentence in which PRED is the arg0. For example, (denotesArgInReln #$Mother-TheWord CountNoun mother 2) says that one denotation for the word 'mother,' qua CountNoun, is the collection of things T such that (relationExistsInstance mother Thing T) -- i.e., the collection of all mothers. This predicate is useful for linking nouns in the lexicon to *virtual* KB collections, particularly collections we don't necessarily want to have explicitly represented in the KB.
label: Denotes Arg In Reln
denotesArgInReln

comment: (bodyPartCollectionOfType ANIMAL TYPE COL) means that Collection COL is the collection of all of the instances of the collection TYPE (a specialization of AnimalBodyPart) that are anatomical parts (see anatomicalParts) of ANIMAL.
label: Body Part Collection Of Type
bodyPartCollectionOfType

comment: (desirabilityOfForAgent_RoleInType AGENT THING EVENT-TYPE ROLE QUANTITY) means the desirability for AGENT to have THING play the role ROLE in an event of EVENT-TYPE is QUANTITY.
label: Desirability Of For Agent Role In Type
desirabilityOfForAgent-RoleInType

comment: (subSituationOfType SIT-INSTANCE SUBSIT SUBSIT-TYPE) is true iff (subSituations SIT-INSTANCE SUBSIT) and (isa SIT SUBSIT-TYPE) where, for some SITTYPE, both (isa SIT-INSTANCE SITTYPE) and (properSubSituationTypes SITTYPE SUBSIT-TYPE) are true. That is, this relation holds between the instance of a situation type and the sub-situation uniquely instantiating a given sub-situation type in it
label: Sub Situation Of Type
subSituationOfType

comment: The predicate biologicalFunction is used to describe a type of situation (and the role) in which is a function of a BiologicalLivingObject. (biologicalFunction BLO SIT-TYPE ROLE) means that the organism or body part, BLO, is able to act as a ROLE in a situation of type SIT-TYPE and such situations naturally occur for such BiologicalLivingObjects. In a creationist microtheory, this would be a subset of intendedBehaviorCapable. Roles which are possible due to the physical structure of the body part or to learning by the organism are not included. Thus (biologicalFunction Fin Swimming_Underwater providerOfMotiveForce) but not (biologicalFunction Hand Swimming_Generic providerOfMotiveForce) even though a hand can be used this way.
label: Biological Function
biologicalFunction
Forcewise Continuous
forcewiseContinuous
comment: Suppose that REG is a LineOfMilitaryForces; then intuitively REG is forcewiseContinuous if it has no gaps through which an opposing force could pass without encountering significant resistance. More precisely, (forcewiseContinuous REG) is true iff there is a ModernMilitaryUnit_Deployable UNIT whose #$taskAreaOfOperations includes REG and for any two greater-than-granule-size points X and Y, there is a path PATH connecting X and Y such that PATH is physically in REG and any hostile action through PATH can be prevented by UNIT. Thus the purpose of a defensive operation aimed at controlling a certain area, for instance, will be among other things that of establishing a forcewiseContinuous line of defense. By contrast, offensive operations against established defensive positions will need to create and exploit non-forcewiseContinuous regions in the opposing forces, i.e., gaps in their defense. However, applications of this concept need not be restricted to defensive operations.
(closestEventOfTypePriorTo EVT1 EVT2 TYPE) means that EVT1 is the nearest event of TYPE aftero EVT2. In medical contexts it is assumed that both events involve the same patient.
label: Closest Event Of Type After
closestEventOfTypeAfter

comment: arg3 is the set of entries on arg1's arg2 slot, considered as a mob.
label: Mobified Entries
mobifiedEntries

comment: (nounSemTrans NOUN INT FRAME TRANS) means that the translation of word sense number INT of noun NOUN in frame FRAME is TRANS.
label: Noun Sem Trans
nounSemTrans

comment: This relates a structured information source (usually an RDF triple store) to namespaces employed by it and their corresponding prefixes.
label: Name Space Prefix For SKS
nameSpacePrefixForSKS

comment: (regionHasSurfaceLevelInNumberOfAdjacentDirections REGION LEVEL NUMBER) means that REGION has NUMBER adjacent sides where the surface level of the terrain is LEVEL. For example, (regionHasSurfaceLevelInNumberOfAdjacentDirections Saddle001 TerrainLowGround 0) means that Saddle001 has low ground on no adjacent sides. To specify the total number of sides that are LEVEL, see regionHasSurfaceLevelInNumberOfDirections. To describe types of geographical regions, use regionTypeHasSurfaceLevelInNumberOfAdjacentDirections and regionTypeHasSurfaceLevelInNumberOfDirections.
label: Region Has Surface Level In Number Of Adjacent Directions
regionHasSurfaceLevelInNumberOfAdjacentDirections

comment: (admittedNAT NAT) states that NAT is a CycLNonAtomicTerm which is both syntactically and semantically well-formed wrt arg constraints. For example, (admittedNAT (MotherFn Muffet)) is true precisely in those mts in which Muffet satisfies all the applicable arg1 constraints imposed by MotherFn. See also admittedSentence.
label: Admitted NAT
admittedNAT

comment: This predicate compares two things in terms of some BinaryPredicate that relates them to different instances of a given collection (provided by the argument constraints on the predicate). (differentInRelation THING1 THING2 BIN-PRED) holds just in case there exists REL-1 and REL-2 such that (BIN-PRED THING1 REL-1),(BIN-PRED THING2 REL-2), and REL-1 is different than REL-2.
label: Different In Relation
differentInRelation

comment: An assertion of the form (sitConflictsWithSpecificationForAgents SIT SPEC AGENT) is used to relate an instance of Situation SIT to an instance of NormativeSpecification and an instance of Agent_Generic. Instances of NormativeSpecification describe some type of situation that some agent either wants to bring about or wants to avoid. The effect of such an assertion is to state that SIT undermines or otherwise hinders, in a very generic sense, AGENT with regard to satisfying or achieving SPEC. As an example, consider a person who wants to sell her house (where we represent that as an instance of NormativeSpecification). If the house burns down, then that event would bear the relation sitConflictsWithSpecificationForAgents to that NormativeSpecification and that person. AGENT need not have any awareness of SIT.
label: Sit Conflicts With Specification For Agents
sitConflictsWithSpecificationForAgents

comment: (footnoteInWork WORK MARK FOOTNOTE) means that the GraphicalStructure FOOTNOTE is a footnote in the StructurallySpecificWork WORK and that FOOTNOTE is indicated within WORK by MARK, an instance of CharacterString.
label: Footnote In Work
footnoteInWork

comment: (keIrrelevantTerm TERM) means that printed representations of TERM (for example, via preferredGenUnit) should not show up in any RKF-based interface. (keIrrelevantTerm TERM) does not entail that inferences involving TERM will be ignored. This is a general predicate and has several spec preds which should be used in order to separate different categories of ke irrelevance. This separation will aid in controlling which terms should be seen in different types of KFD/UIA interactions and which terms should be used in inferences based upon ke irrelevance. For upper ontology terms use keIrrelevantTerm_UpperOntologyConcept, for internal terms use keIrrelevantTerm_InternalCycTerm, for general experimental terms use keIrrelevantTerm_ExperimentalVocabulary and for terms created in the attribute cleanup use keIrrelevantTerm_AttributeCleanupVocabulary.
label: Ke Irrelevant Term
keIrrelevantTerm

comment:
An instance of RelativeLocationalPredicate. (between THIS THAT MID) means that MID is in the space separating THIS and THAT, and is directly between them. Depending on the context, "directly between" might imply that MID lies on a straight line between THIS and THAT, or that it lies on a great circle between them.

For the notion of "betweenness" along a particular physical path (e.g. Austin is between Dallas and San Antonio on Highway I-35), or on some trajectory, see betweenOnPath.
label: Between
between

comment: (clothingSize ITEM SIZE-TYPE SIZE) holds just in case ITEM is designed to fit people of size SIZE with respect to SIZE-TYPE. For instance, (clothingSize PairOfPants01 HumanTypeByInseamLength (InseamLengthFn (Inch 30))) holds just in case PairOfPants01 is designed to fit people whose inseam measures 30 inches.
label: Clothing Size
clothingSize
Use Reformulation Rule For NL Quantifier Placeholder Processing
useReformulationRuleForNLQuantifierPlaceholderProcessing
comment: (useReformulationRuleForNLQuantifierPlaceholderProcessing RULE) indicates that RULE will be used by the NLQuantifierPlaceholderProcessingRLModule.

(precedes_Metric T T' TYPE 1) means that (1) both T and T' are instances of TYPE, (2) T is earlier than T' (or T' starts after the ending of T), and (3) there is no element of TYPE that is temporally between T and T'. For each k > 1, (precedes_Metric T T' TYPE k) means that there are instances T_0, ..., T_k of TYPE, where T_0 = T and T_k = T', such that (precedes_Metric T_0 T_1 TYPE 1), ..., (precedes_Metric T_(k-1) T_k TYPE 1) all hold. Note that TYPE does not have to be a member of CalendarCoveringType like CalendarDay and CalendarWeek etc. --- it can also be, e.g., Friday, May, and even members of #$AnnualHolidayTimeType.
label: Precedes-Metric
precedes-Metric

comment: This is a ternary version of the binary predicate cost which allows cost assertions regarding a given thing to be relativised to those who bear the cost in question. (costTo OBJECT MONEY AGENT) means that the TemporalThing OBJECT has a cost in MonetaryValue of MONEY to the SocialBeing AGENT. See also the ternary predicates monetaryValueOfThingTo, willingToPay.
label: Cost To
costTo

comment: (temporallySubsumesNDatesOfType TYPE NUMBER TIME-INTERVAL) means that there are NUMBER instances of TYPE in the instance of INTERVAL. For example, (temporallySubsumesNDatesOfType Weekday 2 (TimeIntervalInclusiveFn (DayFn 12 (MonthFn February (YearFn 2004))) (DayFn 15 (MonthFn February (YearFn 2004))))) means that the time interval between February 12th to the the 15th in 2004 has 2 Weekdays in the interval.
label: numerousness of time type in an interval
temporallySubsumesNDatesOfType

comment: (excludedCoreferentInUDS UDS PEG1 PEG2) is true if PEG1 is an anaphoric discourse entity in UDS and PEG2 has been ruled out as a coreference candidate for PEG2. This could mean that PEG2 is not accessible from UDS, or that it violates applicable syntactic or semantic constraints.
label: Excluded Coreferent In UDS
excludedCoreferentInUDS

comment: (calendarMonthIndex MONTH-TYPE MONTH INDEX) means that in the calendar system MONTH-TYPE, PositiveInteger INDEX indicates absolute rank-order of MONTH with respect to the other months ion the system. Thus (calendarMonthIndex GregorianMonthType March 3) means that March is the third month in the Gregorian calendar system.
label: Calendar Month Index
calendarMonthIndex

comment: (firstVADInsertOfOperationHasOrganTransplantAtDate INDEX-OP INSERT TRANSPLANT-OP DATE) means that the operation INDEX-OP has INSERT as its first VAD insertion, and TRANSPLANT-OP is a cardiac transplant that occurs after INSERT (and is performed on the same patient as INSERT).
label: First VAD Insert Of Operation Has Organ Transplant At Date
firstVADInsertOfOperationHasOrganTransplantAtDate

comment: Friction is typically characterized by a coefficient of friction which is the ratio of the frictional resistance force to the normal force which presses the surfaces together. (coefficientOfFriction OBJ1 OBJ2 NUM) means that NUM is the ratio of the frictional resistance force (see FrictionVector) to the normal force which presses the surfaces of OBJ1 and OBJ2 together. See also coefficientOfFriction_Static and coefficientOfFriction_Kinetic. When coefficients of friction are quoted for specific surface combinations, it is the kinetic coefficient which is generally quoted since it is typically the more reliable number.
label: Coefficient Of Friction
coefficientOfFriction

comment: (quantitySlotForArg1 SLOT THING> COMPLEX-SLOT) means that SLOT is the QuantitySlot which results from restricting the first argument of COMPLEX-SLOT to THING. See the corresponding function QuantitySlotForArg1Fn.
label: Quantity Slot For Arg 1
quantitySlotForArg1

comment: (expectedTenureInUnitPosition COUNTRY BOS ECHELON POSITION DURATION) means that an agent who holds POSITION in a military unit of the branch-of-service BOS with sovereignAllegianceOfOrg COUNTRY and echelonOfUnit ECHELON is expected to hold that position for DURATION.
label: expected tenure in position
expectedTenureInUnitPosition

comment: (hasDegreeInField PERSON DEGREETYPE FIELD) means that person has an educationalDegrees DEGREETYPE in the FieldOfStudy FIELD.
label: Has Degree In Field
hasDegreeInField

comment: (percentOfTerritoryIs ?POLITY ?TYPE ?PCT) means that ?PCT percent of the territory of ?POLITY is made up of ?TYPE.
label: Percent Of Territory Is
percentOfTerritoryIs

comment: (differentInValue THING1 THING2 COLL) holds just in case THING1 and THING2 are different with respect to COLL. For instance, (differentInValue ARedThing ABlueThing Color) holds because ARedThing and ABlueThing differ with respect to color. That is, there is no one color that they both can be said to have. Statements like these hold, in most cases, because there is no instance of COLL such that THING1 and THING2 are both instances of it, yet they are each an instance of some instance of COLL. identicalInValue and differentInValue cannot both be correctly asserted of the same two things. See also resemblesInValue.
label: different
differentInValue

comment: (tradeBalanceInWithDuring REGION1 PRODUCT-TYPE REGION2 THING MONEY) means that the instance of MonetaryValue MONEY is a measure of the difference between the value of the instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE exported by the GeographicalRegion REGION1 to the GeographicalRegion REGION2 during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING and the value of the instances of PRODUCT-TYPE imported by REGION1 from REGION2 during the temporal extent of THING. (THING will often be a calendar time period.) Thus if the value of REGION1's exports of PRODUCT-TYPE to REGION2 is greater than the value of its imports of PRODUCT-TYPE from REGION2 during the temporal extent of THING, REGION1 will have a positive trade balance in PRODUCT-TYPE with REGION2. If the value of its imports of PRODUCT-TYPE from REGION2 exceeds that of its exports, it will have a negative trade balance in PRODUCT-TYPE with REGION2. This latter case can be expressed using a UnitOfMoney function with a negative number as its argument.
label: Trade Balance In With During
tradeBalanceInWithDuring

comment: A predicate relating instances of WorldWideWebServerProgram with instances of LocalProgram and instances of Computer. (webServerInitiatesProgramOn WEBSERVER PROGRAM COMPUTER) means that WEBSERVER can invoke a process of PROGRAM in response to remote user requests. In most cases, the second arg of this predicate will be filled by an instance of CGIScript.
label: Web Server Initiates Program On
webServerInitiatesProgramOn
Polymer Type Subunit Type Linked By Bond Type
polymerTypeSubunitTypeLinkedByBondType

comment: (contentVectorDotProduct CASE1 CASE2 N) indicates that the dot product of the content vectors for CASE1 and CASE2 is N
label: Content Vector Dot Product
contentVectorDotProduct

comment: The predicate pointOfContactInfo allows one to characterize a string of information as belonging to a certain kind of contact location for a particular agent. (pointOfContactInfo AGENT LOC-TYPE INFO-TYPE STRING) means that the Agent_PartiallyTangible AGENT's contact locations of type LOC-TYPE (an instance of ContactLocationType (q.v.)) have STRING as one of their contact address of INFO-TYPE (where INFO-TYPE is a BinaryPredicate such as phoneNumberText, faxNumberText, or addressText).
label: point of contact information
pointOfContactInfo

comment: rewriteTemplate relates a class of natural language utterances to a set of different natural language utterances. It generally is used to reduce a complicated sentence into several less-complicated sentences.
label: Rewrite Template
rewriteTemplate

comment: (representsAgentToAgent AGENT1 AGENT2 AGENT3) means that in in dealings with AGENT3, AGENT1 represents AGENT2. For example, if Joe Terwilliger is a salesman working for IBM, and is their sales rep to NASA, then we could represent that by asserting to Cyc (representsAgentToAgent JoeTerwilliger IBM NASA).
label: Represents Agent To Agent
representsAgentToAgent

comment: (differentInQuantity THING1 THING2 QUANT-TYPE) means that the two things THING1 and THING2 do not have the same values of the quantity type QUANT-TYPE. Here 'the same' could mean complete identity or close resemblance -- what this 'different' means, and what the standard of closeness or identity is, depends on the context, but differentInQuantity and identicalInQuantity cannot both be correctly asserted of the same two things. See also resemblesInQuantity.
label: Different In Quantity
differentInQuantity

comment: (instancesDontNeedLexification COLL) means that the usual requirement that a CycL term have lexical assertions associating it with natural language words and phrases does not apply to instances of COLL.
label: Quoted Instances Dont Need Lexification
quotedInstancesDontNeedLexification

comment: An assertion of the form (hasStatusWRTAssignmentOnDateWithEstimatedTimeRemaining AGENT STATUS-PRED ASSIGN INTERVAL QUANTITY) states that the IntelligentAgent AGENT bears the relation STATUS-PRED, an instance of WorkStatusBinaryPredicate, to the Assignment_Specification during the TimeInterval INTERVAL and that AGENT believes there is QUANTITY of work remaining for it to complete it's work on the realization of ASSIGN. This predicate is designed to work with the FET Template ProjectManagement_TemplateTopic and to handle the problem of not being able to substitute values from an FET field into multiple positions within the underlying formula.
label: Has Status WRTAssignment On Date With Estimated Time Remaining
hasStatusWRTAssignmentOnDateWithEstimatedTimeRemaining

comment:
A TernaryPredicate that relates an IntelligentAgent to a PersonTypeByPositionInOrg to an Organization. (agentAppointsPositionInOrg AGENT POSITION ORG) means that AGENT has the right/responsibility to appoint persons to POSITION in ORG (under appropriate circumstances).

For example, (agentAppointsPositionInOrg (PresidentFn UnitedStatesOfAmerica) USSecretaryOfDefense USDepartmentOfDefense) means that the president of the United States has the right/responsibility to appoint a Secretary of Defense to the U.S. Defense Department under appropriate circumstances (e.g. when the president first takes office or when the current Secretary of Defense resigns).
label: Agent Appoints Position In Org
agentAppointsPositionInOrg

comment: (givesPreferentialTreatmentToEntityOfType AGENT OBJ COL) means that AGENT gives preferential treatment to OBJ over all other instances of the class COL, where OBJ is itself an instance of COL.
label: Gives Preferential Treatment To Entity Of Type
givesPreferentialTreatmentToEntityOfType

comment: (parsedNounCompound NOUN-COMPOUND-RULE MOD-STRING HEAD-STRING PARSE) means that 'MOD-STRING HEAD-STRING' was parsed using NOUN-COMPOUND-RULE to PARSE.
label: Parsed Noun Compound
parsedNounCompound

comment: A statement (provenReservesDuring PLACE TYPE AMOUNT DATE) means that records for the Date DATE indicate that there exists at least Quantity AMOUNT of NaturalResourceType TYPE in the GeographicalRegion PLACE and that it is economically feasible to harvest that resource given economic conditions during DATE. The actual known amount of TYPE that exists in PLACE could be greater than AMOUNT; however, its state might be such that it would not make economic sense to extract it (e.g., the cost of the extraction is too high relative to the price).
label: Proven Reserves During
provenReservesDuring

comment: (inheritSomeRolePlayersOfType_SubSitTypeToSubSitType SITTYPE SUBSITTYPE1 ROLE1 SUBSITTYPE2 ROLE2 TYPE) means that some instance(s) of TYPE playing ROLE1 in SUBSITTYPE1 play ROLE2 in SUBSITTYPE2 of SITTYPE. Note: this is a weaker form of inheritRolePlayersOfType_SubSitTypeToSubSitType.
label: Inherit Some Role Players Of Type Sub Sit Type To Sub Sit Type
inheritSomeRolePlayersOfType-SubSitTypeToSubSitType

comment: (exportCapacityDuring REGION PRODUCT-TYPE THING AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the greatest possible amount of instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE that could be exported by the GeographicalRegion REGION during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. In the case of automobile exports, for example, AMOUNT might be an Integer indicating the number of cars that could be exported. In the case of oil exports, AMOUNT might be a Volume (a number of barrels) indicating the total quantity of oil that could be exported, or it might be an instance of MonetaryValue indicating the monetary value of all the oil that could be exported. Alternatively, AMOUNT might be a Rate, characterizing what would be the average rate of export of instances of PRODUCT-TYPE from REGION during the temporal extent of THING if REGION were exporting PRODUCT-TYPE at the limit of its capacity. Oil exports, for example, might be expressed in terms of so many million barrels per day or in terms of so many dollars per day (again, indicating the monetary value of the oil).
label: Export Capacity During
exportCapacityDuring

comment: This ternary predicate is used to indicate that a borrower is forbidden by the terms of a loan agreement, to play a particular role in a particular kind of situation. (loanAgreementForbidsBorrower AGREEMENT SIT-TYPE ROLE) means that the LoanAgreement AGREEMENT specifies that the borrower is forbidden from playing the Role ROLE in some situation that is an instance of the subcollection of Situation SIT-TYPE. Cf. loanAgreementForbidsCreditor.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: loan agreement restriction on the borrowers
label: loan agreement restriction on the borrower
loanAgreementForbidsBorrower

comment: (containingWorkForStyleAndRendering WORK STYLE RENDERING STRING) means that STRING is the canonical string used to express the containing work for WORK according to STYLE-SPECIFICATION, for rendering using MARKUP-LANGUAGE.
label: Containing Work For Style And Rendering
containingWorkForStyleAndRendering

comment: An assertion of the form (superiorWRTCriterion THING1 THING2 CRITERION) states that THING1, some Thing, is superior to THING2, another Thing, with regard to CRITERION, some instance of EvaluativeCriterion. For instance (superiorWRTCriterion BananasInPajamas_TheTVShow ElGranJuegoDeLaOca_TheTVShow Foo) would assert that BananasInPajamas_TheTVShow is superior to ElGranJuegoDeLaOca_TheTVShow according to the Foo standard. It is important to note that superiorWRTCriterion is a TemporallyQualifiableRelation.
label: Superior WRT Criterion
superiorWRTCriterion

comment: A LogicalConnective that represents conjunction in CycL. It is a VariableArityRelation, taking an arbitrary number of #$ELSentence-Assertibles as arguments. (and P Q ... Z) is true if and only if all of the sentences P, Q, ..., and Z are true.
label: And (relationship)
and

comment: Used to express succession in a role (i.e. headOfStateOf Kingdom).  Notice that this predicate does not pertain only to the roles of humans, but can also show a succession in roles of animals, things, or even thoughts and ideas.
label: Successor In Role
successorInRole

comment: A ternary MetaRelation predicate for stating that a certain kind of complex, partly genls based relationship holds between the fifth argument to a given function and the corresponding value that is returned. (interArg2ResultGenls FUNC INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when a subcollection of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the fifth argument to FUNC, then -- regardless of what the other arguments to FUNC might be -- the value (if any) of that function for those arguments is a subcollection of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is: if INST is a subcollection of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL and (FUNC ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 INST ...) = VALUE, then VALUE is a subcollection of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. Note that, unlike (e.g.) the InterArgTypePredicates, interArg5ResultGenls _cannot_ be used to put semantic well-formedness constraints on functions. See also the similar but more flexible quaternary interArgResultGenl.
label: Inter Arg 5 Result Genls
interArg5ResultGenls

comment: A MetaRelation that is used to indicate that a given relation is "asymmetric" with respect to two given argument-places. (asymmetricInArgs REL M N) means that REL is asymmetric in its Mth and Nth arguments: these arguments are _not_ freely permutable. This entails that, given any true (if REL is a predicate) or denoting (if REL is a function) formula built from (the CycL term for) REL, inter-substituting the formula's Mth and Nth arguments (while leaving the other arguments unchanged) will always result in a change in the formula's truth-value or denotatum). If REL is a binary predicate this is equivalent to its being an AsymmetricBinaryPredicate. More generally: (i) If REL is a Predicate that holds of given argument-sequence SEQ, then REL does _not_ hold of the sequence SEQ-PERMUTED obtained by permuting the Mth and Nth items in SEQ (while leaving the other items unchanged). (ii) If REL is a Function_Denotational whose value for a given argument-sequence SEQ is VALUE, then REL does _not_ have VALUE as its value for SEQ-PERMUTED (defined as above); REL might have something other than VALUE as its value for SEQ-PERMUTED, or it might be undefined for SEQ-PERMUTED. For example, a (hypothetical) ternary predicate called `greaterThanOnScale', which took as arguments two physical objects and a scale for measuring some physical property, would be asymmetric in its first and second arguments; i.e. (asymmetricInArgs greaterThanOnScale 1 2) would hold. For a function example, a (hypothetical) ternary function called `TransportToFromViaVehicleTypeFn' that took as arguments two _distinct_ locations and a vehicle-type (and returned, say, the collection of all trips from the first location to the second location in vehicles of that type) would also be asymmetric in its first and second arguments. Note that (each of) the argIsa constraint(s) on REL's Mth argument-place must not be disjoint with (any of) the argIsa constraint(s) on REL's Nth argument-place (see disjointWith), and likewise for the corresponding argGenl constraints (if any). For some discussion of why this is so, see the #$NoteOnArgumentCosatisfiabilityRequirement. See also antiSymmetricInArgs and commutativeInArgs.
label: Asymmetric In Args
asymmetricInArgs

comment: (redundantSentence FORMULA) indicates that the given FORMULA is redundant with Cyc's existing knowledge. In other words, FORMULA can already be proven from the current state of the knowledge base. This is a specialization of trueSentence, primarily for reasons of focus.
label: Redundant Sentence
redundantSentence

comment:
A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgEqualsIsa1_3 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when INDEPENDENT-ARG appears as the first argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the third argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, (RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG ARG2 ARG3 ...) is semantically well-formed only if ARG3 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL.

For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations. See interArgEqualsIsa for a similar but more general predicate that is quintary, allowing the user to specify the positions of the independent and dependent arguments.
label: Inter Arg Equals Isa 1 3
interArgEqualsIsa1-3

comment: (lawAppliesToObjectInSituation LAW THING SIT) means that the law of nature, LAW, applies to the thing THING in the situation SIT.
label: Law Applies To Object In Situation
lawAppliesToObjectInSituation

comment:
(genlMtWithMonadIndexAndParameter MT GENL-MT MONAD TIME PAR) means that the following hold:

1. (genlMt MT GENL-MT)
2. (mtMonad MT MONAD)
3. (mtTimeIndex MT TIME)
4. (mtTimeParameter MT PAR)
label: Genl Mt With Monad Index And Parameter
genlMtWithMonadIndexAndParameter
Semi Transparent Situation Type Predicate
semiTransparentSituationTypePredicate
comment: A characteristic predicated of instances of SituationTypePredicate. If (semiTransparentSituationTypePredicate PRED) and PRED is used to express a GAF where the second, "situation type" argument is expressed as (CollectionSubsetFn Situation (TheSetOf FORMULA)) and FORMULA provably entails ENTFORMULA in CycL, then an analogous GAF holds for PRED in which the other argument or arguments are the same as before, and the 'sit type' argument is (CollectionSubsetFn Situation (TheSetOf ENTAILEDFORMULA)). More collocquially, if a situation type predicate is semiTransparentSituationTypePredicate and relates a #$SituationType with a certain definition to an argument or arguments, then it also relates any #$SituationType whose definition is a generalization of the first to the same argument or arguments.

(infectionRoute INFECTION-TYPE ORGANISM-TYPE PART-TYPE) means, colloquially, that organisms of type ORGANISM-TYPE are ordinarily vulnerable to infections of type INFECTION-TYPE through physical parts or features of type PART-TYPE, when some instance of an appropriate infection-causing pathogen penetrates the organism through such a part. More formally, it means that if an organism of the type ORGANISM-TYPE is penetrated by at least one instance of a pathogen such that this pathogen causes infections of type INFECTION-TYPE, and the penetration occurs through a physical part of the organism of type PART-TYPE, then the organism is vulnerableTo an infection of type INFECTION-TYPE caused by the pathogen, unless of course the organism is for some reason immune to infections of that kind. It also entails that a pathogen of a type capable of causing infections of type INFECTION-TYPE is capable of entering an organism of type ORGANISM-TYPE through a physical part of type PART-TYPE.
label: Infection Route
infectionRoute

comment: (hypotheticalTerm TERM) states that TERM is a term that was hypothesized. The most common reason a term is hypothesized is to pose a hypothetical query to Cyc.
label: Hypothetical Term
hypotheticalTerm

comment: A quaternary MetaRelation predicate for stating that a certain kind of complex, partly genlPreds based relationship holds between a given argument to a given function and the corresponding value that is returned. (interArgResultGenlPred FUNC N INDEPENDENT-ARG-PRED DEPENDENT-ARG-PRED) means that, when SPEC is a specialization of INDEPENDENT-ARG-PRED such that (genlPreds SPEC-PRED INDEPENDENT-ARG-PRED) holds, if SPEC-PRED appears as the Nth argument to FUNC, then (regardless of what the other arguments to FUNC might be) the value (if any) of that function for those arguments is a predicate that is a specialization of DEPENDENT-ARG-PRED. That is: if SPEC-PRED is a predicate that is a specialization of INDEPENDENT-ARG-PRED and (FUNC ARG(1) ... ARG(N-1) SPEC-PRED ...) = VALUE, then VALUE is a predicate that is a specialization of DEPENDENT-ARG-PRED. Note that, unlike (e.g.) the InterArgTypePredicates, interArgResultGenlPred _cannot_ be used to put semantic well-formedness constraints on functions.
label: Inter Arg Result Genl Pred
interArgResultGenlPred

comment: (punishmentFor x y z) denotes agent x is punished as described in punishment y because proposition z is true.
label: Punishment For
punishmentFor

comment:
(foreignKeyConstraintWithActionType REFERENCED-SCHEMA REFERENCED-KEY REFERENCING-SCHEMA REFERENCING-FIELD-LIST MODIFY-TYPE RESTRICTION-TYPE) means that:

1. A foreign key reference (see foreignKeyMap) holds between REFERENCED-SCHEMA, REFERENCED-KEY, REFERENCING-SCHEMA, and REFERENCING-FIELD-LIST;

2. Whenever an agent attempts to perform a database modification of type MODIFY-TYPE on a record in the table corresponding to REFERENCED-SCHEMA that will modify one or more of the values of the REFERENCED-KEY fields, then the database management system will enforce an integrity constraint of type RESTRICTION-TYPE.
label: Foreign Key Constraint With Action Type
foreignKeyConstraintWithActionType

comment: This predicate relates performers to types of actions. (skillLevel OBJ ACT-TYPE ROLE PERF-ATT LEVEL) means that the SomethingExisting OBJ has the ability to play the role ROLE in instances of the type of Event ACT-TYPE, with LEVEL degree of PERF-ATT. For example, (skillLevel Joe DiggingAHole performedBy Agility highAmountOf) means that, in general, Joe can dig holes with great agility. To talk about actual performance in a particular action, use performanceLevel.
label: Skill Level
skillLevel

comment: enables_MakesComplCapable expresses the notion that an agent is rendered completely capable (in the sense of capableOf) of doing something by a certain state of affairs -- a situation, that is, or, perhaps more frequently, an event. 'Being completely capable' implies that, were one to attempt to do something, one would in fact succeed. More accurately, (enables_MakesComplCapable SIT AGENT ACT_TYPE) is true iff SIT obtains, AGENT is completely capable of performing actions of type ACT_TYPE, and SIT is in fact what causes AGENT to be completely capable of performing a token of ACT_TYPE. An example: a military unit's clearing and securing a given area makes another unit completely capable of advancing through that area; short of extremely unlikely accident, the second unit would pass through, were it to attempt. An example in which this predicate does NOT apply: merely giving an ax to someone of ordinary physical build and skills does not amount to making him completely capable of chopping down a tree, for even with the ax he may lack the strength, training, etc., necessary to ensure that he would succeed were he to try. The 'enabling' in this case consists in the removal of a preventing factor, namely the lack of a proper tool -- see enables_RemovesDisablingFactors.
label: Enables Makes Compl Capable
enables-MakesComplCapable

comment:
A unary #$InferenceCompletenessPredicate and a specialization of completeExtentDecidable and minimizeExtent (qq.v.) that applies to predicates whose entire extents can be enumerated by the CycInferenceEngine. (completeExtentEnumerable PRED) means that the Inference Engine can, without using transformations, generate a list of all of (and only) the sequences of things among which PRED holds (see relationExtension and relationHoldsAmong).

For example, (completeExtentEnumerable assertedSentence) holds, as the Inference Engine could, if asked, list all of the assertions in the Knowledge Base. Conversely, although the Inference engine could correctly determine if any given CycL sentence is in the extent of knownSentence (i.e completeExtentDecidable holds of knownSentence), it could not generate a list of all CycL sentences in the extent of knownSentence.

The practical import of completeExtentEnumerable can be stated more precisely as follows. Let's say that an N-length sequence of terms "pointwise-denotes" an N-length sequence of things just in case each term in the former denotes the corresponding item in the latter. Suppose (completeExtentEnumerable PRED) holds. If PRED is a FixedArityRelation of arity N and VAR1...VARN are N distinct CycLVariables, then, given a query of the form (PRED VAR1 ... VARN), the Inference Engine can, without the use of Transformation Modules, return a list of N-length sequences of terms -- each sequence consisting of bindings for the respective variables VAR1-VARN -- such that every sequence in PRED's extent (and nothing else) is pointwise-denoted by some term-sequence on the list. If PRED is a VariableArityRelation, it is the same, except the given query should then have the form (PRED . VARS), and there might be no constant length N shared by all of the term-sequences in the returned list.

If PRED's extent is completely enumerable and a given term-sequence <TERM-1, ..., TERM-N> is not in the list returned for the above query, that fact consitutes a strong argument for the truth of the negation (not (PRED TERM-1 ... TERM-N)), assuming that it's semantically well-formed. But note that it is not a conclusive argument: the normally-reliable "unique name assumption" might fail here, and some term TERM-I could conceivably denote something that Cyc can prove to be a member of something in the extent of PRED only under some other CycL name it has. For suppose #$Pace was also denoted by the (imaginary) CycL term ErasmusCAnderson, but Cyc did not know that #$Pace and Erasmus C. Anderson are the same person. Cyc will return the term-sequence <#$Pace, GeneralCycKE> for the query (cyclistPrimaryProject ?X ?Y); but it might nevertheless fail to return the sequence <ErasmusCAnderson, GeneralCycKE>, even though the sentence 

  (cyclistPrimaryProject ErasmusCAnderson GeneralCycKE)
was in fact true.
label: Complete Extent Enumerable
completeExtentEnumerable

comment: If (mostNotableIsaInContext X COL CNTXT), then X is an instance of (isa) COL, and in the Microtheory CNTXT, COL is the most important or most obvious collection of which X is an instance. In other words, COL is what typically comes to mind in that context as an answer to the question, "What is X?" For example, in the context of human activities, a side of beef might be considered most notably food, whereas in the context of human vegetarian activities it might be considered most notably to be an animal carcass.
label: Most Notable Isa In Context
mostNotableIsaInContext

comment: (missionActionOnTypeWithFeatures MISSION ACT-TYPE LIST-OF-COLS) means that the mission MISSION requires an instance of ACT-TYPE to have as the objectActedOn some thing which is an instance of each of each of the collections in LIST-OF-COLS.
label: Mission Action On Type With Features
missionActionOnTypeWithFeatures

comment: (posPredConstraintForNCR RULE INDEXICAL POSPRED) means that RULE requires its NounCompoundRuleIndexicalTerm_Direct term INDEXICAL to satisfy the TermPhrasesConstraint associated with POSPRED. In general, this means that there will a ncRuleConstraint relating rule RULE to the constraint (NCPOSPredConstraintFn INDEXICAL POSPRED).
label: Pos Pred Constraint For NCR
posPredConstraintForNCR

comment: A 3-place relation between an event type, an actor slot and an actor slot filler. (resultantStateObtains TYPE SLOT FILLER) means that FILLER is in a state resulting from playing the role SLOT in an instance of TYPE. It presupposes, in other words, that an occurrence of TYPE has happened. A relevant use of this predicate is in linking perfect-tense assertions in instances of AspectTenseMicrotheory to their associated states, i.e., the resultative states of events of the given type. Note that this is a type-level predicate, unlike postSituations, which relates an particular event or situation to a particular individual regardless of role played.
label: Resultant State Obtains
resultantStateObtains

comment: (exclusiveCandidateSubSituationTypes SIT-TYPE SUB-SIT-TYPE1 SUB-SIT-TYPE2) means that no instance of SIT-TYPE has instances of both SUB-SIT-TYPE1 and SUB-SIT-TYPE2 as sub-situations.
label: Exclusive Candidate Sub Situation Types
exclusiveCandidateSubSituationTypes

comment: (keIrrelevantPrecisionSuggestion_Precisify TERM) says that TERM is never to be offered as by the precision suggestor as a possible specification.
label: Ke Irrelevant Precision Suggestion Precisify
keIrrelevantPrecisionSuggestion-Precisify

comment: (formulaTemplateFollowUp TEMPLATE1 TEMPLATE2 LOGICAL-CONNECTIVE) means that TEMPLATE2 is a clause that could optionally be added to TEMPLATE1 using LOGICAL-CONNECTIVE. For example, if (formulaForFormulaTemplate Template01 (and (isa ?OCEAN BodyOfWater) (bordersOn ?OCEAN UnitedStatesOfAmerica))), and (formulaForFormulaTemplate Template02 (lengthOfObject ?THING (Kilometer 14500)), and we want the two templates to optionally combine as a conjunction, then (formulaTemplateFollowUp Template01 Template02 and).
label: Formula Template Follow Up
formulaTemplateFollowUp
Action Sequence
actionSequence
comment: (actionSequence (TheList FORM_1 FORM_2 ... FORM_n)) means that the actions described by the action formulas FORM_i were performed in the order indicated. Each FORM_i should be an atomic formula whose predicate is an instance of ActionPredicate.
(makeTCPConnectionToComputer AGENT COMPUTER TARGET) means that AGENT uses COMPUTER to make a TCP connection to TARGET.
label: Make TCP Connection To Computer
makeTCPConnectionToComputer
Checked Via NL Tool
checkedViaNLTool
comment: (checkedViaNLTool WORD DATE) means that WORD was run through an NL tool on DATE. See spec preds for more on how these meta assertions are being used.

(durationBetweenSubSituationTypes SITTYPE SUBSITTYPE1 SUBSITTYPE2 DUR) means that if INST is an instance of SITTYPE where SIT1 and SIT2 are any two properSubSituations of INST such that (startsAfterEndingOf SIT2 SIT1) and (isa SIT1 SUBSITTYPE1) and (isa SIT2 SUBSITTYPE2), there exists a time interval INT of duration DUR such that (timeIntervalBetween INT SIT1 SIT2).
label: Duration Between Sub Situation Types
durationBetweenSubSituationTypes

comment: (chromaInRange BRIGHT VALUE-1 VALUE-2) means that CHROMA is a MunsellChroma with a value somewhere between VALUE-1 and VALUE-2 on the Munsell scale of saturation. Munsell chromas are represented using MunsellChromaFn. For further information, please see MunsellChroma and the #$SharedNoteOnMunsellSystemOfColorClassification.
label: Chroma In Range
chromaInRange

comment: (providesCoverToFrom OBJ REGION1 REGION2) means that the OBJ provides some measure of Cover at REGION1 from the direct or indirect fires from REGION2. Cover is an OCOKA principle that focuses on maximizing the protection troops have from direct and indirect fires. Its contrasting principle is that of Fields of Fire. Units with good cover limit the Fields of Fire for opposing units, and units with good fields of Fire have limited the Cover for opposing units. Although it is usually important to maintain good Cover, this may not always be desirable. For example, if an operation is speed-dependant, Cover may impede a force's ability to move quickily. This principle must be balanced with the other OCOKA principles, as well as those of METT-TC.
label: providing cover to from fires from
providesCoverToFrom
subPropertyOf: limitation on observation from a particular place

comment: (situationMightBeSubSituationType SIT SIT-TYPE SUB-SIT-TYPE) means that there is evidence to the effect that SIT is an instance of SUB-SIT-TYPE, which is a sub-situation type (see subSituationTypes) of SIT-TYPE.
label: Situation Might Be Sub Situation Type
situationMightBeSubSituationType

comment: (candidateReplacementForPosition TEMPLATE POS SET-OR-COLLECTION) means that for formula template TEMPLATE, the term that is in arg position POS of the formula can be replaced by any member of SET-OR-COLLECTION. It also means that (positionInFormulaTemplateIsReplaceable TEMPLATE POS).
label: Candidate Replacement For Position
candidateReplacementForPosition

comment: This predicate is the 'inverse' version of similarWRTTypeViaBinRel, in that (similarWRTTypeViaBinRel_Inverse THING1 THING2 COL PRED) means that if there is an instance of COL, COLINS1 such that (BINPRED COLINS1 THING1) then either (BINPRED COLINS1 THING2) or there is some similar instance of COL, COLINS2, such that (BINPRED COLINS2 THING2).
label: Similar WRT Type Via Bin Rel Inverse
similarWRTTypeViaBinRel-Inverse

comment: A RuleMacroPredicate, useful for stating tersely what the state of matter (see stateOfMatter) of all instances of a given type is, at a certain temperature. (stateOfMatterAtTemperature TYPE STATE TEMPERATURE) says that for every instance INS of TYPE such that (temperatureOfObject INS TEMPERATURE), (stateOfMatter INS STATE) is true.
label: State Of Matter At Temperature
stateOfMatterAtTemperature

comment: '(inheritRolePlayers_SubSitTypeToSitType SIT-TYPE ROLE1 SUBSIT-TYPE ROLE2) means that in any instance SIT of SIT-TYPE whatever things play ROLE2 in sub-situations of SIT that are instances of SUBSIT-TYPE also play ROLE1 in SIT.
label: Inherit Role Players Sub Sit Type To Sit Type
inheritRolePlayers-SubSitTypeToSitType

comment: (constituentMass ?obj ?constituent ?mass) means ?obj has ?mass amount of ?constituent as a constituents.
label: Constituent Mass
constituentMass
Mt Trivial For Justification Paraphrase
mtTrivialForJustificationParaphrase
comment: (mtTrivialForJustificationParaphrase MT) means that when any support (cf.CycSupportDatastructure) in MT is used in a proof, a paraphrase of that proof need not explicitly mention the support, as a human can be expected to consider it obvious.

(totalRoledTypeInType NUM ROLE TYPE-PLAYING-ROLE TYPE) means that NUM is the total number of things of TYPE-PLAYING-ROLE that played ROLE in situations of TYPE. For instance, (totalRoledTypeInType 10000 organismKilled Person TerroristAttack) means that, as far as we know in the KB, a total of 10000 persons were killed in terrorist attack.
label: Total Roled Type In Type
totalRoledTypeInType

comment: (greaterThanOrEqualWRTScalar IND1 IND2 PRED) means that PRED relates IND1 to some value that is greater than or equal to the value to which PRED relates IND2.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: amount comparisons : greater than or equal to with respect to scalar
label: amount comparison : greater than or equal to with respect to scalar
greaterThanOrEqualWRTScalar

comment: A CanonicalizerDirectivePredicate (q.v.) used (in conjunction with a CanonicalizerDirective) to control the behavior of the CycCanonicalizer. (canonicalizerDirectiveForArgAndRest RELN N DIRECTIVE) means that the CycCanonicalizer obeys DIRECTIVE when canonicalizing the Nth and subsequent (i.e. (N+1)th, (N+2)th, ...) arguments of any CycLFormula whose main (or "0th place") operator denotes RELN. See the instances of CanonicalizerDirective for more information on how particular directives affect canonicalization. Also see canonicalizerDirectiveForArg and canonicalizerDirectiveForAllArgs.
label: Canonicalizer Directive For Arg And Rest
canonicalizerDirectiveForArgAndRest

comment: (cycLQueryTypeVariableConstraints QUERY-TYPE VAR MEANING-SENT) means that VAR is an open or existentially bound CycLVariable in the CycLFormula for the query run during events of type QUERY-TYPE, and MEANING-SENT expresses the constraints on VAR.
label: Cyc L Query Type Variable Constraints
cycLQueryTypeVariableConstraints

comment: (penaltyForInfraction GAME INFRACT PENALTY) states that during sports events of type GAME, if a competitor commits an infraction of the type INFRACT, then the agents enforcing the sporting event make that competitor perform a penalty of type PENALTY.
label: penalty
penaltyForInfraction

comment:
(functionDescribesSlotValueForThingInArgDuring FUNCTION SLOT THING N EVENT) means that the Function_Denotational FUNCTION determines the values of the functional slot SLOT with Thing THING as its Nth argument during the Event EVENT.

For example, (functionDescribesSlotValueForThingInArgDuring Function001 altitudeAboveSeaLevel Object001 1 Event001) means that at each time point during Event001, Function001 returns the functional value of altitudeAboveSeaLevel given Object001 as the first argument to altitudeAboveSeaLevel.
label: Function Describes Slot Value For Thing In Arg During
functionDescribesSlotValueForThingInArgDuring

comment:
(slotForTypeHasValueWRTType TYPE1 TYPE2 SLOT VALUE-PRED) holds just in case a typical instance of TYPE1's value in the second argument of SLOT is VALUE-PRED with respect to typical instances of TYPE2 (that are not instances of TYPE2). For example, to state that store credit cards have a high interest rate compared to other credit cards we assert: 
(slotForTypeHasValueWRTType StoreChargeCard CreditCard_RevolvingAccount  
                                                   interestRate highAmountOf)
.
label: Slot For Type Has Value WRT Type
slotForTypeHasValueWRTType

comment:
A RuleMacroPredicate. (relationMostInstance BINPRED COL THING) means that most instances INST of COL are such that (BINPRED INST THING) holds. It is equivalent to the more complex form: 
(most COL (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToFn COL BINPRED THING)).
For example, (relationMostInstance knowsAbout Philosopher Aristotle) means that most philosophers know about Aristotle. See also relationMostExists.
label: Relation Most Instance
relationMostInstance

comment: `(coinhabitDuringYear YEAR PERSON1 PERSON2)' means that PERSON1 and PERSON2 are considered members of the same household for the year YEAR A.D. according to IRS standards. The main purpose of this predicate is to enable the writing of rules that don't involve holdsIn.
label: Coinhabit During Year
coinhabitDuringYear

comment: This is the predicate corresponding to CollectionDifferenceFn. (collectionDifference DIFFERENCE COL1 COL2) means that DIFFERENCE is the collection containing all instances of COL1 which are not instances of COL2.
label: Collection Difference
collectionDifference

comment: (candidateFallsBetweenArgsWRTOrderingByPred_Exclusive PRED THING LOWER-BOUND UPPER-BOUND) means that as a result of some user interaction it has been determined that it is likely that THING falls between LOWER-BOUND and UPPER-BOUND, exclusive, in the (partial) ordering determined by PRED. PRED is a predicate that induces at least a partial ordering of the members of its domain. For instance, heightOfObject induces a partial ordering of the members of its domain by virtue of the fact that all objects in the domain of that predicate can be partially ordered by height.
label: Candidate Falls Between Args WRT Ordering By Pred Exclusive
candidateFallsBetweenArgsWRTOrderingByPred-Exclusive

comment: (strategyApplicableToHypotheses STRATEGY HYP1 HYP2) means that the two instances of EvaluatableHypothesisMicrotheory HYP1 and HYP2 enter into the semantic relationship that the ScoringSoftwareStrategy STRATEGTY rewards.
label: Strategy Applicable To Hypotheses
strategyApplicableToHypotheses

comment: (controlTransferAndUseOfFor ACT-TYPE OBJ-TYPE ROLE) means that the specialization of PurposefulAction_ResourceDrivenWithTransfer ACT-TYPE is the type of event in which instances of the specialization of SomethingExisting OBJ-TYPE are controlled and transferred to play ROLE in a further event.
label: Control Transfer And Use Of For
controlTransferAndUseOfFor

comment: (interArgNotIsa PRED FIRST-ARG FIRST-COL SECOND-ARG SECOND-COL) means that, when an instance of FIRST-COL appears as argument # FIRST-ARG to PRED, argument # SECOND-ARG in that assertion is constrained not to be an instance of SECOND-COL and vice versa.
label: Inter Arg Not Isa
interArgNotIsa

comment: This is the predicate corresponding to SetOrCollectionDifferenceFn. (setOrCollectionDifference SOC1 SOC2 DIFFERENCE) means that DIFFERENCE is the SetOrCollection containing all elements of SOC1 which are not elements of SOC2.
label: Set Or Collection Difference
setOrCollectionDifference

comment: A specialization of locatedInBoundingBoxWithCoordinates (q.v.). (locatedInBoundingBoxWithCoordinates_Minimal PLACE LAT-MAX LON-MIN LAT-MIN LON-MAX) means that the bounding box specified by the corner points LAT-MAX, LON-MIN, LAT-MIN and LON-MAX is the smallest bounding box that can be constructed to fully contain PLACE.
label: Located In Bounding Box With Coordinates Minimal
locatedInBoundingBoxWithCoordinates-Minimal
subPropertyOf: Located In Bounding Box With Coordinates

comment: (tableTypeForTypeAndSection TYPE SUM-PRED TABLE-TYPE) means that TABLE-TYPE is the type of table that should be generated in the sections delineated by SUM-PRED in any factsheet wherein an instance of TYPE is the focal term.
label: Table Type For Type And Section
tableTypeForTypeAndSection

comment: (supplyRateFrom PT1 COL PT2 RATE) means that the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 is supplied with instances of the Collection COL from the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2 at the Rate RATE. Like the predicate suppliedWith (q.v.), supplyRateFrom is very general. In various assertions PT1 might, for instance, be a Cell, a Person, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion; and likewise for PT2. The range of possible supplies is similarly broad.
label: Supply Rate From
supplyRateFrom
Query Extent Cached
queryExtentCached
comment: (queryExtentCached QUERY) is a performative predicate that evaluates QUERY and caches the results in the mt in which it is asserted.

label: Gen With Gloss
genWithGloss
comment: (genWithGloss PRED) means that the english for any rules beginning with PRED will be generated using an englishGloss assertion if there is one. If there isn't, english will be generated in the usual way using genFormats etc..
(sentenceRequiredForJustificationParaphrase SENT) means that when SENT is used in a transformation proof, a paraphrase of that proof should explicitly mention SENT.).
label: Sentence Required For Justification Paraphrase
sentenceRequiredForJustificationParaphrase

comment: This predicate expresses the notion of 'enabling' in the sense of furnishing to someone the skills she needs for the performance of a certain type of action. This is the sense in which training or education may be enabling factors in a person's life. Therefore, (enables_ImpartsSkills SIT AGENT ACT_TYPE) means that SIT causes AGENT to have skills sufficient for the successful performance of tokens of ACT_TYPE, assuming that the circumstances of SIT are favorable. In essence, SIT causes AGENT to be skillCapableOf ACT_TYPE: SIT cause AGENT to be in a certain state, the state we can label as 'having skills sufficient for ACT_TYPE'. The assumption that circumstances be favorable is necessary because even a skilled agent would not be expected to perform successfully if the general circumstances were unfavorable.
label: Enables Imparts Skills
enables-ImpartsSkills

comment: The corresponding predicate for the function AllotmentForOfTypeDuringFn.
label: Allotment For Of Type During
allotmentForOfTypeDuring

comment: (unchangedWRTIsa THING COLLECTION EVENT) means that THING is an instance of COLLECTION before, during, and after EVENT. This predicate is used for collections in which which membership may change over time [TimeDependentCollection] and for things which are involved (or plausibly may be involved) in EVENT in some way (see actors).
label: Unchanged WRTIsa
unchangedWRTIsa

comment: (excludeReplacementOptionForFormulaTemplatePosition TEMPLATE OPT POS) means that for the formula of TEMPLATE, candidates for replacement for the arg position POS should exclude those from replacement option OPT. By default, all instances of ReplacementOption are included as methods to get candidates to replace a term. excludeReplacementOptionForFormulaTemplatePosition means that terms that meet the criteria for OPT should no longer be considered candidates for arg position POS. Note that since the argument position might be nested inside the formula, POS defines the position using a variable number of non-negative integers. See FormulaArgPositionFn.
label: Exclude Replacement Option For Formula Template Position
excludeReplacementOptionForFormulaTemplatePosition

comment: typeOfTimeOfHour is the corresponding predicate to the function TimeOfHourFn. An assertion of the form (typeOfTimeOfHour TIMEOFHOUR MINUTE SECOND) states that the TimeOfHourType TIMEOFHOUR is composed out of the MinuteOfHourType MINUTE and the SecondOfMinuteType SECOND. So, (typeOfTimeOfHour (TimeOfHourFn (MinuteOfHourFn 12) (SecondOfMinuteFn 12)) (MinuteOfHourFn 12) (SecondOfMinuteFn 12)) states that (TimeOfHourFn (MinuteOfHourFn 12) (SecondOfMinuteFn 12)) denotes the collection of every CalendarSecond that is the twelfth CalendarSecond of the twelfth CalendarMinute of some CalendarHour.
label: Type Of Time Of Hour
typeOfTimeOfHour

comment: (lastRoleInEventType INDIV TYPE ACTOR-SLOT EVENT TIME) means that, as of TIME, EVENT is the last instance of TYPE in which INDIV has occupied ACTOR-SLOT. For instance, if (lastRoleInEventType AbrahamLincoln EntertainmentPerformance spectators Event008 (YearFn 1988)), Event008 would be the final event in which Abraham Lincoln watched an entertainment performance. (Presumably, Event008 took place in the Ford Theater shortly before the #$AssassinationOfPresidentLincoln.) See also firstRoleInEventType.
label: Last Role In Event Type
lastRoleInEventType

comment: (natArgument NAT N TERM) means that TERM is in the Nth argument position of the non-atomic term NAT. For example, (natArgument (JuvenileFn Dog) 1 Dog). Note that (termOfUnit NAT (FUNCTION ... ARGN ...)) implies (natArgument NAT N ARGN).

comment:
An HLPredicate that is used to state which literals in a forward rule should not be allowed to re-trigger forward inference. This is useful for placing pragmatic restrictions on the applicability of forward rules. It is only useful when used via pragmaticRequirement on a forward rule.

A pragmatic requirement of the form 

(pragmaticRequirement (forwardNonTriggerLiteral FORMULA) RULE),
where FORMULA is a literal in the antecedent of RULE, ensures that new assertions that are instantiations of FORMULA do not trigger RULE.
label: Forward Non Trigger Literal
forwardNonTriggerLiteral

comment: (exceptMt MT) means that (except ASSERTION) is true for all ASSERTIONs asserted in MT. In other words, in the current microtheory ASSERTION is not known to be true. If ASSERTION is a rule, it will not fire.

comment: (eventTypesOverlapInEvent FIRST SECOND MAIN) means that during an instance, M-INS, of MAIN, any instance of SECOND that is a subevent (subEvents) of M-INS will start during some instance of FIRST which is a subevent of MAIN. For instance, during hockey games, ice cleaning occurs during the intermission so we could assert (eventTypesOverlapInEvent Intermission IceCleaning PlayingOf_HockeyGame). Note that (eventTypesOverlapInEvent FIRST MAIN SECOND) does _not_ imply either that (i) each instance of MAIN has a subevent of type FIRST or of type SECOND, or, given an instance of MAIN, MAIN-INST, that does have a subevent of type FIRST, that (ii) it's having such a subevent entails it having a subevent of type SECOND. See also startsDuringInSituationType and #$startsDuringInScript-Ternary for application to scripts.
label: Event Types Overlap In Event
eventTypesOverlapInEvent

comment: An instance of TernaryPredicate, used to relate an instance of BiologicalLivingObject to the recommended allowance of some type of sustenance. (recommendedAllowanceForBLO BLO TYPE AMOUNT) says that it is recommended that BLO ingest AMOUNT of TYPE. For example, (recommendedAllowanceForBLO Person001 (LiquidFn Water) ((PerFn Cup_UnitOfVolume DaysDuration) 8)) says that it is recommended that Person001 consume 8 cups of water per day. Who or what is doing the recommendation is unspecified with this predicate; accordingly, assertions should go in a Microtheory (for example, the ContextOfPCWFn for some conceptual work on nutrition) that makes the source clear. Note, too, that this is a TemporallyQualifiableRelation: The recommendation for an animal that is sick for some period of time might be different for when that same animal is healthy.
label: Recommended Allowance For BLO
recommendedAllowanceForBLO

comment: This event-predicate template expresses the relation between the agent (active participant) and the tool or device s/he uses in an activity. comment: The predicate positionOfPersonInOrganization is used to relate a particular person to his or her position in a particular organization. (positionOfPersonInOrganization PERSON ORG POS-TYPE) means that the Person PERSON is a member of the Organization ORG, and holds a position of type POS-TYPE. Even in an employment situation, POS-TYPE may or may not specifically indicate PERSON 's occupational field or training; for example, one individual occupying a position of Manager may be a MarketingPerson, while another is an ElectricalEngineer. In addition, POS-TYPE may or may not correspond to an official `Job Title' (cf. titleOfPersonInOrganization), or be the primary occupation of PERSON . Note that assertions using positionOfPersonInOrganization should be properly time-constrained.
label: person's position in an organization
positionOfPersonInOrganization

comment:
A ternary RotationalOrientationPredicate that relates a HexalateralObject to a CartesianCoordinateSystem to an AngularDistance. (normalOrientationInCoordinateSystem OBJ SYSTEM DIST) means that DIST is the angular distance that OBJ has "strayed" (so to speak) from its standard or original rotational orientation about its normal (top-to-bottom) axis in SYSTEM. (See #$NoteOnStandardRotationalOrientation.)

In flight dynamics, the normal orientation of an aircraft is known as its "yaw".

See also lateralOrientationInCoordinateSystem and longitudinalOrientationInCoordinateSystem.

comment: A predicate for stating the frequency with which typical instances of some type of TemporalThing play certain roles in certain types of event. Specifically, (frequencyOfActionType ACTTYPE ACTORTYPE ROLE FREQUENCY) indicates that typical instances of ACTORTYPE (where ACTORRTYPE is a specialization of TemporalThing) play the role ROLE in instances of ACTTYPE (where ACTTYPE is a specialization of Event) with the frequency FREQUENCY. For example, frequencyOfActionType can be used to express the fact that typical vertebrates are virtually always breathing: (frequencyOfActionType Breathing Vertebrate bodilyDoer Continuously). This predicate should _not_ be used for action types that instances of ACTORTYPE do not typically perform role ROLE in, even if those instances of ACTORTYPE that do, do so with frequency FREQUENCY. For those kinds of assertions, use regularFrequencyOfActionType.
label: Frequency Of Action Type
frequencyOfActionType

The `everything else being equal' clause indicates that the value of SLOT for THING might change, even increase, were more information to become available -- that is, the SLOT-value assignment to THING might change, even holding SENT true, if additional sentences were known to be true. This is the propositional version of decreasesSitSlot_Subjective. See increasesSitSlot_Subjective for more extensive documentation.
