Was (unary predicate)
was
comment: was is a ModalOperator, commonly referred to as a `past-tense operator'. For each #$ELSentence-Assertible PROP, (was PROP) means that it was the case that PROP. For example, (was `Amy and Bob are friends') means that Amy and Bob were friends. was has a dual operator: hasAlwaysBeen. Note that (was PROP) does not imply that (not PROP). Note also that was should be used only in instances of TemporalMicrotheory. Strictly speaking, (was PROP) is true in a temporal microtheory MT with time index t and time parameter p (two `dimensions' in the context space, see mtTimeIndex and mtTimeIndexWithParameter) iff PROP is true in a temporal microtheory MT' with time index t' < t and time parameter p', which has the same values of all other dimensions as MT. Here t' < t means (startsAfterEndingOf t t'). It is easy to verify that (was PROP) is true in a temporal microtheory MT with time index t and time parameter p iff it is true in every temporal microtheory MT' that has the same values of all dimensions except the time parameter (another way to put this is that time parameters doesn't matter when dealing with (was PROP)). (See other plain tense operators willBe, hasAlwaysBeen and willAlwaysBe, and metric tense predicates was_Metric and willBe_Metric etc.)
(hypothesisVisualizationTableForPeg PEG WIDTH TABLE) means that TABLE is an HTML table source string graphically illustrating the extent to which PEG has rewrites with hypothesized interpretations.

comment: (hasInterAgentStatusWith AGENT1 AGENT2 STATUS) means that AGENT2 has STATUS with respect to AGENT1. For example, it is believed that, at least until the US invasion of Afghanistan, (hasInterAgentStatusWith #$AlQaida Afghanistan SupportOfSponsorshipOfTerrorism). This predicate is useful for talking about people and political entities like countries. Countries (and their political leaders) change and obviously so does the status they attribute to people so uses of this predicate should be temporally qualified.
label: Has Inter Agent Status With
hasInterAgentStatusWith

areaToProtect
comment: (areaToProtect ?ENTITY) means that ?ENTITY is being protected. This predicate is used in the context of goals and causes.

A quaternary rule-macro predicate used for stating that there are a certain number of assertions of a particular form in the Cyc Knowledge Base. (assertedPredicateArgCardinality THING ARGNUM PRED N) means that there are currently in the KB exactly N assertions of the form 
  (PRED ...THING...)
where (a CycL term denoting) THING appears in the Nth argument-position.

For example, (assertedPredicateArgCardinality PresidentFn 1 arg1Isa 1) means that there is exactly one asserted arg1Isa constraint on PresidentFn.

Note that the above does not imply that no other sentence of the relevant form is derivable. Indeed, given the assertion (arg1Isa PresidentFn Organization), it follows by transitiveViaArg (q.v.) reasoning that (arg1Isa PresidentFn Individual) is also true.

See also assertedPredicateArg.
label: Asserted Predicate Arg Cardinality
assertedPredicateArgCardinality

programAlgorithmInputs

comment: (playsRoleTypicalOf OBJ OBJ-TYPE EVENT) means that, in a particular instance of Event EVENT, one would usually expect an instance of OBJ-TYPE to play an instrumental role. In this particular event, however, that role is being played by OBJ, an object of another type. For instance, (playsRoleTypicalOf JimsScalpel CarvingKnife CuttingTheTurkeyAtThanksgiving2000) means that there is some role in that particular CuttingAPieceOfFood event that one would expect to be played by a carving knife, but in this case that role is being played by Jim's scalpel.

comment: (chemicalEquation_Unbalanced REACTION-TYPE REACTANT-LIST PRODUCT-LIST) means that in ChemicalReactions of type REACTION-TYPE instances of the substances included in REACTANT-LIST react to form instances of the substances included in PRODUCT-LIST. By the meaning of this predicate one should not assume that the equilibrium of REACTION-TYPE lies entirely to the right of the equation.

comment: (adjustedEPSForPeriodByAccountingCOC ORG MONEY TIME COC) means MONEY is the amount that would be earned (i.e. profit) by ORG per share of stock during the time interval that is subsumed by TIME according to the calculation techniques allowed by the AccountingCOC COC, if all amortization and exceptional costs to ORG were added back to ORG's profits. This value is called "adjusted EPS" or "headline EPS" (because it is often the EPS reported by companies). The exact nature of the adjustments made varies from company to company. See also adjustedEarningsPerShare_ForStockType.
label: Adjusted EPS For Period By Accounting COC
adjustedEPSForPeriodByAccountingCOC

comment: (hasPathologyAtLocation CVPD EVENT LOC-TYPE PATH-TYPE) means that according to the CVD associated with EVENT the focal valve has the pathology PATH-TYPE at the lcoation type LOC-TYPE.

comment: (nearestCommonIsa THING1 THING2 NEAR-COL) means that NEAR-COL is a "nearest" collection of which both THING1 and THING2 are instances. That is, both (isa THING1 NEAR-COL) and (isa THING2 NEAR-COL) hold, and there is no reified Collection NEARER-COL distinct from NEAR-COL such that (isa THING1 NEARER-COL), (isa THING2 NEARER-COL) and (genls NEARER-COL NEAR-COL) all hold. Note that this predicate is non-assertible (see notAssertible), since its extension at any given time depends upon (and so must be computed from) the current state of the isa and genls hierarchies in the Cyc Knowledge Base. See also nearestCommonGenls and nearestCommonSpecs.
label: Nearest Common Isa
nearestCommonIsa

comment: The predicate actsInCapacity indicates the capacity in which an agent participates in certain kinds of actions. (actsInCapacity AGENT ROLE SCRIPT-TYPE CAP) means that the agent AGENT plays the role ROLE in instances of SCRIPT-TYPE, and s/he does that role in the capacity CAP. CAP is a CapacityPredicate (q.v.) which describes the AGENT's mode of participation--e.g., as a job, hobby, main function, support function, etc. Contrast three cases of acts of GreetingSomeone, when performedBy: (1) instances of Receptionist, in their actsInCapacity_JobCapacity and as their actsInCapacity_MainFunction; (2) instances of FlightAttendant, in their actsInCapacity_JobCapacity but as a #$SupportFunction; and (3) instances of TrainEngineer, in a actsInCapacity_HobbyCapacity (though they do it while working, it's not part of their job).
label: Acts In Capacity
actsInCapacity

A CycL description of the situation and involvement is then returned as a binding for ?Description. If more than one answer is available, multiple successive bindings are made to ?Description. If a list of roles, rather than a single role, is used as the value of ?Role, then all member values are considered in turn.

comment: (reusabilityOfTypeForType COL EVENTTYPE ROLE QUAN) means that after an instance of COL plays the role ROLE in an event of type EVENTTYPE, then QUAN indicates the likelihood to assign to its re-usability if one does not know how many times it has played that role before. If QUAN is a high value this indicates that things are unlikely to wear out after playing the indicated role. So we might say that (reusabilityOfTypeForType Hammer HammeringANail deviceUsed veryHighAmountOf) because hammers survive many hammering events without any decrease in functionality. However, (reusabilityOfTypeForType FacialTissue BlowingOnesNose deviceUsed veryLowAmountOf).
label: Reusability Of Type For Type
reusabilityOfTypeForType

label: loan agreement requirement on the creditor
loanAgreementRequiresOfCreditor

comment: '(delegatedAuthority DELEGATING SIT-TYPE ROLE)' means that the authority, power, or function to play ROLE in situations of type SIT-TYPE is delegated to the delegate by the DelegatingAuthority DELEGATING.
label: delegating authority
delegatedAuthority

comment: (numberOfPrescriptionsByDocTypeDuring ?DOC-TYPE ?DRUG-PROD ?PRESC-TYPE ?TIME ?NUM) means that, during the time interval ?TIME, MedicalCareProfessionals of type, ?DOC-TYPE, had ?NUM DrugPrescriptions for ?DRUG-PROD filled.
label: Number Of Prescriptions By Doc Type During
numberOfPrescriptionsByDocTypeDuring

comment: (worksWithInOrg ORG PERSON1 PERSON2) holds just in case PERSON1 and PERSON2 are members of ORG and work closely together or are in close contact with each other on a regular basis. Note: "work" in this context doesn't necessarily mean that ORG is their employer. Two volunteers at a local soup kitchen can stand in this relation if they are both part of the same charitable organization and often help out on the same evenings.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: had worked together in an organization
has worked together in an organization
have worked together in an organization
will have worked together in an organization
will work together in an organization
label: working together in an organization
worksWithInOrg

comment: (typesGreaterInQuantity COL1 COL2 QUANT-TYPE) means that instances of COL1 have more of QUANT-TYPE than instances of COL2. This cashes out as meaning every instance of COL11 is related to a value of QUANT-TYPE that is greater than any value had by an instance of COL2. So, for any VAL1, VAL2, if (QUANTITY-PRED INSTANCE-OF-COL1 VAL1) and (QUANTITY-PRED INSTANCE-OF-COL2 VAL2) and VAL1 and VAL2 are both instances of QUANT-TYPE, then (followingValue VAL2 VAL1). Note: QUANTITY-PRED in the above explanation is supposed to be the canonical quantity attribution predicate for use with QUANT-TYPE. Example: (typesGreaterInQuantity Dog Cat IntelligenceLevel) means that dogs have higher levels of intelligence than cats. This entails that any value for argument 2 in hasIntelligenceLevel when an instance of Dog is in argument 1 is higher than when an instance of Cat is in argument 1.
label: Types Greater In Quantity
typesGreaterInQuantity

comment:
A quaternary MetaFunction (q.v.) predicate used for stating that when a given function is applied to successive argument(-sequence)s that are related in a specified way, then the successive resulting values will themselves be related in another specified way. (intraArgRelnIntraResultReln FUNC N PRED-ARGS PRED-RESULTS) means that when FUNC is applied to successive argument-sequences ARGS1 and ARGS2 such that (i) ARGS1 and ARGS2 differ (at most) only in their respective Nth items ARGN1 and ARGN2 and (ii) (PRED-ARGS ARGN1 ARGN2) holds, then (PRED-RESULTS (FUNC . ARGS1) (FUNC . ARGS2)) holds. For example, (intraArgRelnIntraResultReln GroupOfCardinalityFn 2 different disjointWith) means that for any TYPE, N, and M, if N =/ M, then these two collections are disjoint: 

  (GroupOfCardinalityFn TYPE N)
  (GroupOfCardinalityFn TYPE M) .
label: Intra Arg Reln Intra Result Reln
intraArgRelnIntraResultReln
Exception Effect On Actor New Role
exceptionEffectOnActor-NewRole

comment: (obligationHasPriorityOverObligationForAgent PRIOR-OBLIGATION OBLIGATION AGENT) means that the instance AGENT of IntelligentAgent is obliged to fufill the instance PRIOR-OBLIGATION of Obligation before fufilling the distinct instance of Obligation OBLIGATION. Thus this predicate entails the existence of a third obligation that specifies which obligation takes priority.
label: Obligation Has Priority Over Obligation For Agent
obligationHasPriorityOverObligationForAgent

comment: (customary_SitRolePlayerOfType SIT ROLE CUSTOMARY-TYPE) means that it would follow custom or convention in some culture (see CulturalConvention_Specification) if at least one object playing ROLE in SIT were an instance of CUSTOMARY-TYPE. That is, it would follow custom if there were an instance CUSTOMARY-INS of CUSTOMARY-TYPE such that (ROLE SIT CUSTOMARY-INS). Assertions involving this predicate should be made in a context that reflects the contents of some IndividualCustom, or larger CulturalConvention_Specification.
label: Customary Sit Role Player Of Type
customary-SitRolePlayerOfType

comment: This predicate relates an element of a set to its "nearest neighbor" in the set. That is, (nearestNeighborInSet P Q SET) means that (i) P and Q are elements of SET, and (ii) P is the closest element to Q in SET, with respect to some "distance" function. Note that in general, it does not follow that Q is also the closest element to P in SET.
label: nearest neighbor
nearestNeighborInSet

comment:
A KBDependentRelation (q.v.) and specialization of assertedSentence (q.v.) that is used to state that a given CycLSentence_Assertible has been asserted in the KB (in some accessible Microtheory). More exactly, (exactlyAssertedSentence SENT) is true in microtheory MT precisely when SENT canonicalizes without commutative handling of the sentence args into a set of clauses of the same form as the canonicalized form of some assertion in a microtheory accessible to MT. (The predicate is thus true both of assertions entered into the KB by hand and assertions deduced by Cyc from forward rules.)

This predicate enables Cyc to select a subset of information when answering queries, filtering out more generic (asserted-without-commutative-canonicalization) information. Thus, for example, the query:

(assertedSentence (bordersOn CentralUSATimeZone EasternUSATimeZone))

will return True (in appropriate microtheories), whereas:

(exactlyAssertedSentence (bordersOn CentralUSATimeZone EasternUSATimeZone))

will not.
label: Exactly Asserted Sentence
exactlyAssertedSentence

comment: (mechanismOfAction DRUG EVENT ROLE) means that for the type of DrugSubstance DRUG, one of the mechanisms of action (i.e., the way, at the level of chemical interactions, in which it achieves its expected effects) is for its molecules to play the role ROLE in biochemical events of type EVENT.
label: Mechanism Of Action
mechanismOfAction

comment: This predicate relates each of the object schema types for a schema integration to the set of explicitly represented relationship defining schemas that relate some object defining schema of the given type. That is, (schemaIntegrationTypeForInputExplicitRDSSet INTEGRATION TYPE RDS-SET) means that in the schema integration INTEGRATION, each RelationshipDefiningSchema in the set RDS-SET relates some ObjectDefiningSchema of type TYPE (determined via schemaIsa). See also schemaIntegrationTypeForInputImplicitRDSSet.
label: Schema Integration Type For Input Explicit RDS Set
schemaIntegrationTypeForInputExplicitRDSSet
subPropertyOf: Schema Integration Type For Input RDS Set

comment: potentialDutyOfAgentType is a variant of potentialDutyOfAgent whose first argument is a type of ModernMilitaryUnit_Deployable rather than an instance of Agent_PartiallyTangible.
label: Potential Duty Of Agent Type
potentialDutyOfAgentType

comment: (closestHistoryPriorToWithStatus HIST EVT2 STATUS-TYPE) means that HIST is the nearest PastPatientHistory prior to EVT2 that contains an instance of STATUS-TYPE.
label: Closest History Prior To With Status
closestHistoryPriorToWithStatus

comment: (motivesForAction ACTION PRED AGENT THING) means one of the motives behind AGENT's performance of ACTION is AGENT's relationship PRED to THING during some period leading up to ACTION. For example, to express that AGENT's motive for committing a particular roberry is (his or her feelings of) greed, one can write (motivesForAction BankRobbery001 AGENT feelsEmotion (PositiveAmountFn Greed)). Where THING is an instance of CycLSentence_Assertible and PRED is an instance of CognitivePredicate, use the more specific reasonsForAction.
label: Motives For Action
motivesForAction

comment: An instance of ActionPredicate. (setRegistryKeyToValueOnComputer AGENT REG_KEY VALUE COMP) means that AGENT sets the RegistryKey REG_KEY on COMP to VALUE. Note that, for some instances of RegistryKey, VALUE may be an instance of MaliciousComputerProgram set by an evil hacker who has access to COMP. Or AGENT might be a friendly systems administrator trying to make his network #$CycSecure.
label: Set Registry Key To Value On Computer
setRegistryKeyToValueOnComputer

comment: An assertion of the form (notAbducibleWRTTypeInArg PRED TYPE N) states that abductive inferences should not seek to posit hypothetical values for the other arguments of PRED when an instance of TYPE fills the PRED's Nth argument position. Abductive inferences sometimes involving hypothesizing the existence of states of affairs. Abductive inferences often seek to explain an assertion or set of assertions by hypothesizing the truth of other assertions. However, we wish to restrict the kinds of assertions which Cyc will hypothesize such that Cyc does not hypothesize new theoretical or conceptual knowledge, or even contingent states of affairs that are quite rigidly constructed in the actual world. Thus, the assertion (notAbducibleWRTValueInArg cityInState State_UnitedStates 1) would prevent the Cyc inference engine from hypothesizing the existence of unknown cities within any of the states of the UnitedStatesOfAmerica.
label: Not Abducible WRT Type In Arg
notAbducibleWRTTypeInArg

comment: (zodiacSignDateRange SIGN BEGIN-DAY END-DAY) state that the range of dates for the #$ZodiacSign SIGN ranges from BEGIN-DAY to END-DAY. See also hasZodiacSign.
label: Zodiac Sign Date Range
zodiacSignDateRange

comment: (tourNightLodging TOUR DAY BLDG) means that on DAY, the participants in TOUR will spend the night at BLDG.
label: Tour Night Lodging
tourNightLodging

comment: An instance of TernaryPredicate. (propertiesOfSubstanceAtTemperature SUBSTANCE PROPERTY TEMPERATURE) says that when an instance of SUBSTANCE is at the temperature TEMPERATURE, it will have the property (will be an instance of) PROPERTY.
label: Properties Of Substance At Temperature
propertiesOfSubstanceAtTemperature

comment: For any N greater than or equal to 2, (coordinateSlot PRED1 PRED2 N) is true iff both (associateSlotInArg PRED1 SLOT N) and (associateSlotInArg PRED2 SLOT N).
label: Coordinate Slot
coordinateSlot

comment: This predicate relates agents to the kinds of things they dislike doing. (dislikesRoleInEventType AGENT ROLE EVENTTYPE) means that AGENT dislikes playing ROLE in events of the type EVENTTYPE. This entails that AGENT actually _has_ played -- and disliked playing -- ROLE in one or more instances of EVENTTYPE, and that s/he found most (if not all) such occasions unpleasant. Typically, AGENT will have played ROLE in a number of instances of EVENTTYPE. For example, (dislikesRoleInEventType Joe performedBy Running) means that Joe dislikes running. Cf. likesRoleInEventType.
label: Dislikes Role In Event Type
dislikesRoleInEventType

comment: (colorPropertiesOfSubstanceAtTemperature SUBSTANCE TYPE TEMPERATURE) means that instances of SUBSTANCE at Temperature TEMPERATURE typically exhibit the ColorPerceptionCategoryType TYPE. Chemists find this an easy and useful heuristic to identify some chemical substances.
label: Color Properties Of Substance At Temperature
colorPropertiesOfSubstanceAtTemperature

comment:
(closestEventPriorToWithinIntervalWithValueFor EVT1 EVT2 INTERVAL PROPERTY ) means that EVT1 is the nearest event prior to EVT2 within INTERVAL that has some value for PROPERTY. This entails that 
   
     (thereExists ?VALUE 
          (PROPERTY EVT1 ?VALUE))
In medical contexts it is assumed that both events involve the same patient.
label: Closest Echo Or Cath Event Prior To Within Interval With Value For CYC
closestEchoOrCathEventPriorToWithinIntervalWithValueFor-CYC

comment: The corresponding predicate of the function WorkOnSpecificationByAgentFn. It relates an instance of WorkingEvent to an instance of NormativeSpecification and an instance of IntelligentAgent and asserts that the WorkingEvent is the total work done by the IntelligentAgent towards bringing about the NormativeSpecification NORM-SPEC.
label: Work Done On Specification By Agent
workDoneOnSpecificationByAgent

comment: A KEFacilitationPredicate and RuleMacroPredicate. (keStrongSuggestionPredsInverse_SpecsOfType COL BINPRED TYPE) means that for every known (i.e. Cyc-reified) instance INST of COL, it is strongly suggested that there be some reified specialization SPEC of TYPE such that (BINPRED SPEC INST) is known in the Knowledge Base.
label: Ke Strong Suggestion Preds Inverse Specs Of Type
keStrongSuggestionPredsInverse-SpecsOfType

comment: An instance of TernaryPredicate. recommendedFoodOrDrinkAllowanceForBLO is a specialization-predicate recommendedAllowanceForBLO, where the arg1 is restricted to specializations of FoodOrDrink -- a category of high interest. (recommendedFoodOrDrinkAllowanceForBLO BLO TYPE AMOUNT) says that it is recommended that BLO ingest AMOUNT of food or drink of the type TYPE. For example, (recommendedFoodOrDrinkAllowanceForBLO Person001 (LiquidFn Water) ((PerFn Cup_UnitOfVolume DaysDuration) 8)) says that it is recommended that Person001 drink 8 cups of water per day. Who or what is doing the recommendation is unspecified with this predicate; accordingly, assertions should go in a Microtheory (for example, the PITOfIBTFn for some conceptual work on nutrition) that makes the source clear. Note, too, that this is a TemporallyQualifiableRelation: The recommendation for an animal that is sick for some period of time might be different for when that same animal is healthy.
label: Recommended Food Or Drink Allowance For BLO
recommendedFoodOrDrinkAllowanceForBLO

comment: (manageableSubEventTypesOnTour TOUR EVENTTYPE SUBEVENTTYPE) means that within the context of TOUR, a tourParticipants in TOUR can generally manage to perform an instance of SUBEVENTTYPE during the course of an event of type EVENTTYPE that occurs as part of the tour.
label: Manageable Sub Event Types On Tour
manageableSubEventTypesOnTour

comment: The predicate corresponding to VectorFn (q.v.).
label: Vector
vector

comment:
A ternary predicate that relates a pair of tangible objects, space regions, or spatially-localized events to their mereological symmetric difference. (spatialSymmetricDifference SYMDIFF THING1 THING2) means that SYMDIFF is the unique SpatialThing (of the same basic type as THING1 and THING2) such that a spatial thing intersects (see spatiallyIntersects) SYMDIFF if and only if it intersects with THING1 but is disjoint with (see spatiallyDisjoint) THING2 or it intersects with THING2 but is disjoint with THING1.

Note that "of the same basic type" in the above means that the three relata are either all PartiallyTangibles, all SpaceRegions, or all Event_Localizeds. This restriction is needed in order to ensure the uniqueness of SYMDIFF, since a tangible object, a space region, and an event can have the same spatial extent (see cospatial), despite their being distinct things.

See the corresponding function SpatialSymmetricDifferenceFn. Also compare with spatialDifference.
label: spatial symmetric difference
spatialSymmetricDifference

comment: A predicate used to indirectly map concepts from external data sources into Cyc, even though the target concept has not been reified. (synonymousExternalPredWRTTypes PRED-1 SOURCE STRING TYPE1 TYPE2) means that the string STRING, as it occurs in the data source SOURCE, denotes a binary predicate PRED-2 such that (equivPredsWRTTypes PRED-1 PRED-2 TYPE1 TYPE2).
label: Synonymous External Pred WRT Types
synonymousExternalPredWRTTypes

comment: (evidentialSupportForPhenomena AGT PHENOM GVP) allows us to say that AGT has level associated with GVP of evidence supporting AGT's belief in the existence of PHENOM, without requiring us to spell this out in terms of the propositional content of AGT's belief. For example, (evidentialSupportForPhenomena FoxMulder_FBIAgent #AlienBeing highToVeryHighAmountOf) says that Fox Mulder has a great deal of evidence supporting his belief in AlienBeings. To say that someone has evidence for his or her belief *that* something is the case, see evidentialSupportForBelief.) evidentialSupportForPhenomena is useful for parsing English sentences, which frequently omit references to the belief that the evidence supports, and often contain only references to the object of the supported belief. See also evidentialSupportForBelief.
label: Evidential Support For Phenomena
evidentialSupportForPhenomena

comment: A specialization of monetaryValueOfThingTo. (willingToPay THING VALUE AGENT) means that the economic Agent_PartiallyTangible AGENT is willing to pay a maximum of MonetaryValue VALUE in order to obtain the TemporalThing THING (which may be goods or services). This may or may not mean that AGENT actually possesses funds greater than or equal to VALUE (and thus that AGENT would actually buy OBJECT if it were offered at the price VALUE or lower). This predicate is inspired by the economic concept of "demand price".
label: Willing To Pay
willingToPay

comment:
A ternary RuleMacroPredicate that can be used to state that a BinaryPredicate stands in a certain relation to two collections. (relationOnlyAll BINPRED COL1 COL2) means for any instance Y of COL2, (BINPRED X Y) holds only if X is an instance of COL1. It is equivalent to (and can thus be used as shorthand for) the more complex form 
(implies
  (and
    (BINPRED ?X ?Y)
    (isa ?Y COL2))
  (isa ?X COL1)).
For example, (relationOnlyAll wearsClothing HumanChild ChildrensClothing) means that only children wear children's clothing. This assertion is shorthand for the following rule: 
(implies
  (and
    (wearsClothing ?PERSON ?CLOTHING)
    (isa ?CLOTHING ChildrensClothing))
  (isa ?PERSON HumanChild)).
See also relationAllOnly and #$NoteAboutUseOfRuleMacroPredicates.
label: Relation Only All
relationOnlyAll

comment: (infoStructureRepresentsSentenceInCC AIS CYC_SENTENCE CC) means that AIS uses the CommunicationConvention CC to represent the meaning of CYC_SENTENCE, a sentence in CycL [CycLSentence].
label: Info Structure Represents Sentence In CC
infoStructureRepresentsSentenceInCC

comment: (sourceOfTypeForProject SOURCE CW-TYPE SOURCE-TYPE PROJECT) means that SOURCE is, or is likely to be, a source of CW-TYPE, which is of SOURCE-TYPE, of facts or knowledge entered into the CycKB on behalf of PROJECT.
label: Source Of Type For Project
sourceOfTypeForProject

comment: salientDifferenceBetweenSiblings COL1 COL2 COL3 BINPRED) means that while for any given instance, INS1, of COL1 there will be an instance, INS3, of COL3 such that (BINPRED INS1 INS3), this does not hold for instances of COL2 that are not instances of COL1. See also salientDifferenceBetweenSiblings_Inverse and salientDifferenceBetween for closely related predicates.
label: Salient Difference Between Siblings
salientDifferenceBetweenSiblings

comment: (userProgramLoginTime USER PROGRAM TIME) says that the agent USER logged in to use the interactive program PROGRAM at TIME.
label: User Program Login Time
userProgramLoginTime

comment: (interArgNotIsa2_3 PRED COL1 COL2) means that, when an instance of COL1 appears as the second argument to PRED, the third argument in that assertion is constrained to not be an instance of COL2 and vice versa.
label: Inter Arg Not Isa 2 3
interArgNotIsa2-3

comment: (mtContainsResultsOfApplyingStrategy MT THING STRATEGY) identifies MT as the instance of Microtheory that contains the results of Cyc applying the strategy (Strategy, q.v.) STRATEGY to THING.
label: Mt Contains Results Of Applying Strategy
mtContainsResultsOfApplyingStrategy

comment: A QuaternaryPredicate that relates a PartiallyTangible to a ForceVector to a TemporalThing to an EnergyQuantity. (workDoneOnObjectByForceIn OBJ FORCE TEMP-THING QUANT) means that the quantity of work done on OBJ by FORCE during TEMP-THING is QUANT. The relevant notion of "work" is that of classical mechanics, namely: the magnitude of the displacement times the component of the force parallel to the displacement. This is the predicate corresponding to (QPQuantityFn WorkQuantity). See also netWorkDoneOnObjectIn.
label: Work Done On Object By Force In
workDoneOnObjectByForceIn

comment: (orgAllocatesAmountFor ORG MONEY SIT-TYPE) means the instance ORG has allocated the amount MONEY for instances of SIT-TYPE.
label: Org Allocates Amount For
orgAllocatesAmountFor

comment: the piece of space, arg1, has a number of particles present of type arg2, at a concentration arg3.
label: Particle Concentration Per Vol
particleConcentrationPerVol

comment: This event-predicate template expresses the relation between the object in motion, the point of departure and the point of arrival in types of activity subsumed by Movement_TranslationEvent. Example: (movingToFrom_EPFT (TransportViaFn AirTransportationDevice) OBJECT LOC-TO LOC-FROM) is true iff OBJECT is (being) transported by air from place LOC-FROM to place LOC-TO. It is not implied that OBJECT has either a passive or active role in the motion, or that it need be a separate object from the conveyor_Generic used.
label: Moving To From EPFT
movingToFrom-EPFT

comment: (eventTypeThreatensWithFrequency EVENT-TYPE OBJ-TYPE FREQUENCY) means that events of type THREAT-TYPE threaten damage to things of type OBJ-TYPE with frequency FREQUENCY. The purpose of this predicate is to represent type-level claims about the threats certain events pose to physical objects
label: Event Type Threatens With Frequency
eventTypeThreatensWithFrequency

comment: (stockTradedAt COMPANY MARKET YEAR) means that COMPANY's stocks are regularly traded on the stock market MARKET during the defined time interval INTERVAL.
label: Stock Traded At
stockTradedAt

comment: A TernaryPredicate that relates three CycLSentences. (conditionallyIndependentSentences SENT1 SENT2 CONDITION) means that given the information that CONDITION holds, SENT1 is independent of SENT2 (in the sense of independentSentences, q.v.).
label: Conditionally Independent Sentences
conditionallyIndependentSentences

comment:
A quaternary RelativeLocationalPredicate. (coplanarPoints POINT1 POINT2 POINT3 POINT4) is true if and only if all of the Points POINT1, POINT2, POINT3, and POINT4 lie in a common Plane.

See also coplanarLines.
label: Coplanar Points
coplanarPoints

comment: (consolidatedNetRevenueForPeriodByAccountingCOC ORG MONEY TIME COC) means MONEY is the consolidated net revenue of ORG during TIME based on the accounting principles allowed by the AccountingCOC COC. Consolidated net revenue is the combined net revenue (i.e. total revenue minus expenses) of an organization and all of its subordinateOrganizations.
label: Consolidated Net Revenue For Period By Accounting COC
consolidatedNetRevenueForPeriodByAccountingCOC

comment: (populationBasedNumberUsedToDetermineProportionalRepresentation N AGENT ORG) means that the number N is used as the basis for determining how many representatives AGENT is entitleds to have in the LegislativeOrganization ORG.
label: proportional representation population number
populationBasedNumberUsedToDetermineProportionalRepresentation

comment: (preoperativeStatus SURG-TYPE COND-TYPE STAT-TYPE) means that STAT-TYPE is the subcollection of SURG-TYPE that is warranted for the treatment of COND-TYPE.
label: Preoperative Status
preoperativeStatus

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa3_1 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the third argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the first argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN ARG1 ARG2 INST ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG1 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 3 1
interArgIsa3-1

comment: (currentAccountBalanceDuring COUNTRY THING MONEY) means that the instance of MonetaryValue MONEY is a measure of the difference between, on the one hand, the sum of the value of all goods and services exported by the Country COUNTRY during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING and the transfer payments received by COUNTRY from foreigners during the temporal extent of THING, and, on the other, the sum of the value of all goods and services imported by COUNTRY during the temporal extent of THING and the transfer payments by COUNTRY to foreigners during the temporal extent of THING. (THING will often be a calendar time period.) Thus if the value of COUNTRY's exports and received transfer payments is greater than the value of its imports and outgoing transfer payments during the temporal extent of THING, COUNTRY will have a positive current account balance. If the value of its imports and outgoing transfer payments exceeds that of its exports and incoming transfer payments, it will have a negative current account balance. This latter case can be expressed using a UnitOfMoney function with a negative number as its argument.
label: Current Account Balance During
currentAccountBalanceDuring

comment: A plane, PLANE is tangent to a surface, SURFACE at a point POINT, if and only if for every curve, CURVE, on SURFACE passing through POINT there is some straight line, LINE, contained in PLANE which is tangent to CURVE. POINT is often called the point of tangency. In Cyc, this relation is stated as (tangentPlaneAtPointOnSurface POINT PLANE SURFACE).
label: Tangent Plane At Point On Surface
tangentPlaneAtPointOnSurface

comment: (importFromAmountDuring REGION1 PRODUCT-TYPE REGION2 THING AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the amount of instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE imported by the GeographicalRegion REGION1 from the GeographicalRegion REGION2 during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. In the case of automobile imports, for example, AMOUNT might be an Integer indicating the number of cars imported. In the case of oil imports, AMOUNT might be a Volume (a number of barrels) indicating the total quantity of oil imported (by REGION1 from REGION2), or it might be an instance of MonetaryValue indicating the monetary value of all the oil imported. Alternatively, AMOUNT might be a Rate, characterizing the average rate of import of instances of PRODUCT-TYPE by REGION1 from REGION2 during the temporal extent of THING. Oil imports, for example, might be expressed in terms of so many million barrels per day or in terms of so many dollars per day (again, indicating the monetary value of the oil).
label: Import From Amount During
importFromAmountDuring

comment: (argIsaOutputModeForDetermination PRED N TYPE DET) means that relative to the InductiveLogicProgrammingDetermination DET, the Nth argument of the Predicate PRED should be an instance of the Collection TYPE and that argument position has a mode of an output variable. The sense of "mode" here is derived from Prolog_ComputerLanguage.
label: Arg Isa Output Mode For Determination
argIsaOutputModeForDetermination

comment: (bestReminding PROBE CL R), given PROBE and case library CL, binds R to the case with the highest FAC score. This assumes that remindingCaseOnly has been evaluated first.
label: Best Reminding
bestReminding

comment: Agent ARG1 prefers that ARG4 fill ARG2's ARG3 slot over having ARG5 fill it.
label: Prefers On Slot
prefersOnSlot

comment: This is a predicate for indicating regular payments (i.e. expenses) from an Agent's (ARG1) account: ARG4 is added to ARG1's ARG2 at ARG3 intervals. For example to say that XYZCompany pays $20000 a week in personal expenses: (expenseToAccount XYZCompany PersonnelExpenseAccount Weekly (Dollar_UnitedStates 20000))
label: Expense To Account
expenseToAccount

comment: This predicate relates a spatial path to the directions between one of its ends and the other. (directionsOfPath_EndToEnd PATH DIR OPPDIR) means that the direction from one of PATH's endsOfPathSegment to the other -- call them END1 and END2 -- is DIR and the direction from END2 to END1 is OPPDIR. DIR and OPPDIR must of course be opposite directions, and directionsOfPath_EndToEnd is symmetric with respect to its second and third argument-positions. This predicate is more general than directionsOfPath in that it does not require that PATH be relatively straight. directionsOfPath_EndToEnd depends only on the relative positions of END1 and END2.
label: direction of a path's endpoints
directionsOfPath-EndToEnd

comment: (marketConsequenceUnderConditionType MARKET SENTENCE CONDITION) means that SENTENCE is true of the instance MARKET Market whenever it is subject to CONDITION, a type of MarketConditionChange.
label: Market Consequence Under Condition Type
marketConsequenceUnderConditionType

comment: An instance of RuleMacroPredicate. (relationExistsAndOnlyAll PRED TYPE-1 TYPE-2) says that for every instance INSTANCE of TYPE-2 there exists a thing THING such that (PRED THING INSTANCE) where the fact that (PRED THING INSTANCE) guarantees that (isa THING TYPE-1). So, for example, (relationExistsAndOnlyAll madeBy Artifact ManufacturingOrganization) says that every instance of ManufacturingOrganization makes some artifact (in the sense of "makes" captured in the definition of madeBy), and the only things made (in that sense) by such organizations are artifacts.
label: Relation Exists And Only All
relationExistsAndOnlyAll

comment: This predicate is used to make the similarity between two things more explicit. (similarWRTTypeViaBinRel THING1 THING2 COL BINPRED) means that THING1 and THING2 both bear the relation BINPRED to similar instances of COL, i.e., if there is an instance of COL, COLINS1 such that (BINPRED THING1 COLINS1) then either (BINPRED THING2 COLINS1) or there is some similar instance of COL, COLINS2, such that (BINPRED THING2 COLINS2). For instance, (similarWRTTypeViaBinRel BillClinton GeorgeWBush Automobile likesObject) means that Clinton and Bush have similar tastes in automobiles. Note that (similarWRTTypeViaBinRel THING1 THING2 PRED COL) does not necessarily imply that (similarTo THING1 THING2), however, we might expect that claims of similarity between THING1 and THING2 be accompanied by clarification of the respects in which THING1 and THING2 are similar. Note that this predicate, along with similarTo, is intended as a very general starting place for the development of improved vocabulary to discuss similarity in Cyc. Use or introduce a specification, e.g. similarWRTPartType, (or see resemblesInQuantity or identicalInQuantity) when possible or feasible.
label: Similar WRT Type Via Bin Rel
similarWRTTypeViaBinRel

comment: Intended for use in the representation of underspecified plural noun phrases, as in the well-worn example `The sailors danced with the waitresses'. (genlsAtLeast NUM SUBCOLL COLL) means that SUBCOLL is a subcollection of COLL consisting of at least NUM elements. In the example above, `the sailors' can be rendered as (thereExists ?SUBCOLL (genlsAtLeast 2 ?SUBCOLL #$Sailor)), and the same form can be applied to `the waitresses'.
label: Genls At Least
genlsAtLeast

comment: This ternary predicate is used to indicate that a borrower is required, by the terms of a loan agreement, to play a particular role in a particular kind of situation. (loanAgreementRequiresOfBorrower AGREEMENT SIT-TYPE ROLE) means that the LoanAgreement AGREEMENT specifies that the borrower is required to play the Role ROLE in some situation that is an instance of the subcollection of Situation SIT-TYPE. Cf. loanAgreementRequiresOfCreditor.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: loan agreement requirement on the borrowers
label: loan agreement requirement on the borrower
loanAgreementRequiresOfBorrower

comment: A QuaternaryPredicate used to represent the total amount of some instance of ExistingStuffType that plays a given Role in an event. (amountOfStuffInRole EVENT STUFF AMOUNT ROLE) says that the amount of STUFF such that (ROLE EVENT STUFF) is AMOUNT. For example, (amountOfStuffInRole BobTouchesPeanutButter001 PeanutButter (Gram 5) objectActedOn) says that in the event where Bob touched peanut butter, the total amount of peanut butter touched by Bob is 5 grams.
label: Amount Of Stuff In Role
amountOfStuffInRole

comment: The LogicalConnective that represents the NOR operator in CycL. (nor P Q) is equivalent to (not (or P Q)).
label: Nor (relationship)
nor

comment: (keIrrelevantTypeGenls TERM) should be used for all terms whose instances should not be suggested even though a typeGenls assertion may suggest it.
label: Ke Irrelevant Type Genls
keIrrelevantTypeGenls
NuSketch initial location information
initialLocationInformation
comment: A predicate for identifying, via nuSketch, the initial, relative directional information about moving objects.

(qaFollowupConcepts TERM STRING CONCEPT) states that for the Cyc concept TERM, CONCEPT is one of the concepts which should be presented as followup concept in the Query Augmentation application. Additionally, CONCEPT can sensibly be tagged with STRING for presentation to the user as followups for TERM.
label: Qa Followup Concepts
qaFollowupConcepts

comment: (typesDifferInQuantityRelatedTo COL1 COL2 QUANT-TYPE BINPRED) means that instances of COL1 will be related to a different instance(s) of QUANT-TYPE by BINPRED than will instances of COL2. Note that if QUANT-TYPE is ordered, the collection that will take on "greater" instances of ATT-COLL is to appear in the first argument place.
label: Types Differ In Quantity Related To
typesDifferInQuantityRelatedTo

comment: A predicate used to state the most recent opening price of a share of a particular company's stock (of a certain "class", e.g. common or preferred). (stockPrice_Close STOCK PRICE DATE EXCHANGE) means that PRICE is the price per share for STOCK at the most recent market opening of EXCHANGE prior to DATE. See also stockPrice_Close.
label: open
stockPrice-Open
Unbound Predicate Rules
unboundPredicateRules
comment: (unboundPredicateRules PREDICATE) means that when the inference engine, in the course of backchaining, is attempting to prove a literal of the form (PREDICATE ARG1 ... ARGN) or the negation of such a literal, rules (in accessible microtheries) containing literals with unbound predicates will be available. For example, the consequent of the rule (implies (and (seriesOrderedByInverse ?SER ?PRED) (seriesLength ?SER ?L) (greaterThanOrEqualTo ?L ?N) (greaterThan ?N ?M)) (?PRED (NthInSeriesFn ?SER ?N) (NthInSeriesFn ?SER ?M))) has an unbound predicate, the variable ?PRED. Given that the KB contains the assertion (unboundPredicateRules caudalTo), that rule can be used in backchaining to prove, for instance, (caudalTo (NthInSeriesFn (The Vertebrae) 20) (NthInSeriesFn (The Vertebrae) 6)).

(situationRequiresRepairOfObjToStartByDateForFutureStageOfType SIT OBJ DATE FUTURE-SIT-TYPE) means that in order to have an instance of FUTURE-SIT-TYPE occur as a sub-situation of SIT, repair of OBJ must start by DATE.
label: Situation Requires Repair Of Obj To Start By Date For Future Stage Of Type
situationRequiresRepairOfObjToStartByDateForFutureStageOfType

comment: (extConceptOverlapsColAndReln COL RELN SOURCE STRING) means that the external structured data source SOURCE variously uses the term named by STRING as a value that semantically maps to the Cyc Collection COL, and as a slot that maps to the Cyc BinaryPredicate RELN.
label: Ext Concept Overlaps Col And Reln
extConceptOverlapsColAndReln

comment: (registryKeyNotSetToValueOnComputer KEY VALUE COMP) means that, on the Computer COMP, the RegistryKey KEY in the WindowsRegistry found on COMP is not set to VALUE, or such a key does not exist. This relation is the negation of registryKeySetToValueOnComputer.
label: Registry Key Not Set To Value On Computer
registryKeyNotSetToValueOnComputer
Represents Sentence As Arg Of Sentence
representsSentenceAsArgOfSentence
comment: An assertion of the form (representsSentenceAsArgOfSentence REP SENT ATOM) means that the LocalVariableFn CycLSentence) REP represents the CycLSentence that is the value of one of the arguments of the CycLAtomicSentence ATOM. REP does not denote exactly the same sentence as SENT, instead this is a relativized representation intended to refer to SENT as it appears within ATOM. This is the corresponding predicate of the function ArgSentenceFn. NOTE: The third argument of this predicate is not quoted so that it is possible to use a term to denote ATOM without it being the case the term is an actual sentence that has SENT as the value of one of its argument.
PositionSelection involves looking for a person to fill a position. This predicate gives the organization and position to be filled in a such a selecting.
label: Position To Fill
positionToFill

comment: (interArgNotGenl PRED FIRST-ARG FIRST-COL SECOND-ARG SECOND-COL) means that, when a spec of FIRST-COL appears as argument # FIRST-ARG to PRED, argument # SECOND-ARG in that assertion is constrained not to be a spec of SECOND-COL and vice versa.
label: Inter Arg Not Genl
interArgNotGenl

comment: (vaporDensityOfTypeAtTemperatureToType SUBSTANCE1 RATIO TEMPERATURE SUBSTANCE2) is a relation that expresses the ratio of vapor density RATIO for the substance SUBSTANCE1 when compared to an equal volume of SUBSTANCE2 (typically either Air or (ChemicalSubstanceFn H2Molecule)), where SUBSTANCE2 = 1. Thus, if the RATIO is greater than 1, SUBSTANCE1 is heavier than SUBSTANCE2, and if RATIO is less than 1, then SUBSTANCE1 is lighter than SUBSTANCE2. This predicate assumes standard pressure. WHen the temperature is not explicitly stated in the source, it is assumed to be standard temperature, which is (DegreeCelsius 0).
label: vapor density
vaporDensityOfTypeAtTemperatureToType

comment: (supplyFromThroughAmountDuring PT1 COL PT2 PT3 THING AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the amount of instances of the Collection COL with which the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 is supplied from the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2 through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT3 (on their way from PT2) during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. Like the predicate suppliedWith (q.v.), supplyFromThroughAmountDuring is very general. In various assertions PT1 might, for instance, be a Cell, a Person, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion; and likewise for PT2. And PT3 might, for example, be a Hose, a Railway, a GeographicalRegion, or a BloodVessel. The range of possible supplies is similarly broad. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. If AMOUNT is a Rate, AMOUNT indicates the average rate of supply of instances of PRODUCT-TYPE to PT1 from PT2 through PT3 during the temporal extent of THING.
label: Supply From Through Amount During
supplyFromThroughAmountDuring

comment: (sentenceTrivialForJustificationParaphrase SENTENCE) means that when SENTENCE, an instance of CycLSentence, is used in a transformation proof, it is deemed trivial. It is unnecessary to explicitly mention SENTENCE as a support for returned bindings, because a human would regard it as obvious.
label: Sentence Trivial For Justification Paraphrase
sentenceTrivialForJustificationParaphrase

comment: (pathnamePermissions PATHNAME ACCT PERM) means that a user logged on to a Computer as ACCT has PERM access to the computer file specified by PATHNAME accessible to that Computer.
label: Pathname Permissions
pathnamePermissions

comment: (representsAgentInOrganization AGENT REPRESENTED-AGENT ORG) means that REPRESENTED-AGENT is represented by AGENT in ORG. This relation is used to describe, for example, the relation a U.S. Senator bears to a U.S. State and the U.S. Senate, or the relation a U.N. Ambassador bears to a nation and the U.N.
label: Represents Agent In Organization
representsAgentInOrganization

comment: (inProgressTerm TERM) states that TERM will either be treated as retainTerm or ephemeralTerm at the KB cleanup step of the build process. Which of these two it is will depend on whether at KB cleanup time, more will be known about the term than just the inProgressTerm assertion. The predicate is designed for use by knowledge acquisition tools that have no way of knowing whether a term created during a user interaction will ever be fleshed out by the user.
label: In Progress Term
inProgressTerm

comment: (scheduledEventTypeWhereWhen EVENT_TYPE PLACE DATE) means that an event of type EVENT_TYPE is scheduled to occur at PLACE at the time DATE. Cyc can conclude that such an event actually occurs at that time and place unless there are other reasons for concluding otherwise.
label: Scheduled Event Type Where When
scheduledEventTypeWhereWhen

comment: (cardinalityOfSubSystemsWithStatus DATE STATUS CARD SYSTEM SET) means that as of DATE, the cardinality of the set SET of sub-systems of SYSTEM with the status STATUS is CARD.
label: Cardinality Of Sub Systems With Status
cardinalityOfSubSystemsWithStatus

comment:
A TernaryPredicate that relates a ScalarInterval to a ScalarInterval to a set of ScalarIntervals. (nearestScalarInSet A B SET) means that B is a member of SET and the absolute value of A minus B is less than the absolute value of the difference between A and any other member of SET. For example, the following is true: 
(nearestScalarInSet 7 8 (TheSet 5 8 10)).
label: Nearest Scalar In Set
nearestScalarInSet

comment: (textParagraph TEXTMT N STRING) means that STRING is the Nth paragraph in the text of TEXTMT.
label: Text Paragraph
textParagraph
Test Answers Cyc L Unimportant
testAnswersCycLUnimportant
comment: A test usually involves comparing the results of the test with some expected or 'correct answer'. However, tests can also be run merely to gather data about the run. testAnswersCycLUnimportant should be used to state that there is no firm expectation of bindings being returned for a #$KBContentTest-FullySpecified. (testAnswersCycLUnimportant TEST)) states that the bindings that result from submitting the formula of TEST as a CycL query are not the concern of the test. Instead, we are most likely running the test to gather metrics about query performance.
This predicate relates a pair consisting of an organism and disease type to the last vaccination event for that ailment.
label: Most Recent Vaccination For
mostRecentVaccinationFor

comment: (relationExistsSpecMinAll SLOT COL1 COL2 NUM) means that, for every instance of COL2 (INS2) there are at least NUM subcollections of COL1 (SUBCOL1, SUBCOL3, ...) such that (SLOT SUBCOL1 INS2), (SLOT SUBCOL3 INS2), ..., hold.
label: Relation Exists Spec Min All
relationExistsSpecMinAll

comment: The predicate helpfulProposition is used to state a condition that, if true, would (normally) increase an agent's chances of success in a particular effort. (helpfulProposition ENDEAVOR PROP DEGREE) means that if the #$ELSentence-Assertible PROP is true, then AGENT (who is referred to in PROP) will (normally) be helped in achieving the PurposefulAction ENDEAVOR. DEGREE is a GenericValuePredicate giving an estimate of how helpful such an occurrence would be to the success of ENDEAVOR. For example, in a basketball game, it's normally helpful if one or more of the team's players is alot taller than the average adult. Thus, for any particular game, a veryHighAmountOf advantage is indicated if the following helpfulProposition (expressed in CycL) is true: (heightOfObject PLAYER-X (RelativeGenericValueFn heightOfObject BasketballPlayer veryHighAmountOf)). (Rohrbaugh, 3/1998)
label: Helpful Proposition
helpfulProposition

comment: ARG3 is the amount of ObjectType ARG2 sold in ARG1. This is a kind of predicate slot since its interpretation depends on the object type and perhaps some additional context.
label: Quantity Sold
quantitySold

comment: A ternary predicate that relates source code for a computer program, an executable machine code translation of it, and the compiler that translates the first into the second. (compiledVersionOfCode SOURCE EXEC COMPILER) means that EXEC is the output of COMPILER for the input SOURCE.
label: Compiled Version Of Code
compiledVersionOfCode

comment: An instance of RuleMacroPredicate, (agreementAuthorizationCondition AUTHORITY PRED THING) means that any instance INS of Agreement authorized by AUTHORITY is such that (PRED INS THING).
label: Agreement Authorization Condition
agreementAuthorizationCondition

comment:
A ternary MetaRelation predicate that relates a Collection to an integer (representing an argument-place) to a Relation such that every instance of the collection is an admittedArgument (q.v.) to the specified argument-place of the relation. (admittedAllArgument COL ARGNUM RELN) means that every instance of COL satisfies all of the (single-argument) argument-type constraints (see ArgIsaPredicate and ArgGenlPredicate) for the ARGNUMth argument position of RELN. Note that COL is required not to be an EmptyCollection.

For example, (admittedAllArgument FemaleHuman 1 spouse) and (admittedAllArgument PersonTypeByActivity 1 JuvenileFn) both hold.
label: Admitted All Argument
admittedAllArgument

comment: (setOfListWithSameMemberInPos SET-OF-LISTS N LIST-OF-LISTS) means that SET-OF-LIST is a maximal set constructed from the members of LIST-OF-LISTS that have the same memberOfList in list position N. The set of the returned SET-OF-LISTS values effectively partitions out the members of LIST-OF-LISTS into an exhaustive set of disjoint sets.
label: Set Of List With Same Member In Pos
setOfListWithSameMemberInPos

comment: (unitsOfDrugPrescriptionsByDocPayerDuring DOC DRUGTYPE RXFILLTYPE PAYER PERIOD NUM) means that Prescriber DOC has had NUM prescriptions of type RXFILLTYPE filled for DRUGTYPE and paid by PAYER during PERIOD. RXFILLTYPE may be FillingAPrescription-Retail, FillingAPrescription_MailOrder, FillingANewPrescription, FillingARefillPrescription, intersections of these, or merely FillingAPrescription.
label: Units Of Drug Prescriptions By Doc Payer During
unitsOfDrugPrescriptionsByDocPayerDuring

comment: (agentHasRelationshipTo AGENT1 AGENT2 STATUS) holds just in case AGENT1 has STATUS with respect to AGENT2. This relationship is not, in general, symmetric. Though, depending on the arg3, AGENT2 may have STATUS with respect to AGENT1. An example of a case where symmetry does hold is: (agentHasRelationshipTo Spouse1 Spouse2 Married).
label: Agent Has Relationship To
agentHasRelationshipTo

comment: (agentFiscalYear AGENT INTEGER FISCAL-YEAR) means that a fiscal year of AGENT is the year FISCAL-YEAR, which ends during the year denoted by (YearFn INTEGER).
label: Agent Fiscal Year
agentFiscalYear

comment: (decreasesCausally EVENT THING SLOT) means that EVENT causes the value of the predicate SLOT applied to THING (in the first argument position) to decrease over some time period after the start of EVENT. This is defined in terms of decreasesCausallyOverPeriod (see also). Compared with its value immediately before EVENT, the value of SLOT applied to THING is guaranteed to be higher immediately following or some time after EVENT. This net decrease need not be monotonic. See #$NoteAboutQuantityChangePredicates for a map of related predicates.
label: Decreases Causally
decreasesCausally

comment: (obstacleInLocationBlocksPathForType OBJ PATH TYPE) means that OBJ is an obstacle to the traversal of PATH for all instances of TYPE.
label: Obstacle In Location Blocks Path For Type
obstacleInLocationBlocksPathForType

Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: will have detected with a sensor
label: detecting with a sensor
detectsWithSensor

comment: arg1 smells Odor arg2 which has an #$OdorMagnitude of arg3.
label: Smells Odor Of Magnitude
smellsOdorOfMagnitude

comment: An important concept in representing food chains and food webs in Ecosystems is what might be termed 'arity of consumption' - basically, the shortest distance in the food web that separates a consumer (see consumerInEcosystem) from a producer (producerInEcosystem). This recursively defined predicate instantiates this concept. Thus (n_AryConsumerInEcosystem ECOSYSTEM AGENT 1) means that there is an organism that is a producer in ECOSYSTEM (producerInEcosystem) which is an instance of a type which is a foodSourceFor AGENT, which has its habitat (hasHabitat) in the region of ECOSYSTEM, and (n_AryConsumerInEcosystem ECOSYSTEM AGENT N) means that there is an organism SOURCE such that (n_AryConsumerInEcosystem ECOSYSTEM SOURCE (DifferenceFn N 1)) and such it is an instance of a type which is a foodSourceFor AGENT which has its habitat in the region of ECOSYSTEM.
label: N Ary Consumer In Ecosystem
n-AryConsumerInEcosystem

comment: (assertionFormatForFormulaTemplate TEMPLATE FORMAT TOPICTYPE) means that in TOPICTYPE, TEMPLATE has the FormulaTemplateAssertionFormat FORMAT. FORMAT is the quantity of assertions that may be generated using TEMPLATE.
label: Assertion Format For Formula Template
assertionFormatForFormulaTemplate

comment: For the event Arg1, it is useful if any entry on Arg1's Arg2 slot has a value of Arg4 for its Arg3 slot. Arg5 describes how useful. (Note that if Arg5 is Low or veryLowAmountOf that does not just mean it is not useful, that means it is detrimental.) For example: (usefulActorAttribute Surgery objectActedOn constitutionLevel Strong highAmountOf) means its Highly useful for the objectActedOn in a Surgery event to have an Strong Constitution.
label: Useful Actor Attribute
usefulActorAttribute

comment: (personTakingTourMightParticularlyEnjoyObject TOUR PERSON THING) means that an argument exists to the effect that, if PERSON were to take TOUR, PERSON might particularly enjoy the SomethingExisting THING connected with TOUR.
label: Person Taking Tour Might Particularly Enjoy Object
personTakingTourMightParticularlyEnjoyObject
Complete Object Schema
completeObjectSchema
comment: This relation is the structured knowledge source analogue of completeExtentEnumerable. (completeObjectSchema SCHEMA_LS) means that where (meaningSentenceOfSchema SCHEMA_LS TEMPLATE) is asserted, and SENTENCE is a CycL sentence that matches TEMPLATE in the sense of substituting appropriate CycL terms for the indexicals such that the terms in question denote individuals described in the database of which SCHEMA_LS is a logical schema, if SENTENCE cannot be proved by dynamic-access lookup from the database using the meaningSentenceOfSchema assertion in question, this is a strong argument that SENTENCE is false.

label: Function With Respect To Arg Type
functionWithRespectToArgType
Different WRT Facet Via Bin Rel
differentWRTFacetViaBinRel

comment: (iteratedEventTypeOfSubSituationType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE EVT-TYPE) means that in any instance of SIT-TYPE, iterations of EVT-TYPE comprise the subsituation of type SUBSIT-TYPE.
label: Iterated Event Type Of Sub Situation Type
iteratedEventTypeOfSubSituationType

comment: (quantityChangeFunction TIME THING QUANTITY-SLOT FUNCTION-TYPE) means that during TIME the value of QUANTITY-SLOT for successive instantaneous time slices of THING varies as instances of FUNCTION-TYPE vary. Thus to say that 'during 1998 Fred had a net weight gain' we could say (quantityChangeFunction (YearFn 1998) Fred massOfObject NetIncreasingFunction). This would mean that the value of massOfObject of Fred shows a net increase over 1998. To say that the speedOfFlow is irregular throughout DribblingEvent01 one would write (quantityChangeFunction DribblingEvent01 DribblingEvent01 speedOfFlow IrregularFunction). The thickness of the previously mentioned instantaneous time slices are determined by the temporal granule size of the Microtheory in which the statement is made. Thus flow rate over time for a dribbling faucet would be smoother for large temporal grained contexts. The slot in arg2 is assumed to be functional in arg3, unless e.g. FunctionToArg is used appropriately. See also quantityInfluenceFunction for representing factors which influence but do not necessarily result in some particular kind of change in a quantity. See #$NoteAboutQuantityChangePredicates for other important quantity change related predicates.
label: Quantity Change Function
quantityChangeFunction

comment:
(constrainKnownValuesForPredRelativeToIsaInArg_Isa PRED COLL-1 N COLL-2 M)
holds just in case COLL-1 is the collection of terms that are known arg N values for a sentence using PRED when an instance of COLL-2 stands in arg M.

For example,

(constrainKnownValuesForPredRelativeToIsaInArg_Isa isa (#$FactEntrySourceTypeForProjectFn #$DecisionSupportSBIRProject) 2 ConceptualWork 1)

means that only instances of (#$FactEntrySourceTypeForProjectFn #$DecisionSupportSBIRProject) should be shown as known values for the arg 2 in isa literals when an instance of ConceptualWork appears in arg1 of the literal.
label: Constrain Known Values For Pred Relative To Isa In Arg Isa
constrainKnownValuesForPredRelativeToIsaInArg-Isa

comment:
A ternary predicate that is used to state the prescribed duration of a "term" for a given position in an organization. Positions with such built-in term-lengths are usually elected or appointed ones. (termOfPositionInOrg DURATION POSITION ORG) means that it is stipulated by ORG that POSITION is to be held by any given agent for a (maximum) period of DURATION, at which point there is another election or appointment to POSITION. Of course, ORG's rules allowing, the same agent might hold POSITION for consecutive terms. Conversely, an agent might leave POSITION voluntarily, be forced out, or die before her term is over.

Note that if POSITION is one that is normally held for the remainder of the electee/appointee's life (or until s/he resigns), DURATION should be LifetimesDuration.

For organizations in which the same term-length applies to all members, use termOfMembershipInOrg
label: Term Of Position In Org
termOfPositionInOrg
Reconsider Assertion Deductions
reconsiderAssertionDeductions
comment: (reconsiderAssertionDeductions ASSERTION) tells the system to perform TMS on ASSERTION. Note that reconsiderAssertionDeductions is an instance of ELRelation_OneWay that expands to a performSubL sentence.

(opponentsInConflict AGT1 AGT2 CONF) means that AGT1 and AGT2 are instances of IntelligentAgent who participate, with conflicting purposes, in the ConflictEvent CONF. Note that there could be more than two agents who participate in CONF with conflicting purposes, but there are at least two. Accordingly, AGT1 and AGT2 must be distinct agents when (opponentsInConflict AGT1 AGT2 CONF) holds.
label: opponent in a conflict
opponentsInConflict

comment: (reusabilityOfPromptWRTResource FT TEMPLATE FORMAT) means that the #$FormulatTemplate FT can be handled in a manner consistent with FORMAT when it occurs as part of the KEInteractionResource TEMPLATE. In some cases, how a template should be handled may be predictable from argFormat constraints on replaceable args.
label: Reusability Of Prompt WRT Resource
reusabilityOfPromptWRTResource
Greater Than Or Equal To WRT Slot
greaterThanOrEqualToWRTSlot

comment: (nthInteriorRingOfPolygon POLYGON N RING) means that RING is the Nth interior ring of POLYGON.
label: Nth Interior Ring Of Polygon
nthInteriorRingOfPolygon

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa4_5 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the fourth argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the fifth argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 INST ARG5 ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG5 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 4 5
interArgIsa4-5
Minimize
minimize
comment: minimize allows Cyc to assume that a statement is not true unless it is known to be true. Specifically, if for some bindings of the variables that appear in the minimized formula the formula with the bindings substituted in cannot be proved, then assume the negation of the formula with the bindings substituted in. From an example in the KB: (minimize (disjointWith ?Collection ?Collection)) and binding ?Collection to Poodle means if we cannot prove (disjointWith Poodle Poodle) assume (not (disjointWith Poodle Poodle, i.e. assume every Collection is nonempty unless we know otherwise. In the case where we bind ?Collection to some other variable ?Y and substituting in means if we cannot show (disjointWith ?Y ?Y) then assume the negation, (not (forAll ?Y (disjointWith ?Y ?Y))) which is equivalent to (thereExists ?Y (not (disjointWith ?Y ?Y))). This is one of the predicates that has been created to allow Cyc to do negation by failure. Other related predicates are minimizeExtent and minimizeExtentForArg.

label: Type Feels Towards Object To Degree
typeFeelsTowardsObjectToDegree

comment:
A KEFacilitationPredicate and RuleMacroPredicate. (keSuggestionPredsInverse_InsSpec COL1 BINPRED COL2) means that for every known instance INS1 of COL1, it is suggested that there be some specialization SPEC2 of COL2 such that (BINPRED SPEC2 INS1) is known in the knowledge base.

For example,

(keSuggestionPredsInverse_InsSpec SkilledActivityType agentTypePerformsActsOfType IntelligentAgent)

means that for every known instance ACT-TYPE of SkilledActivityType, it is suggested that there be a specialization AGT-TYPE of IntelligentAgent such that (agentTypePerformsActsOfType AGT-TYPE ACT-TYPE) is known in the knowledge base.

See also keSuggestionPreds_InsSpec.
label: Ke Suggestion Preds Inverse Ins Spec
keSuggestionPredsInverse-InsSpec

comment: The predicate stateOfAilment expresses the relation between an animal, a type of AilmentCondition that it has, and the state of the disease, which must be an instance of AnimalTypeByAilment. For instance, (stateOfAilment #$Kean GettingSick Influenza) means that Kean is coming down with the flu.
label: State Of Ailment
stateOfAilment

comment: (no_GenQuantRelnToFromType RELN COL1 COL2) is true iff there is no element INST1 of COL1 such that there is an element INST2 of COL2 for which (RELN INST1 INST2) holds.
label: No Gen Quant Reln To From Type
no-GenQuantRelnToFromType
subPropertyOf: Few Gen Quant Reln From Type
Few Gen Quant Reln To Type

comment: Let SLOT denote an QuantitySlot, SLOT-ARG1 denote the arg1Isa constraint on SLOT, SLOT-ARG2 denote the arg2Isa constraint on SLOT, and VALUE denote the instance of SLOT-ARG2 such that (SLOT O-TYPE VALUE). Then (maximumTrafficableValue_TransporterConstraint PATH O-TYPE SLOT MAX) means that PATH is pathTrafficableForTransportVia transporters of type O-TYPE only if (greaterThanOrEqualTo MAX VALUE). See also the related predicates minimumTrafficableValue_TransporterConstraint, maximumTrafficableValue_PathConstraint, and minimumTrafficableValue_PathConstraint.
label: Maximum Trafficable Value Transporter Constraint
maximumTrafficableValue-TransporterConstraint

comment: (rootsAgainst PERSON WHEN AGENT) means that PERSON (an instance of IntelligentAgent) roots against AGENT during WHEN (which can be a TimeInterval or Event). Use instead of negativeVestedInterest where appropriate.
label: Roots Against
rootsAgainst

comment: (speedInMoveTypeOnTerrain VEHICLETYPE MOVETYPE TERRAINTYPE SPEED) means that the typical speed of vehicles of type VEHICLETYPE when they are playing the role of primaryObjectMoving in translation events of MOVETYPE on TERRAINTYPE is SPEED.
label: Speed In Move Type On Terrain
speedInMoveTypeOnTerrain

comment: A predicate that relates an instance of ConfigurationFile to instances of SoftwareParameter, CharacterString, and ComputationalSystem. (fileSetsParameterToValueOnComputer FILE PARAM VALUE COMP) means that on COMP, when the program configured by FILE runs (see fileConfiguresSoftware), it runs with the value of PARAM set to VALUE. For example, if on vega.cyc.com the file /etc/sendmail.cf sets AliasFile to /etc/aliases, it is true that (fileSetsParameterToValueOnComputer Sendmail_cf_TheConfigurationFile SendmailOption_AliasFile "/etc/aliases" #$Vega-Cyc-Com).
label: File Sets Parameter To Value On Computer
fileSetsParameterToValueOnComputer

comment: ARG1 feels discomfort or pain in body part(s) of type ARG2 when pressures equal to or greater than ARG3 are applied for an extended period.
label: Threshold Of Pain Pressure
thresholdOfPain-Pressure

comment: (doEscalatePrivilegeOnSystemSurreptitiously AGENT LEVEL SYSTEM) means that AGENT raises his privileges on SYSTEM to LEVEL, in a manner likely to escape detection. For instance, someone could load an executable root exploit, run it, and then remove it from the system.
label: Do Escalate Privilege On System Surreptitiously
doEscalatePrivilegeOnSystemSurreptitiously

comment: An assertion of the form (requestReservesPercentageOfIndForInterval REQUEST PERCENT INDIVIDUAL INTERVAL) states that the ResourceRequest REQUEST represents a request to reserve PERCENT percent of the Individual INDIVIDUAL's time during the TimeInterval INTERVAL. This is a core predicate for describing what an ResourceRequest reserves, see also requestReservesPercentageOfIndForInterval.
label: Request Reserves Percentage Of Ind For Interval
requestReservesPercentageOfIndForInterval

label: Pp Comp Frame For Type And Word
ppCompFrameForTypeAndWord

comment:
A quaternary RuleMacroPredicate (q.v.) that can be used to state that a given binary predicate stands in a certain numerical relationship with respect to two collections. (relationExistsRangeAll BINPRED COL1 COL2 RANGE) means that for any instance INST of COL2 there are between the minimum and maximum of RANGE (see NonNegativeIntegerRange) many instances INST(i) of COL1 such that (BINPRED INST(i) INST) holds. This is equivalent to (and can thus be used in effect as shorthand for) the more complex form: 

  (implies
     (isa ?INST COL2)
     (thereExistRange RANGE ?INST-I
        (and
           (isa ?INST-I COL1)
           (PRED ?INST-I ?INST)))).

For example, '(relationExistsRangeAll anatomicalParts Mammal Foot_AnimalBodyPart AFew_Quant)' means every mammal has a few feet. Cf. relationAllExistsRange, and see #$NoteAboutUseOfRuleMacroPredicates.
label: Relation Exists Range All
relationExistsRangeAll

comment: A ternary MetaRelation predicate for stating that a certain kind of complex, partly genls based relationship holds between the first argument to a given function and the corresponding value that is returned. (interArg1ResultGenls FUNC INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when a subcollection of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the first argument to FUNC, then -- regardless of what the other arguments to FUNC might be -- the value of that function for those arguments is a subcollection of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is: if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL and (FUNC INST ...) = VALUE, then VALUE is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. Note that, unlike (e.g.) the InterArgTypePredicates, interArg1ResultGenls _cannot_ be used to put semantic well-formedness constraints on functions. See also the similar but more flexible quaternary interArgResultGenl.
label: Inter Arg 1 Result Genls
interArg1ResultGenls

comment: (captionInWorkTo WORK CAPTION STRUC) means that the TextString CAPTION is a caption to STRUC and both CAPTION and STRUC are contained within the StructurallySpecificWork WORK. STRUC is an instance of either Table_AIS, Graph_AIS or AbstractVisualStructure. Captions are textual descriptions or explanations of parts of documents that are understood or experienced, at least in part, non-textually (i.e. AbstractVisualStructures).
label: Caption In Work To
captionInWorkTo

limitPriceOfStockTypeForAgent-Sell

useReformulationRuleForQuantifierMovement
comment: (useReformulationRuleForQuantifierProcessing RULE) indicates that RULE will be used by the QuantifierMovementRLModule, which serves to move ill-placed NLTagFn expressions into a position where they can be used by the QuantifierProcessingRLModule.

label: Evaluate Immediately
evaluateImmediately
comment: (evaluateImmediately FUNCTION) means that the canonicalizer will translate each non-atomic term (see the collection CycLNonAtomicTerm) whose initial (or "0th" argument-place) term denotes FUNCTION into the value to which the non-atomic term evaluates. For example, if (evaluateImmediately PlusFn) held, then the non-atomic term `(PlusFn 2 3 4)' would canonicalize as `9'. Note that a non-atomic term containing a nested non-atomic term whose initial term denotes another instance of EvaluatableFunction (call that instance OTHER-FUNCTION) will not canonicalize in this way, unless (evaluateImmediately OTHER-FUNCTION) is also true. For example, `(PlusFn 2 (DifferenceFn 3 4))' would not canonicalize as `1' unless (evaluateImmediately DifferenceFn) were also true.
A unary MetaKnowledgePredicate. (unassertForOpenCycBuild ASSERTION) means that ASSERTION should be unasserted before compiling a ResearchCyc build that should not include TKB data.
label: Unassert For Non TKB Build
unassertForNonTKBBuild

label: Possible Bridging Entailment
possibleBridgingEntailment

comment: (discardedVerbNetVerbClassAssertion SENTENCE) means SENTENCE expresses contetn which was imported from VerbNet_Version2_0 and has since been discarded.

Preserves Disjointness Unary
preservesDisjointness-Unary
comment: preservesDisjointness_Unary is a unary instance of MetaRelation. (preservesDisjointness_Unary FUNCTION) means that FUNCTION (an instance of CollectionDenotingFunction and UnaryRelation) has the following property: if COL1 and COL2 are specializations of Collection that can both serve as the 1st argument of FUNCTION, and COL2 is disjoint with COL1 (so that (disjointWith COL2 COL1) holds), then the result of FUNCTION taking COL2 as its argument will be disjoint with the result of FUNCTION taking COL1 as its argument. For example, (preservesDisjointness_Unary GroupFn) holds because (disjointWith COL-2 COL-1) implies (disjointWith (GroupFn COL-2) (GroupFn COL-1)), for all collections COL-1 and COL-2 that satisfy the argument constraints for GroupFn.

This predicate can be used to relate a lot of land, a street intersection it is adjacent to, and a general direction from the latter to the former. (streetCornerOf LOT XING DIR) means that LOT is adjacent to XING and the general direction from the center of XING to the center of LOT is DIR. See also StreetCornerFn.

streetCornerOf

comment: Let SLOT denote an QuantitySlot, SLOT-ARG1 denote the arg1Isa constraint on SLOT, SLOT-ARG2 denote the arg2Isa constraint on SLOT, and VALUE denote the instance of SLOT-ARG2 such that (SLOT O-TYPE VALUE). comment: An instance of RuleMacroPredicate. (relationAllExistsAndOnly PRED TYPE-1 TYPE-2) says that for every instance INSTANCE of TYPE-1 there exists a thing THING such that (PRED INSTANCE THING) where the fact that (PRED INSTANCE THING) guarantees that (isa THING TYPE-2). So, for example, (relationAllExistsAndOnly premeditatedMurderer PremeditatedMurder Person) says that only people carry out premediated murders, every instance of which must have at least one person who carries it out.

relationAllExistsAndOnly

comment: sitEnablesAgentTo is a generalization of all enables-* predicates for which the arg1Isa Situation, with the exception of enables_ImpartsSkills. Motivation: occasionally one needs to label a broad class of events as generically `enabling', i.e., as events that enable an agent to do something in one or the other sense of enabling. This predicate should be used sparingly: When describing the enabling relation between a specific event or type of event, an agent and a specific action or type of action, one should use the specific enables-* predicate appropriate to that circumstance.

comment:
A ternary RelativeLocationalPredicate that holds of three spatial things when the third is located in the region generally between the first two. (inRegionBetween PLACE1 PLACE2 THING) means that PLACE1 is closer to THING than to PLACE2, and PLACE2 is closer to THING than to PLACE1. More precisely, THING is subsumed by the space region REGION such that, for every point POINT in REGION, (i) PLACE1 is closer to POINT than to PLACE2 and (ii) PLACE2 is closer to POINT than to PLACE1.

For cases in which a spatial thing is directly between two others, see the specialization between.
label: In Region Between
inRegionBetween

comment:
A ternary predicate that relates pairs of agents to an organization. (appointedByAgentToOrg APPOINTEE APPOINTER ORG) means that APPOINTEE is a member of ORG in virtue of having been appointed by APPOINTER. This entails that (hasMembers ORG APPOINTEE ORG) is true and, at least at the time of the appointment, that (agentAppointsMembersOfOrg APPOINTER ORG) is true.

Note that appointedByAgentToOrg is contemporaryInArg (q.v.) in its first and third argument-places, but not in its second argument-place. So the above sentence can be true only so long as APPOINTEE and ORG exist (and, indeed, the former remains a member of the latter); but the sentence might be true even after APPOINTER ceases to exist.

See also agentAppointsPositionInOrg.
label: Appointed By Agent To Org
appointedByAgentToOrg

areaOfPlantBLOPlantedByType

comment: (except ASSERTION) means that there is an exception to ASSERTION in the current microtheory such that ASSERTION is not known to be true. If ASSERTION is a rule, it will not fire.

comment: '(typeBehaviorIncapable TYPE SIT-TYPE ROLE)' means that instances of TYPE are defeasibly incapable of playing ROLE in instances of SIT-TYPE. For instance, '(typeBehaviorIncapable FlightlessBird Flying_FlappingWings doneBy)' means that flightless birds are incapable of flying.
