relationInstanceMember

comment: (moreThwartedFromBecause AGENT EVTTYPE ROLE PROP) means that there is a decreased chance of AGENT's playing the role ROLE in a situation of type EVTTYPE because PROP is true (decreasedChanceForRoleBecause AGENT EVTTYPE ROLE PROP) and AGENT has the goals (ROLE EVTTYPE AGENT).
label: More Thwarted From Because
moreThwartedFromBecause

comment: (typeFunctionCapable TYPE SYSTEMTYPE ROLE) means that under normal background conditions, a normal instance of TYPE can play the functional role (see SystemRolePredicate) ROLE with respect to the class of FunctionalSystem SYSTEMTYPE. This means, specifically, that for some large and nontrivial set of instances of SYSTEMTYPE, it would be unsurprising if Cyc learned that an instance of TYPE played the role ROLE with respect to any of those instances. (typeFunctionCapable TYPE SYSTEMTYPE ROLE) does *not* mean that every instance of TYPE can play the role ROLE in every instance of SYSTEMTYPE: e.g., a particular instance of TYPE could not play ROLE in an instance of SYSTEMTYPE that ceased to exist before the instance of TYPE had come into being.
label: Type Function Capable
typeFunctionCapable

comment: A statement of the form (totalDebtDuring PLACE QUANTITY DATE) is used to give an estimate of the total debt (borrowings minus repayments) of the government of the GeopoliticalEntity PLACE during the Date DATE. For instance, (totalDebtDuring Syria (Dollar-UnitedStates 1.8E10) (YearFn 2005)) would state that during 2005, the Syrian government had a total debt of $18 billion.
label: Total Debt During
totalDebtDuring

comment: (prefersToMaximize AGENT THING SLOT) means that AGENT prefers (see also prefers) greater values of SLOT (its second argument) when applied to THING (as the first argument of SLOT). In a sense it means that AGENT will prefer situations whereby SLOT of THING becomes higher, or stays the same, over situations whereby SLOT of THING becomes less. It need not imply that the agent will directly pursue such maximization (in order to imply direct pursuit, see goals)
label: Prefers To Maximize
prefersToMaximize

comment: (scaleUsedInJudgement STYPE CRITERION SCALE) states that when evaluating scripts of type STYPE for performance of a CRITERION, the values of the scoring metric are all instances of SCALE. For example, when judging figure skating for technical merit, the 0-10 scale is used.
label: Scale Used In Judgement
scaleUsedInJudgement

comment: The predicate actorCapacity is used to indicate the capacity in which some entity participates in a particular event or situation. (actorCapacity ENTITY SIT CAP) means that ENTITY has an (unspecified) role in SIT with the CapacityPredicate CAP. An important difference between the CapacityPredicates and this predicate is that the CapacityPredicates are type level with respect to the event -- that is, they take an event type as their third argument while actorCapacity takes an instance of Situation as its second argument. An important use of actorCapacity is with the capacity predicates actsInCapacity_MainFunction or actsInCapacity_IntendedFunction to state that a device is serving its primaryFunction or intended function (i.e., intendedBehaviorCapable) in a certain situation.
label: Actor Capacity
actorCapacity

comment: It is medically recommended that the organism ARG1 *refrain* from playing the role ARG3 in some instance of ARG2, typically but not necessarily, in order to ameliorate some condition they are experiencing.
label: Medical Proscription For BLO
medicalProscriptionForBLO

comment: (hasPartCount OBJ PART-TYPE INT) means that INT is the number of parts of type PART-TYPE that object OBJ has. For example (hasPartCount BookCW001 Chapter_PCW 15) says that BookCW001 has fifteen chapters. To talk about physical parts, use the more specific hasPhysicalPartCount.
label: Has Part Count
hasPartCount

comment: (muchCloserToThan THING CLOSER FARTHER) says that the distance between CLOSER and THING is much less than the distance between FARTHER and THING.
label: much closer to
muchCloserToThan

comment: (costarsIn ACTOR1 ACTOR2 MOVIE) means that actors ACTOR1 and ACTOR2 both appear as actors in the same film MOVIE. For example (costarsIn LeonardoDicaprio KathyBates Titanic_TheMovie) means that both LeonardoDicaprio and KathyBates appear in 'Titanic', the movie. Note that, although the name might suggest otherwise, the two actors need not have the same billing or status in the movie. See also costars.
label: Costars In
costarsIn

comment: This predicate relates pairs of things to the kinds of physical parts they have in common and which are instantiated similarly in each. (similarWRTPartType THING1 THING2 PART-TYPE) means that THING1 and THING2 both have parts that are instances of PART-TYPE and these parts are similar to each other. For instance, (similarWRTPartType MUSCLE-CAR1 MUSCLE-CAR2 GasolineEngine) means that MUSCLE-CAR1 and MUSCLE-CAR2 both have instances of GasolineEngine as parts and these engines are similar to each other. Obviously, judgements of similarity are going to be highly context dependent. To relate things in terms of attributes that they share, see resemblesInQuantity and identicalInQuantity. To discuss part similarity at a type level, see typesSimilarWRTPartType.
label: Similar WRT Part Type
similarWRTPartType

comment: (runningMates AGENT-1 AGENT-2 ELECTION) means that AGENT-1 and AGENT-2 was/are/will-be running mates in ELECTION, an instance of ElectionForOffice.
label: Running Mates
runningMates

comment: (priceCeiling MARKET PRODUCT PRICE) means that the instance PRICE of MonetaryValue has been imposed as the maximum price at which PRODUCT may be sold in MARKET.
label: price ceiling
priceCeiling

comment: (applicationBasePath APP COMPUTER BASEPATH) means that an instantiation of APP is installed on COMPUTER, and that BASEPATH is the default base pathname of all APP-related program (not data) files on COMPUTER. The absolute pathname of a file can be determined by appending its full relative pathname to its base pathname. The full relative pathname for a file 'FILE' can be determined by combining the relative directory pathname for files of which 'FILE' is a type with the relative file pathname of 'FILE'.
label: Application Base Path
applicationBasePath

comment: Let SLOT denote an QuantitySlot, SLOT-ARG1 denote the arg1Isa constraint on SLOT, SLOT-ARG2 denote the arg2Isa constraint on SLOT, and VALUE denote the instance of SLOT-ARG2 such that (SLOT PATH VALUE). Then (minimumTrafficableValue_PathConstraint PATH O-TYPE SLOT MIN) means that PATH is pathTrafficableForTransportVia transporters of type O-TYPE only if (greaterThanOrEqualTo VALUE MIN). See also the related predicates maximumTrafficableValue_PathConstraint, maximumTrafficableValue_TransporterConstraint, and minimumTrafficableValue_TransporterConstraint.
label: minimum trafficable value
minimumTrafficableValue-PathConstraint
Existentially Close Variables Of Type
existentiallyCloseVariablesOfType
comment: (existentiallyCloseVariablesOfType COLL) means that variables appearing in query search fragments that are constrained to be instances of COLL should be existentially closed. The binding should appear at the widest scope.

A predicate used for probability statements. (bayesParent BAYES-VARIABLE1 BAYES-VARIABLE2 BAYESNET) means that the BayesDiscreteOutcome associated with BAYES-VARIABLE2 influences the BayesDiscreteOutcome associated with BAYES-VARIABLE1, and that BAYES-VARIABLE2 is an immediate 'parent node' of the BAYES-VARIABLE1 node in the Bayesian Network BAYESNET representing probabilistic influence in the applicable Microtheory. That is, the second bayes variable is a direct parent of the first in the BayesNet. Note that BAYES-VARIABLE1/outcome and BAYES-VARIABLE2/outcome cannot be conditionallyIndependent in the Microtheory if one is a bayesParent of the other. Given the outcomes of all of a node's bayesParent nodes, then all of its further ancestor nodes and other non-descendant nodes are conditionallyIndependent of it in the applicable Microtheory. To relate a node to the set of all of its parent nodes, use bayesParentSet. The direction is obtained from the conditional dependence --- given the outcome of a node --- among its bayesParents (the 'explaining away' effect), which does not seem to apply among its Bayesian 'child' nodes. Many Bayesian network theorists consider that the directions on the links correspond to the direction of causal influence, and hence to the direction of time.
label: Bayes Parent
bayesParent

comment: (seemsLikeTo THING1 THING2 AGENT) means that, to the person or other agent AGENT, THING1 seems like THING2. For example, a fake MonaLisa_Painting might seem like the real one to a non-expert. Or Canada might seem like the UnitedStatesOfAmerica to an Asian visitor.
label: semblance
seemsLikeTo

comment: (connotes OBJ-1 OBJ-2 DEGREE) means that as a consequence of perceiving or thinking about one thing (OBJ-1), a typical sane intelligent perceiving agent would likely think of another thing (OBJ-2) with a strength of association indicated by DEGREE. E.g., (connotes GermanNaziParty Prejudice highAmountOf). This predicate is sometimes symmetric, but often not. See also typeConnotes.
label: connoting
connotes

comment: enablesAgentTo_Generic is a generalization of all enables-* predicates, with the exception of enables_ImpartsSkills. Motivation: occasionally one needs to label a broad class of events as generically `enabling', i.e., as events that enable an agent to do something in one or the other sense of enabling. This predicate should be used sparingly: When describing the enabling relation between a specific event or type of event, an agent and a specific action or type of action, one should use the specific enables-* predicate appropriate to that circumstance.
label: Enables Agent To Generic
enablesAgentTo-Generic

comment: This is the corresponding predicate of the function IndividualArgModeFn.
label: Mode For I Oand Individual Type
modeForIOandIndividualType

comment: (expectationCapabilities COL ACTTYPE ROLE) means that if INST is an instance of COL, then it is expected to be the case that INST is behaviorCapable of playing ROLE in Events of type ACTTYPE.

expectationCapabilities

comment: The predicate clockTimeIndex_12Hour associates a TimeOfDayType with a three integer representation, using a 12-hour index for the hours, and associating it with either TimeOfDay_AM or TimeOfDay_PM. For instance, an assertionof the form (clockTimeIndex_12Hour (TimeOfDayFn TimeOfDay_11AM (TimeOfHourFn (MinuteOfHourFn 12) (SecondOfMinuteFn 12))) 11 12 12 TimeOfDay_AM) states that they TimeOfDayType (TimeOfDayFn TimeOfDay_11AM (TimeOfHourFn (MinuteOfHourFn 12) (SecondOfMinuteFn 12))) is represented as '11:12:12 AM' on a clock that uses the 12-hour time system.
label: Clock Time Index 12 Hour
clockTimeIndex-12Hour
Vulnerability Alert DOD
vulnerabilityAlert-DOD
comment: vulnerabilityAlert_DOD is a unary predicate used to assert that a CycLAssertion expresses information contained in a vulnerability alert (IAVA) on the DOD CERT webpage http://www.cert.mil/iava/index.htm.

(reasonsForAction ACTION PRED AGENT THING) means that ACTION was performed by AGENT, and that a crucial reason for AGENT's performing ACTION is the fact that (PRED AGENT THING), where PRED is an instance of CognitivePredicate. For example, if the Saudi Arabian air force were to conduct a bombing raid (RAID01) against targets in Iran shortly after the occurrence of a terrorist attack (ATTACK01) directed against Saudi Arabia, and believed by the Saudis to have been sponsored by Iran, then it is reasonable to conclude that (reasonsForAction RAID01 beliefs SaudiArabia (directingAgent ATTACK01 Iran)). Similarly, if Joe-Bob jumps (JUMP01) up from his desk because he sees a spider (SPIDER01) on it, then it is true that (reasonsForAction JUMP01 sees Joe-Bob SPIDER01). When arg2 is an instance of PropositionalAttitudeSlot, arg4 will generally be an CycLSentence_Assertible. However, as the example of Joe-Bob and the spider shows, it need not always be an CycLSentence_Assertible.

Note: reasonsForAction is not a spec-pred of inReactionTo, but in some cases a given claim can be expressed using either of these predicates. For example, the sentence above explaining Saudi Arabia's motivation for a hypothetical attack on Iran might also be expressed as: (inReactionTo RAID01 ATTACK01). However, reasonsForAction is a more discriminating predicate, in that it allows one to identify the precise attitude that motivated a given action. For this reason, reasonsForAction is somewhat less versatile, since one must have more detailed information about the agent's mental state to use this predicate than to use inReactionTo; on the other hand, when this information is available, it can be quite useful to make it explicit. Finally, note that in some cases reasonsForAction is more versatile than inReactionTo for instance, inReactionTo does not apply to the example above involving Joe-Bob and the spider. See the comment on inReactionTo.
label: Reasons For Action
reasonsForAction

comment: expected_ToBe is a deontic operator in Cyc. For each CycLSentence_Assertible PROP, (expected_ToBe PROP) means that it is expected that PROP. expected_ToBe is the dual of amenable_ToBe, i.e., (expected_ToBe PROP) is equivalent to (not (amenable_ToBe (not PROP))).
label: Expected To Be
expected-ToBe

comment: (reviewedByAgentForTask THING AGENT TASK) means that THING was reviewed by AGENT as part of TASK.

reviewedByAgentForTask

comment: (synonymousExternalConceptWRTPredicate_HasSpellingChange THING SOURCE PRED STRING) means that in the latest OWL ontology, THING is a new OWL class such that when THING stands in the relation PRED to any other thing, the string STRING (when it occurs in the data source SOURCE) denotes THING, and STRING is different from the old controlled vocabulary string that was used.
label: Synonymous External Concept WRT Predicate Has Spelling Change
synonymousExternalConceptWRTPredicate-HasSpellingChange

comment: (eventTypeFallsOnNthDayTypeInMonth EVENT MONTH DAY-TYPE NUM) is used to say that a special event falls annually on a specified Nth day of the week DAY-TYPE during a certain month MONTH. For example, to say that Mother's Day falls on the second Sunday of May: (eventTypeFallsOnNthDayTypeInMonth MothersDay May Sunday 2).
label: Event Type Falls On Nth Day Type In Month
eventTypeFallsOnNthDayTypeInMonth

comment: (spits AGT SPIT SOURCE) holds just in case AFT spit the instance of PartiallyTangible, SPIT, from SOURCE. Usually, the arg3 of this predicate will be an instance of Mouth or some other thing capable of being the source of spitting. For instance, when brushing one's teeth the following usually holds for a short time after the brushing (spits AGT SOME-TOOTHPASTE AGT-MOUTH).
label: Spits (cotemporal predicate)
spits

comment: A ternary predicate designed to express the concentration of a substance in moles per unit of volume considered to be in a sample of something -- typically a solution. If the substance is an ionic compound, such as hydrogen chloride, it may be totally disassociated in the solution and so is not a chemical ``species'' in the solution at all. The molar concentration is stated in terms of (molarityOfSubstanceInSample SAMPLE CHEMICAL ((PerFn Mole_ChemicalCountUnit Liter) NUM)) which is moles per liter of CHEMICAL in SAMPLE. Use molarityOfChemicalObjectInSample for concentration of a chemical object type (e.g. ChlorideIon or O2Molecule) instead of a chemical substance (e.g. Sucrose). molarityOfSubstanceInSample is not used for specifying the concentration of ions.
label: molar concentration in a sample
molarityOfSubstanceInSample

comment: (numberOfPrescriptionsByDocPayerDuring DOC DRUGTYPE RXFILLTYPE PAYER PERIOD NUM) means that Prescriber DOC has had NUM prescriptions of type RXFILLTYPE filled for DRUGTYPE and payed by PAYER during PERIOD. RXFILLTYPE may be FillingAPrescription-Retail, FillingAPrescription_MailOrder, FillingANewPrescription, FillingARefillPrescription, intersections of these, or merely FillingAPrescription.
label: Number Of Prescriptions By Doc Payer During
numberOfPrescriptionsByDocPayerDuring

comment: ARG1 makes payments for events of type ARG2 during time ARG3 of total ARG4.

paymentOutForType

comment: unixFilePermissions describes important security features of a file. (unixFilePermissions FILE ACCOUNT VALUE) means that a permission of file FILE for user account ACCOUNT is permission value VALUE.

unixFilePermissions

comment: (situationConstituentWithDesc SIT IND STRING) means that the Individual IND is both a participant in the Situation SIT (situationConstituents) and may be referred to with the TextString STRING.

situationConstituentWithDesc

ruleForOpenCyc

comment: A type-level version of soleFunction. (typeSoleFunction_AgnosticIntentional AGTTYPE SITTYPE ROLE) means that in ordinary or normal circumstances, instances of AGTTYPE have playing ROLE in situations of type SITTYPE as their only function in some immediate functional context. Like primaryFunction, the relation is agnostic as to whether the functionality derives from the intent of some intentional designer: i.e., the relation is not a spec-pred of typeIntendedBehaviorCapable. This is not to say that usage of typeSoleFunction_AgnosticIntentional implies that no design exists: the relation is simply agnostic as to whether a design exists or not. For this reason typePrimaryFunction is deemed to be a specialization. In cases where SITTYPE is itself a FunctionalSystem (say, a kind of Cell or a kind of Organization in the FunctionalRoleAnalysisMt), SITTYPE itself specifies the functional context: otherwise, this context is taken to be specified by the Microtheory in which the assertion is made.
label: Type Sole Function Agnostic Intentional
typeSoleFunction-AgnosticIntentional

comment: (increasesImmediately PERIOD THING SLOT) means that the value for the predicate SLOT applied to THING (in the first argument position) is greater immediately after (STIF q.v.) PERIOD than it was immediately before (STIB q.v.) PERIOD. PERIOD may be any instance of TemporalThing, i.e., anything that has a time period associated with it, whether an event, an entity, a life stage, etc. No causal connection is implied between the TemporalThing PERIOD and the increase. See #$NoteAboutQuantityChangePredicates for a map of related predicates.
label: Increases Immediately
increasesImmediately

comment: An assertion of the form (availableQuantityForInterval THING QUANTITY INTERVAL) states that the 'portion' of the Individual THING that could be reserved during the TimeInterval has the Quantity QUANTITY.
label: Available Quantity For Interval
availableQuantityForInterval

comment: (trademarkStringOfCW AGENT DW STRING) means that company or person AGENT (an Agent_PartiallyTangible) has a government-granted right to market instantiations of the DevisedPracticeOrWork DW using as mark some physical embodiment of the string STRING.
label: Trademark String Of CW
trademarkStringOfCW

comment: (agentObligationInSituation AGENT REQUIREMENT SITUATION) means that AGENT is required to fulfill REQUIREMENT due to its involvement in SITUATION. Note that REQUIREMENT is an element of Obligation. If it can not be proven that agent fulfills REQUIREMENT (see agentFulfillsObligation) then (agentViolatesObligation AGENT REQUIREMENT) is concluded. In order to see the content of REQUIREMENT, one should look at assertions on ist_Obligation for the microtheory REQUIREMENT.
label: Agent Obligation In Situation
agentObligationInSituation

comment: (situationTypeStages_ForRole_Maximal SIT-TYPE ROLE LIST) means that LIST gives a complete listing of all the roles that an agent playing the role ROLE in SIT-TYPE will play, together with the situation types in which s/he plays them, in the temporal order in which they are played.
label: Situation Type Stages For Role Maximal
situationTypeStages-ForRole-Maximal

comment: (oxidationChangeFromTo ELEMENT REACT-NUM PROD-NUM REACTION-TYPE) holds just in case the oxidation number of an instance of ELEMENT changes from REACT-NUM to PROD-NUM in reactions of type REACTION-TYPE. This statement holds just in case (oxidationNumberInForm ELEMENT REACT-NUM SOME-STUFF REACTION-TYPE) and (#$postOxidationNumber ELEMENT PROD-NUM SOME-OTHER-STUFF REACTION-TYPE) hold for some SOME-STUFF and SOME-OTHER-STUFF. This is not a functional relationship. For any given ELEMENT, it might be the case that ELEMENT appears in multiple places as a reactant or product. If this is the case, then two or more distinct oxidationChangeFromTo statements could be predicated of ELEMENT.
label: change in oxidation number
oxidationChangeFromTo

comment: This ternary predicate is used to indicate that a creditor is forbidden, by the terms of a type of loan agreement, from playing a particular role in a particular kind of situation. (loanAgreementTypeForbidsCreditor AGREEMENT-TYPE SIT-TYPE ROLE) means that entering into an instance of AGREEMENT-TYPE (a specialization of LoanAgreement) forbids the creditor from playing the Role ROLE in some situation that is an instance of the subcollection of Situation SIT-TYPE. Cf. loanAgreementTypeForbidsBorrower.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: loan agreement type restriction on the creditors
label: loan agreement type restriction on the creditor
loanAgreementTypeForbidsCreditor

comment: A predicate used to offer intelligent precision suggestions when parsing user NL questions. (precisionSuggestionForGivenTypeWhenUnboundInArg UNDERSPECIFIED-PRED FIXED-ARG-POSITION TYPE PRECISION-SUGGESTION OPEN-ARG-POSITION) says that if a user utterance QUERY is parsed into a sentence of the form, (UNDERSPECIFIED-PRED ... TERM-IN-FIXED-ARG-POSITION ... VARIABLE-IN-OPEN-ARG-POSITION) where VARIABLE-IN-OPEN-ARG-POSITION is an unbound variable appearing in the argument position OPEN-ARG-POSITION and TERM-IN-FIXED-ARG-POSITION appears in the argument position FIXED-ARG-POSITION and denotes an instance of TYPE, then the user should be offered (PRECISION-SUGGESTION ... TERM-IN-FIXED-ARG-POSITION ... VARIABLE-IN-OPEN-ARG-POSITION) as a possible precisification of his or her input. For example, (precisionSuggestionForGivenTypeWhenUnboundInArg sizeParameterOfObject 1 GeopoliticalEntity numberOfInhabitants 2) says that if a user utterance is parsed into (sizeParameterOfObject CityOfParisFrance ?SIZE), the user should be offered (numberOfInhabitants CityOfParisFrance ?SIZE) as a possible precisification.
label: Precision Suggestion For Given Type When Unbound In Arg
precisionSuggestionForGivenTypeWhenUnboundInArg

comment:
An instance of BinaryPredicate. intendedOrientation_DeviceType describes the intended orientation, with respect to the object acted on, of a PhysicalDevice being used according to its intendedPrimaryFunction. The orientation is required in order for the device to be causally efficacious in fulfilling the primary function. The orientation is specified in terms of a spatial relation that a specified type of part of the device must bear to a specified sort of situationConstituents in the device's intended use.

In particular, intendedOrientation-DeviceType (DEVICE-TYPE PART-TYPE ROLE RELATION) means that during an instance of the intended primary function of a device of type DEVICE-TYPE, the intended orientation of the device consists in one or more of its physical parts of type PART-TYPE bearing the relation RELATION to one or more of the things that play the role ROLE in the event. For example, (intendedOrientation-DeviceType WritingPen PenTip objectMarked touchesDirectly) means that during any instance of MarkingOnASurfaceWithAPen, a PenTip of the WritingPen that is the deviceUsed should bear the touches_Directly relation to the objectMarked.

Note that the intended orientation need not obtain throughout all of the intended-use event. Rather it must obtain throughout all of each of a certain type of subevent of the intended-use event. For example, although the pen tip need not touch the writing surface during all of a given writing event (e.g., because the writer might lift the pen to dot an "i"), the pen tip does need to touch the writing surface throughout all of each of the writing event's subevents that are of type MarkingOnASurfaceWithAPen_Uninterrupted.
label: Intended Orientation Device Type
intendedOrientation-DeviceType

comment: (resultNamedByArg FN N NAME-STRING-PRED) means that any non-atomic term whose functor is FN is named by its Nth argument. Specifically, NAME-STRING-PRED holds of such a term and its Nth argument.
label: Result Named By Arg
resultNamedByArg

comment: The binary predicate (cycTacticID CYC-TACTIC CYC-PROBLEM SUID) relates an instance of CycTactic qualified by the containing CYC-PROBLEM, with its internal ID.
label: Cyc Tactic ID
cycTacticID

comment: (rangeSystemRequiredToDegreeForLaunchOperation SYSTEM LAUNCH-OP DEGREE) means that SYSTEM is required to DEGREE for LAUNCH-OP,
label: Range System Required To Degree For Launch Operation
rangeSystemRequiredToDegreeForLaunchOperation

comment: (similarWRTTypeSpecsViaBinRel_Inverse THING1 THING2 COL BINPRED) means that if SPEC1 is a spec of COL such that (BINPRED SPEC1 THING1), then either (BINPRED SPEC1 THING2) or there exists a different SPEC2 such that SPEC2 is also a spec of COL, (similarTo SPEC1 SPEC2), and (BINPRED SPEC2 THING2).
label: Similar WRT Type Specs Via Bin Rel Inverse
similarWRTTypeSpecsViaBinRel-Inverse

comment: A quintary predicate used to describe the balanced chemical equation for a given type of ChemicalReaction. In a gaf of the form (chemicalEquation_Balanced R-TYPE LIST1 LIST2 LIST3 LIST4), LIST1 and LIST3 are lists of chemical substances, and LIST2 and LIST4 are list of numbers each of which is the balancing coefficient of the corresponding element in, respectively, LIST1 and LIST3. Thus, (chemicalEquation_Balanced R-TYPE (TheList COMPOUND-1 COMPOUND-2) (TheList 2 3) (TheList PRODUCT-1 PRODUCT-2) (TheList 1 4)) means that in the type of chemical reaction denoted by R-TYPE 2 units of COMPOUND-1 and 3 units of COMPOUND-2 result in 1 unit of PRODUCT-1 and 4 units of PRODUCT-2. Just as in the case of chemicalEquation_Balanced, one should not assume that the equilibrium of REACTION-TYPE lies entirely to the right of the equation.
label: balanced chemical equation
chemicalEquation-Balanced

comment: `(taxableIncomeDuringYear PERSON INCOME YEAR)' means that PERSON's federally taxable income for the year YEAR A.D. was INCOME.
label: Taxable Income During Year
taxableIncomeDuringYear

comment: (internationalMonetaryReservesDuring GE THING MONEY) means that the instance of MonetaryValue MONEY is a measure of the monetary value of the foreign currency reserves of the GeopoliticalEntity GE during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. (To the extent that there is fluctuation in the amount of GE's foreign currency reserves during the temporal extent of THING, NR should be taken to be an average.) A country would be a typical instance of GE. THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event.
label: International Monetary Reserves During
internationalMonetaryReservesDuring

comment: (statusAffected EVT AGT-1 AGT-2 RELN) means that in the ChangeOfStatusEvent EVT, the relation RELN between the agents AGT-1 and AGT-2 is changed somehow (depending on the kind of ChangeOfStatusEvent).
label: Status Affected
statusAffected

comment: (argGenlQuantity REL N QUANT) means that anything given as the Nth argument to REL has to be a quantity subsumed by the quantity QUANT.
label: Arg Genl Quantity
argGenlQuantity

comment: (marketDemandIsPriceUnitElasticWRTChange MARKET PRODUCT OLD-PRICE NEW-PRICE) means that percentage of change in MARKET's price of PRODUCT from OLD-PRICE to NEW-PRICE is identical to the percentage of change in demand for that product at those prices.

comment: (softwareParameterValueInSpecification PARAM VAL SPEC) states that, according to the ProgramSpecification SPEC, the SoftwareParameter PARAM has the value VAL.
label: Software Parameter Value In Specification
softwareParameterValueInSpecification

comment: (formulaTemplateArgSelectionOption TEMPLATE ARG OPT) means that arg position ARG in formula template TEMPLATE has, by default, selection option OPT. This does not mean that no other options are necessarily available, it just means that OPT will be the default selection option. If an arg position in a formula template does not have a formulaTemplateArgSelectionOption assertion, and the formula template does not have a formulaTemplateSelectionOption assertion, then, by default, the arg position in that template will have NonAtomic_SelectionOption.
label: Formula Template Arg Selection Option
formulaTemplateArgSelectionOption

comment: An assertion of the form sitSatisfiesSpecificationForAgents SIT SPEC AGENT) is used to represent the fact that a particular Situation SIT satisfies the NormativeSpecification SPEC for the Agent_Generic AGENT. A NormativeSpecification amounts to a reason for an agent to behave in a particular way. This notion of 'satisfaction' is generic in the sense that the requirements of NormativeSpecification have been met by the Situation SIT such that AGENT need no longer consider how to bring about events which would satisfy SPEC For example, let us say that SPEC has the specification that AGENT goes on vacation to Mexico in May 2004, if SIT is Mexican vacation in May 2004 performed by AGENT, then SIT would bear the relation sitSatisfiesSpecificationForAgents to SPEC and AGENT. This predicate implies that AGENT is aware of SIT.
label: Sit Satisfies Specification For Agents
sitSatisfiesSpecificationForAgents

comment:
(verificationExampleForNCRuleAppliedToString SENTENCE RULE COMPOUND) means that the CycL sentence SENTENCE is a logical sentence whose truth verifies that RULE, a rule for parsing noun compounds (see NounCompoundRule) is a good rule for parsing the particular noun compound STRING. For example, 
 (verificationExampleForNCRuleAppliedToString
   (Quote
     (typicallyRelnTo primaryActivityTypeOfLocation
      (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToFn Field_Land primaryActivityTypeOfLocation
        (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToTypeFn MaintainingSomething objectTakenCareOf CornPlant))  
      (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToTypeFn MaintainingSomething objectTakenCareOf CornPlant))) #$PumpkinPatch-NCR "corn fields")
means that the truth of the CycL sentence 
 (typicallyRelnTo primaryActivityTypeOfLocation
   (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToFn Field_Land primaryActivityTypeOfLocation
     (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToTypeFn MaintainingSomething objectTakenCareOf CornPlant)) 
   (SubcollectionOfWithRelationToTypeFn MaintainingSomething objectTakenCareOf CornPlant))

(transparencyRangeOfType TYPE TRANS-1 TRANS-2) means that all instances of TYPE have some transparency between TRANS-1 and TRANS-2. For example, (transparencyRangeOfType Glass ModeratelyTranslucent Transparent) means that individual pieces of glass will have a transparency somewhere between moderately translucent and completely transparent. comment: (cycLQueryEventVariableConstraints QUERY-EVENT VAR MEANING-SENT) means that VAR is an open or existentially bound CycLVariable in the CycLFormula for the query run during QUERY-EVENT, and MEANING-SENT expresses the constraints on VAR.

comment: A CommonUnaryModalOperator that applies to a quoted instance of CycLSentence_Assertible. (probabilisticallyCertain PROP) means that PROP holds in every element of the sample space (see sampleSpace) that is relevant in the current context. Loosely speaking, (probabilisticallyCertain PROP) means that PROP is assumed to be true no matter how things turn out, i.e. no matter which of the specific scenarios considered relevant (in the current context) is ultimately realized.

comment: (demandAmountDuring PT PRODUCT-TYPE THING AMOUNT) means that the ScalarInterval AMOUNT is a measure of the demand for instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE by the instance of PartiallyTangible PT during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING. In a general economic context, PT will often be an instance of (GroupFn IntelligentAgent). THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. If AMOUNT is a Rate, AMOUNT indicates the average rate of demand for instances of PRODUCT-TYPE by PT during the temporal extent of THING.

To put it a little more roughly (consumerOfResourceTypeInSystem AGENT RESOURCE-TYPE SYSTEM) means that AGENT acts as a component in system, and is capable of doing things that are part of the 'life-process' of the system that involve 'consuming' instances of RESOURCE-TYPE.

That is, if Cyc knows that (isa SYS SYSTYPE) and (holdsIn TEMP (ROLE1 SYS AGENT), (holdsIn TEMP (ROLE2 SYS AGENT)) is semantically constrained to be an unknownSentence: attempting to assert it will generate an error condition.

comment: A SituationTypeTernaryPredicate that is used to describe the functions a given artifact (see Artifact_Generic) is, by design, capable of serving. (intendedBehaviorCapable ARTIFACT SITTYPE ROLE) means that (i) ARTIFACT can play ROLE in situations or events of type SITTYPE (see behaviorCapable) and (ii) ARTIFACT is intended by its designer to play ROLE in situations or events of type SITTYPE. Note that a given artifact can be intended to be capable of serving more than one function. (In contrast, such things typically have just one primary function; see primaryFunction.) For example, a wall calendar is intended to be capable both of being hung on a wall and of being legible; a vacuum cleaner is meant to serve both as a device (see deviceUsed) and -- in virtue of its dust bag -- as a container (see containerUsed) in Vacuuming events.
label: Intended Behavior Capable
intendedBehaviorCapable

comment:
A ternary RuleMacroPredicate (q.v.) that can be used to state that a given binary predicate stands in a certain relation to two collections. (relationExistsAll BINPRED COL1 COL2) means that for any instance INST2 of COL2, there exists some instance INST1 of COL1 such that (BINPRED INST1 INST2) holds. It is equivalent to (and can thus be used in effect as shorthand for) the more complex form 
  (implies
    (isa ?INST2 COL2)
    (thereExists ?INST1
      (and
        (isa ?INST1 COL1)
        (BINPRED ?INST1 ?INST2)))).
For example, (relationExistsAll adjacentTo Harbor PortCity) means that for every port city there exists a harbor to which the city is adjacent. See also relationAllExists and #$NoteAboutUseOfRuleMacroPredicates.
label: Relation Exists All
relationExistsAll

comment: (inheritRolePlayersOfType_SubSitTypeToSitType SIT-TYPE ROLE1 SUB-SIT-TYPE ROLE2 TYPE) means that any instance of TYPE playing ROLE2 in an instance of SUB-SIT-TYPE that is a subsituation of an instance of SIT-TYPE plays ROLE1 in that instance of SIT-TYPE. This predicate allows us to track the identity of participants in a script by the role they play in scenes of the same script. For a dual version of the relation, cf. inheritRolePlayersOfType_SitTypeToSubSitType.
label: Inherit Role Players Of Type Sub Sit Type To Sit Type
inheritRolePlayersOfType-SubSitTypeToSitType

In the special case where THING1 occupies all of THING2, the value of FRACTION would be 1. (FRACTION is always greater than zero if this predicate holds.) See also occupiesMostOf.

comment: (cityGridSectionBoundedBy SECTION ST1 ST2 ST3 ST4) means that SECTION is a roughly rectangular urban region that is completely bounded by segments of each of the streets ST1 - ST4. The relative order (but not the absolute positions) of the 2nd - 5th arguments here is important: it should be physically possible to circle completely SECTION once by starting along ST1 and making successive right-hand turns on ST2, ST3, ST4, and back onto ST1. SECTION must be part of a region that has a GridStreetSystem running through it. To have this predicate correctly relate a given street-bounded rectangular city section SECTION to the four streets that border it, one can fill its arg2 position with any of the four streets, and then continue to fill in the remaining argument-places according to the order in which one would travel along the other three streets if one were circling SECTION in a clockwise fashion (i.e. by making only right-hand turns). See also CityGridSectionFn, citySectionBoundedBy, and cityBlockBoundedBy.
label: City Grid Section Bounded By
cityGridSectionBoundedBy

comment:
A ternary MetaPredicate that relates two predicates to the predicate that is by definition their union or disjunction, which holds whenever either of the first two predicates hold. (predicateUnion UNIONPRED PRED1 PRED2) means that, for any sequence ARGS and any context MT, (UNIONPRED . ARGS) holds in MT if and only if either (PRED1 . ARGS) or (PRED2 . ARGS) holds in MT. UNIONPRED is thus a generalization (via genlPreds) of both PRED1 and PRED1; indeed UNIONPRED is a nearest possible common generalization of the other two predicates.

For example, this holds: 

  (predicateUnion biologicalOffspring biologicalSons biologicalDaughters)
If either PRED1 or PRED2 is of fixed arity N, then the other must either be of arity N or be variable-arity, and UNIONPRED is itself of arity N. If both PRED1 and PRED2 are variable-arity, then so is UNIONPRED.

See also the corresponding function PredicateUnionFn; and see predicateIntersection and #$predicateIsBinaryCompositionOf.
label: Predicate Union
predicateUnion

comment: (several_GenQuantRelnFrom RELN COL THING) is true if several of the instances INST of COL are such that (RELN THING INST) holds.

several-GenQuantRelnFrom

comment: (colorPerceptionCategoryRangeOfType TYPE CATEGORY-1 CATEGORY-2) means that all instances of TYPE, a specialization of SpatialThing_Localized, are instances of some collection COL, where COL is such that: 1) it is an instance of ColorPerceptionCategoryType, and 2) COL falls along a spectrum of color-relevant perceptual properties between CATEGORY-1 and CATEGORY-2. For example, (colorPerceptionCategoryRangeOfType Adamsite LightGreen_Color YellowColor) says that individual samples of adamsite be a color somewhere on the spectrum between light green and yellow. Similarly, (colorPerceptionCategoryRangeOfType NitrogenMustard_1 ColorlessThing PaleYellow_Color) says that samples of HN-1 will be somewhere along the spectrum of having no color to being pale yellow. "The spectrum" here refers to an intuitive range directly between and including the two types; one can think of mixing two substances with those color-perception properties in various proportions to imagine what sorts of types would belong in the spectrum. See also colorRangeOfType, which is restricted to Colors, and is tied to a particular direction around the color wheel, and thus for which argument order matters significantly.
label: Color Perception Category Range Of Type
colorPerceptionCategoryRangeOfType

ARGN) in which ARG4 is an instance of COL, PRED's arg5 position (i.e. the position occupied by the metavariable `ARG5' in the preceding sentence-form) is subject to FORMAT. comment:
This predicate is used to trigger SKSI's database saturation capability. If <RULE> is a CycL conditional formula with free variables in its consequent, <SOURCE_MT> and <TARGET_MT> are microtheories, then asking a query such as

will recursively ask the antecedent of <RULE> in the <SOURCE_MT>, inheriting all of its other inference parameters from the parent query, and then via SKSI attempt to assert the consequent bindings for <RULE> into any databases relevent within the context of <TARGET_MT>. comment: A unique, language-neutral, variable-sized identifier for a concept that can be used to refer unambiguously to that concept across OWL exports or across Cyc inference engines.

A MetaRelation that is used to state that a given function and a given predicate amount to essentially the same relationship, modulo possible (consistent) differences in argument-order and a specification of which argument to the predicate corresponds to the result of the function. (functionCorrespondingPredicate FUNC PRED N) means that FUNC maps a given argument-sequence ARGS (say of length M) to the value VAL if and only if PRED holds of a certain (M+1 length) sequence ARGS-N-VAL, where ARGS-N-VAL has as members all of the members of ARGS and has VAL as its Nth member. The members of ARGS-N-VAL other than VAL must be in some fixed (but unspecified) order in relation to their ordering in ARGS, though this need not be the same order in which they occur in ARGS. Thus PRED will be a FunctionalPredicate (q.v.), with its Nth argument-place being a "functional" one (see functionalInArgs). For example, (functionCorrespondingPredicate StreetCornerFn streetCornerOf 1) implies that (equals (StreetCornerFn XING DIRECTION) LOT) is either equivalent to (streetCornerOf LOT XING DIRECTION) or (streetCornerOf LOT DIRECTION XING). (It is in fact equivalent to the former.) When reifying an instance of Function_Denotational it is generally considered good ontological engineering practice also to reify a (or to find an already-existing) corresponding Predicate, as this allows one to describe more explicitly the relationship between the members of the function's domain and the corresponding members of its range (see relationDomain and relationRange). See also the more specific functionCorrespondingPredicate_Canonical (for cases where the order of arguments in FUNC and PRED is the same, except for the removal of PRED's Nth argument from FUNC's argument list) and the less specific functionCorrespondingPredicate_Generic.
label: Function Corresponding Predicate
functionCorrespondingPredicate

comment: (programRunToSpecificationWithInputYieldsOutput PROGRAM SPECIFICATION INPUT OUTPUT) means that whenever the computer program PROGRAM is run with INPUT in accordance with the instance SPECIFICATION of ProgramSpecification, OUTPUT will be one of its outputs.

comment:
A TernaryPredicate that relates a CycLSentence_Assertible to a SentenceEvaluationOutput to an InformationStore. (sentenceAssignedStatusViaInfoStore SENT STATUS INFOSTORE) means that SENT was assigned STATUS via INFOSTORE -- i.e. INFOSTORE played an instrumentalRole in assigning STATUS to SENT. The InformationStore in question might be, e.g., a Person, a Database_AbstractContent, or an OnlineGameProgram.

For example, 

(sentenceAssignedStatusViaInfoStore 
   (capitalCity Brazil CityOfSaoPauloBrazil)
    #$FalseCycLSentence 
    FACTory_WebGame)
means that (capitalCity Brazil CityOfSaoPauloBrazil) was deemed false via the FACTory web game.

comment: When two surfaces are in contact and relative motion, the frictional resistance is almost uniform over a wide range of low speeds. This resistance is characterized by the kinetic coefficient of friction. The kinetic coefficient is typically less than the coefficient of static friction (see coefficientOfFriction_Static). (coefficientOfFriction_Kinetic OBJ1 OBJ2 NUM) means that NUM is the ratio of the frictional resistance force (see FrictionVector to the normal force which presses the surfaces of OBJ1 and OBJ2 together. See also coefficientOfFriction
label: Coefficient Of Friction Kinetic
coefficientOfFriction-Kinetic

comment: ARG1 is famous to members of ARG2, for the role played in ARG3.  ARG3 should at least refer to ARG1, and probably should be propositionAbout that Agent.  Note that this assertion does not distinguish between fame and infamy - that should be stated elsewhere, e.g. in a likes/dislikes statement, or feelsTowardsEvent.
label: Famous For
famousFor

comment: (tourTransitsFromTo TOUR MOVETYPE FROM TO) means that, according to its itinerary, TOUR is supposed to include a movement of type MOVETYPE from the PartiallyTangible FROM, considered as a fromLocation, to the PartiallyTangible TO, considered as toLocation.
label: Tour Transits From To
tourTransitsFromTo

comment: An instance of TernaryPredicate. recommendedRoleInType relates an instance of SomethingExisting, a specialization of Situation, and an instance of BinaryRolePredicate, so as to express the recommendation that the arg1 play that role in an event of that type. For example, (recommendedRoleInType Person001 CharitableDonation giver) says that it is recommended that Person001 make a donation to some charity. The source of the recommendation (the agent, conceptual work, moral code, etc.) is unspecified with this predicate; accordingly, assertions should be made in a Microtheory (such as the PITOfIBTFn Mt for a work that contains recommendations) that can reflect the source.
label: Recommended Role In Type
recommendedRoleInType

comment: An assertion of the form (functionDescribesForceOnObjectDuring FORCE-FUNC OBJ SIT) states that relative to the PhysicalSituation SIT, the ForceFunction FORCE-FUNC describes a force that is acting on the PartiallyTangible OBJ.
label: Function Describes Force On Object During
functionDescribesForceOnObjectDuring

comment: (keIrrelevantArgConstraint COLL) says that COLL is to be ignored as an argument constraint for every instance of Relation in the KB during UIA interactions in which the argument constraints for REL would otherwise be used to guess or suggest an isa or genls for a term to be related by REL.
label: Ke Irrelevant Arg Constraint
keIrrelevantArgConstraint

comment: (since_Decontextualized INTERVAL PROP PARAMETER) says that the proposition PROP has been, at at temporal granularity of PARAMATER, continuously true since INTERVAL.
label: Since-Decontextualized
since-Decontextualized

comment: (interArgReln_Inferred RELN N M PRED) means that if RELN appears in the zeroth argument position of a CycLSentence in which ARG-N appears as the Nth argument and ARG-M appears as the Mth argument, it should be inferred that (PRED ARG-N ARG-M).
label: Inter Arg Reln Inferred
interArgReln-Inferred

comment: (setUIDOfProgramOn PROGRAM COMPUTER ACCOUNT) means that the default owner of a process started on COMPUTER by PROGRAM is ACCOUNT.
label: Set UID Of Program On
setUIDOfProgramOn
Connected Sheets Diverge
connected-SheetsDiverge
comment: (connected_SheetsDiverge SHEETSERIES) means that a members of series of SheetOfSomeStuff are all connectedAlongEdge to each other along some common connection. The angle between the adjacent sheets may be either acute or obtuse. The connection between the sheets may be an edge of the combined object (as in a book) or not (e.g. the pivot of a turbine).

(dayOfWeekAfterDate_Inclusive DAY-TYPE DATE CALENDAR-DAY) means that CALENDAR-DAY is the instance of DAY-TYPE (a DayOfWeekType) which most closely follows or overlaps the specified date, DATE. This is the predicate corresponding to the EvaluatableFunction, DayOfWeekAfterDateFn_Inclusive.
label: Day Of Week After Date Inclusive
dayOfWeekAfterDate-Inclusive
Queries Jointly Determine Query Answer In Script
queriesJointlyDetermineQueryAnswerInScript
Ignore Temporary For RKF Tool
ignore-Temporary-ForRKFTool
comment: This predicate serves as a wrapper for rules that would normally be used as ke suggestions, see keFacilitationRules, but whose form results in an undesirable user prompt at present. (ignoreAtPresentForRKFTool FORM) does not mean that FORM is incorrect or fails to state a legitimate knowledge entry expectation, however, the natural language that it results in is very awkward and therefore not worthy of demo inclusion. This should serve as a flag for further NL work or perhaps the creation of simpler vocabulary to represent the salient content. This predicate, once it is incorporated into tool function, should be used to hide assertions causing problems for impending demos.

(appropriateEmotion SIT ROLE QUANT) means that in the Situation SIT, an intelligent agent filling the Role ROLE would be expected to feel the quantity of emotion described by QUANT . If such an agent did not feel that emotion, s/he would generally be considered rude or strange. E.g., (HighAmountFn Grief) is an appropriateEmotion for someone in the audience at a funeral (but not for the workers, the deceased, etc.)
label: Appropriate Emotion
appropriateEmotion
Mixed Rule
mixedRule
comment: (mixedRule RULE) means that RULE is "mixed" in the sense that it combines temporally qualifiable and non-temporally qualifiable vocabulary in a way that renders it false under the standard interpretation of its terms. The general consensus seems to be that such rules need to be edited, perhaps by temporally qualifying some of their temporally qualifiable literals with reference to the times at which events referenced by their non-temporally qualifiable literals occur.

(importsThrough REGION PRODUCT-TYPE PT) means that the GeographicalRegion REGION imports significant amounts of instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT on their way from their origin. PT might, in the case of oil imports, for example, be a GeographicalRegion or a Pipeline.
label: Imports Through
importsThrough

comment: Where FORMULA is a CycL formula with a single open variable, (evidenceForIsa CANDIDATE-ISA CANDIDATE-COL FORMULA) means that the fact that CANDIDATE-ISA is returned as (possibly one of several) bindings for the open variable in FORMULA constitutes weak or prima facia evidence for the claim that (isa CANDIDATE-ISA CANDIDATE-COL).
label: Evidence For Isa
evidenceForIsa

comment: (exportRate COUNTRY PRODUCT-TYPE RATE) means that COUNTRY exports PRODUCT-TYPE at the rate of RATE. Note that RATE may be expressed as a MonetaryRate, but also as rate of volume, mass or number depending on the type of product. For example, for oil which is a fluid we can say both (exportRate SaudiArabia PetroleumProduct (MillionDollarsPerYear NR)) and (exportRate SaudiArabia PetroleumProduct (MillionBarrelsPerYear NR)). Note that services, i.e. specializations of ServiceEvents are included as product types.
label: export rate
exportRate

comment: (doGetAccessToAccountOfTypeOn AGENT ACCT_TYPE NETWORK) means that AGENT takes steps toward the goal of controlling an account of type ACCT_TYPE on some machine on NETWORK.
label: Do Get Access To Account Of Type On
doGetAccessToAccountOfTypeOn

comment: (relationAllExistsSame PRED COLL1 COLL2) holds just in case every instance of COLL1 is related by PRED to the same instance of COLL2. For example, if HoustonTexansCollection is the collection of all the group members of the HoustonTexans, then (relationAllExistsSame hasCoach HoustonTexansCollection SportsCoach). This means that every instance of the collection of players on the Houston Texans football team has the same coach. Another example: (relationAllExistsSame uniformColorOfObject Ruby_Gem Color) means every ruby is the same color. This predicate is useful if you want to state that a collection of things all share some feature, but can't be specific about what feature they share.
label: Relation All Exists Same
relationAllExistsSame

comment: An instance of InterArgFormatPredicate (q.v.). (interArgFormat5_1 PRED COL FORMAT) means that FORMAT is a Format (q.v.) requirement for the first argument-place of PRED when PRED's fifth argument is an instance of COL. That is, with respect to a sentence of the form (PRED ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 ARG5 ... ARGN) in which ARG5 is an instance of COL, PRED's arg1 position (i.e. the position occupied by the metavariable `ARG1' in the preceding sentence-form) is subject to FORMAT. See Format and its instances for further explanation.
label: Inter Arg Format 5 1
interArgFormat5-1

comment: ARG3 percent of ARG1's patients are covered by a provider of type ARG2.
label: Percent Of Patients Insured By Type
percentOfPatientsInsuredByType

comment:
A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgEqualsIsa1_4 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when INDEPENDENT-ARG appears as the first argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the fourth argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, (RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 ... ) is semantically well-formed only if ARG4 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL.

For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations. See interArgEqualsIsa for a similar but more general predicate that is quintary, allowing the user to specify the positions of the independent and dependent arguments.
label: Inter Arg Equals Isa 1 4
interArgEqualsIsa1-4

comment: This predicate can be used to indicate when a point that lies on some path in an instance SYS of PathSystem is an 'access point' to that system, i.e. is a point that allows direct external access to SYS via some instance of Path_Simple. More formally, (entryPointOnPathToSystem ENTRY_POINT PATH SYS) means four things: (i) ENTRY_POINT is a point in the system SYS, i.e. (pointInSystem ENTRY_POINT SYS), and ENTRY_POINT is on PATH, i.e. (pointOnPath ENTRY_POINT PATH); there is some OUTSIDE_POINT such that (iia) (pointOnPath OUTSIDE_POINT PATH) and (not (pointInSystem OUTSIDE_POINT SYS)), (iib) the relationship among PATH, OUTSIDE_POINT and ENTRY_POINT is represented by (pathConnects PATH OUTSIDE_POINT ENTRY_POINT), i.e. PATH always allows 'travel' from OUTSIDE_POINT to ENTRY_POINT and often (but not always) from ENTRY_POINT to OUTSIDE_POINT and (iic) if OTHER_POINT is any pointInSystem SYS, then (not (betweenOnPath OTHER_POINT ENTRY_POINT OUTSIDE_POINT (SubPathBetweenFn PATH ENTRY_POINT OUTSIDE_POINT))), in other words, ENTRY_POINT is the first point one would 'encounter' when 'travelling' along PATH from OUTSIDE_POINT into SYS. This predicate is useful for, say, representing the 'access points' to an instance of LocalAreaNetwork from the Internet.
label: entry point into a system
entryPointOnPathToSystem

comment: An IndividualDenotingFunction for denoting a line which intersects ARG1 and ARG2.
label: Straight Line On Points
straightLineOnPoints

comment: (exportDestinationFractionDuring REGION1 REGION2 THING NR) means that NR is the quotient of the monetary value of the exports by the GeographicalRegion REGION1 to the GeographicalRegion REGION2 during the temporal extent of the TemporalThing THING (as dividend) and the monetary value of REGION1's exports of all goods and services during the temporal extent of THING (as divisor). THING will often be a calendar time period; but it may also be, for instance, a particular Event. For example, to express the fact that exports to the United States accounted for 6 percent of the total value of Oman's exports in 1995, we can say (exportDestinationFractionDuring Oman UnitedStatesOfAmerica (YearFn 1995) (Percent 6)). See also exportAmountDuring.
label: Export Destination Fraction During
exportDestinationFractionDuring
Rendering Properties For Arc In System
renderingPropertiesForArcInSystem

comment:
(most_GenQuantRelnTo BINPRED SOC THING) means that most elements of SOC bear BINPRED to THING -- i.e., most elements X of SOC are such that (BINPRED X THING). It is equivalent to the more complex form: 
(most SOC (TheSetOf ?X (BINPRED X THING))).
For example, (most_GenQuantRelnTo fanOf Liberal_SocialDemocrat FranklinRoosevelt) means that most liberals are fans of FDR.

When SOC is a collection, use the more specialized relationMostInstance.
label: Most Gen Quant Reln To
most-GenQuantRelnTo

comment: (powerInRegion_Economic AGENT REGION GENERIC-VALUE-PRED) means that the economic power of the IntelligentAgent AGENT in region REGION is at the level given by GENERIC-VALUE-PRED. Intelligent Agents can have different amounts of economic power in different regions, e.g., (powerInRegion_Economic Mexico UnitedStatesOfAmerica mediumAmountOf) but (powerInRegion_Economic Mexico Cameroon #$lowToVeryLowAmountOf). The Intelligent Agent need not be a GeopoliticalEntity, but could be of the form (powerInRegion_Economic OPEC PersianGulfRegion highAmountOf).
label: Power In Region Economic
powerInRegion-Economic

comment: The corresponding predicate of the function InstanceOfTypeWithIDFromOrganizationFn.
label: Is Individual Of Type Identified With ID String By Organization
isIndividualOfTypeIdentifiedWithIDStringByOrganization

comment: The corresponding predicate of DecreaseInValueReturnedByFn (cf. functionCorrespondingPredicate_Canonical). Where FN is an EvaluatableFunction whose value for admitted argument ARG changes over time, (decreaseInValueReturnedBy FN ARG COL) means that COL is the collection of DecreaseEvents where the scalar value returned by (FN ARG) is strictly greater at the start of the event than at the end.
label: Decrease In Value Returned By
decreaseInValueReturnedBy

comment: In the piece of free space ARG1, from the light source ARG2 a beam of directed light produces illumination of intensity ARG3 in that space. Thus this is used to describe amount of direct sun- or moonlight. In other contexts ARG2 should be more general than AstronomicalBody.
label: Directed Illumination Level
directedIlluminationLevel

comment: anatomicalResourceRequired is an instance of ResourcePredicate. (anatomicalResourceRequired ACT BODYPARTTYPE NUM) means that the successful doer of ACT must have at least this many (NUM) of the AnimalBodyPartType BODYPARTTYPE. For example, if VOLANT is an instance of Flying_FlappingWings, then (anatomicalResourceRequired VOLANT Wing_AnimalBodyPart 2).
label: Anatomical Resource Required
anatomicalResourceRequired

comment: A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgIsa3_5 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL appears as the third argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the fifth argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, if INST is an instance of INDEPENDENT-ARG-COL, then (RELN ARG1 ARG2 INST ARG4 ARG5 ... ARGN) is semantically well-formed only if ARG5 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations.
label: Inter Arg Isa 3 5
interArgIsa3-5

comment: (constraintOnReplacement TEMPLATE POS SET-OR-COLLECTION) means that any term that will replace the term in POS of TEMPLATE must be a member of SET-OR-COLLECTION.
label: Constraint On Replacement
constraintOnReplacement

comment: An instance of InterArgFormatPredicate (q.v.). (interArgFormat4_3 PRED COL FORMAT) means that FORMAT is a Format (q.v.) requirement for the third argument-place of PRED when PRED's fourth argument is an instance of COL. That is, with respect to a sentence of the form (PRED ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 ... ARGN) in which ARG4 is an instance of COL, PRED's arg3 position (i.e. the position occupied by the metavariable `ARG3' in the preceding sentence-form) is subject to FORMAT. See Format and its instances for further explanation.
label: Inter Arg Format 4 3
interArgFormat4-3

comment:
(earliestIntersectingIntervalOfType TEMPORAL-THING INTERVAL TYPE) means that the instance of TimeInterval INTERVAL is the earliest interval of type TYPE that is temporally subsumed by (c.f., temporallySubsumes) the temporal extent of the instance of TemporalThing TEMPORAL-THING. For example, 
    
     (earliestSubsumedIntervalOfType #$WorldWarII 
        (YearFn 1940) CalendarYear)
means that the year 1940 is the first full calendar year that occurs during WWII. See also latestIntersectingIntervalOfType and earliestIntersectingIntervalOfType.
label: Earliest Subsumed Interval Of Type
earliestSubsumedIntervalOfType

comment: (genericallyEquivalentQuantity COL SLOT QUANT GVP) <=> The GenericValuePredicate GVP's arg2 is equivalent to the quantity QUANT when it appears on SLOT in the context of instances of COL. For example, (genericallyEquivalentQuantity Sprinter age (YearsDuration 14 17) lowAmountOf) holds just in case being age 14-17 is a low amount on the slot age with respect to instances of Sprinter. In other words, it states that 14-17 is a low age for sprinters. This is a way to relativize the values for lowAmountOf. It is as if, in the context of sprinter's ages, (lowAmountOf Time_Quantity (YearsDuration 14 17)) holds. Or, equivalently, in the context of sprinter's ages (LowAmountFn Time_Quantity) = (YearsDuration 14 17).
label: Generically Equivalent Quantity
genericallyEquivalentQuantity

comment: Packages of objects of type ARG1 contain ARG2 individuals and cost ARG3 (amount of money).
label: Cost Per Package
costPerPackage

comment: An instance of InterArgFormatPredicate (q.v.). (interArgFormat5_5 PRED COL FORMAT) means that FORMAT is a Format (q.v.) requirement for the fifth argument-place of PRED when PRED's fifth argument is an instance of COL. That is, with respect to a sentence of the form (PRED ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 ARG5 ... ARGN) in which ARG5 is an instance of COL, PRED's arg5 position (i.e. the position occupied by the metavariable `ARG5' in the preceding sentence-form) is subject to FORMAT. See Format and its instances for further explanation. Note that interArgFormat5_5 is one of several "degenerate-case" inter-argument format predicates, in which the specified condition and the corresponding constraint both have to do with the _same_ argument-place of a given predicate.
label: Inter Arg Format 5 5
interArgFormat5-5

comment: '(inheritRolePlayers_SubSitTypeToSubSitType SIT-TYPE ROLE1 SUBSIT-TYPE1 ROLE2 SUBSIT-TYPE2)' means that in any instance SIT of SIT-TYPE whatever things play ROLE1 in the sub-situation SUB1 (an instance of SUBSIT-TYPE1) will also play ROLE2 in sub-situation SUB2 (an instance of SUBSIT-TYPE2). Note that this predicate does not require that there be a unique player of ROLE1 and ROLE2 in SUB1 and SUB2. There could be multiple such role players. For a similar predicate that does have a uniqueness presupposition, see inheritRolePlayers_SubSitTypeToSubSitType_Unique.
label: Inherit Role Players Sub Sit Type To Sub Sit Type
inheritRolePlayers-SubSitTypeToSubSitType

comment: (givesSupportToAgent GIVER RECEIVER SUPPORT-LEVEL) means that the Agent_PartiallyTangible GIVER provides the Agent_PartiallyTangible RECEIVER with the type and level of support SUPPORT-LEVEL.
label: Gives Support To Agent
givesSupportToAgent

comment: (termPhrases_CaseInsensitive_Lexical TERM CONSTRAINT STRING) means that STRING is a word or phrase explicitly in Cyc's lexicon (i.e. not requiring parsing or generation), modulo case, that denotes TERM and that meets CONSTRAINT. Cf. termPhrases_CaseInsensitive.
label: Term Phrases Case Insensitive Lexical
termPhrases-CaseInsensitive-Lexical

comment: This predicate, which corresponds (see functionCorrespondingPredicate) to the function SubstituteFormulaFn, relates an EL formula to the result of substituting one given term for another within that formula. (formulaSubstitutionFor NEWTERM OLDTERM NEWFORMULA OLDFORMULA) means that NEWFORMULA is the #$ELFormula (q.v.) that results from substituting NEWTERM for every occurrence (or for every _free_ occurrence if OLDTERM is a variable) of OLDTERM in OLDFORMULA. (If OLDTERM contains variables VAR1..VARN that occur free in OLDTERM, then an occurrence OLDTERM-OCC of OLDTERM is replaced with NEWTERM if and only if each occurrence of VAR1..VARN that is free in OLDTERM-OCC is also free in FORMULA.) Note that the first two argument-places of the predicate expression `formulaSubstitutionFor' are "quoted" (see quotedArgument), and so terms occupying those places denote (not their usual denotations, if any, but) _themselves_.
label: Formula Substitution For
formulaSubstitutionFor

comment: (protectsFromActionBy TANG PROTECTED ACTIONTYPE DOER) says that the PartiallyTangible TANG protects the PartiallyTangible PROTECTED from any instance ACTION of ACTIONTYPE where (doneBy ACTION DOER).
label: protecting from the action by
protectsFromActionBy

comment: This predicate relates two things in terms of some BinaryPredicate that relates them to similar instances of a given collection of Quantity[ies]. (similarInQuantityRelation T1 T2 BINPRED) means that there are similar instances of Quantity QUANT1 and QUANT2, such that (BINPRED T1 QUANT1) and (BINPRED T2 QUANT2). See also resemblesInQuantity.
label: Similar In Quantity Relation
similarInQuantityRelation

comment: (nthSubSituationTypeInSituationType SIT-TYPE NUM SUBSIT-TYPE) means that SUBSIT-TYPE is the NUMth sub-situation type of type SUBSIT-TYPE in SIT-TYPE.
label: Nth Sub Situation Type In Situation Type
nthSubSituationTypeInSituationType

comment: (playsRoleWithFrequency INSTANCE SITTYPE ROLE FREQ) means that INSTANCE plays ROLE in instances of SITTYPE with the frequency FREQ. Note that FREQ can be a numeric value, or it can be a coarse-grained measure such as Often or Rarely. For a version of this predicate which is type-level with respect to the first argument, see frequencyOfActionType. To state more concisely that an object 'regularly' plays ROLE in instances of SIT-TYPE, see playsRoleInActionTypeRegularly.
label: Plays Role With Frequency
playsRoleWithFrequency

comment:
A statement that the Product Advisor needs to ask the user to disambiguate
previous input.  (paDisambiguatingQuestion TEMPLATE STRING SET) means that the
formula TEMPLATE is true if one of the terms in SET is substituted for
the free variable in TEMPLATE.  In addition, a user has typed in the string
STRING, which is ambiguous over SET, and the only way to disambiguate 
is to ask the user directly.  TEMPLATE must have exactly one free variable; each
element of SET must be an instance of CycLExpression.
label: Pa Disambiguating Question
paDisambiguatingQuestion
Specification For Concept Filter With Mt
specificationForConceptFilterWithMt

comment: (changeTypeInIncomeFromTo TYPE Q1 Q2) identifies TYPE as the subcollection of ChangeInIncome such that every instance is a change in some market of agent income from Q1 to Q2.
label: Change Type In Income From To
changeTypeInIncomeFromTo

comment: An assertion of the form (actFulfillsNthIterationOfDistributedAssignmentForAgent ACT N ASSIGN AGENT) represents the fact that the Situation ACT represents the Nth performance of the sort of action specified by ASSIGN (an instance of both DistributedAssignment and IteratedAssignment) which the IntelligentAgent AGENT is obligated to perform by virtue of filling an #$assignees role for ASSIGN.
label: Act Fulfills Nth Iteration Of Distributed Assignment For Agent
actFulfillsNthIterationOfDistributedAssignmentForAgent

comment: (physicianInRoleForOperationHasName EVENT ROLE NAME-STRING) means that NAME-STRING is the name of the physician who plays ROLE in EVENT.
label: Physician In Role For Operation Has NPI
physicianInRoleForOperationHasNPI

comment: '(roleToRoleDiff EVENT-TYPE ROLE1 ROLE2)' means that whatever plays the role ROLE1 in an instance of EVENT-TYPE is different from whatever plays the role ROLE2 in that same instance.
label: Role To Role Diff
roleToRoleDiff

comment: (performsActsOfType_Number AGENT ACTION-TYPE-1 ACTION-TYPE-2 NUMBER) holds just in case NUMBER of the instances of ACTION-TYPE-1 that AGENT is known by Cyc to perform are also instances of ACTION-TYPE-2. For instance, if 40 of the instances of TerroristAttack that Hamas is known to perform are also instances of Bombing, then (performsActsOfType_Percentage #$TerroristOrganization-Hamas TerroristAttack Bombing 40) holds.
label: Performs Acts Of Type Number
performsActsOfType-Number

comment: A ternary predicate that relates an instance of BinaryPredicate to a term that occurs in a data source, (synonymousExternalPred_Inverse PRED SOURCE STRING) means that the predicate PRED is the co-inverse of a predicate OTHER-PRED (i.e., (inverseBinaryPredicateOf PRED-1 PRED-2) holds) such that, within the data source SOURCE, the string STRING denotes OTHER-PRED.
label: Synonymous External Pred Inverse
synonymousExternalPred-Inverse
subPropertyOf: Generic Cyc L Mapping To Source String

comment: `(feelsSensationInBodyRegion ORG SENSATIONTYPE REGION)' means that the organism ORG is experiencing a sensation of type SENSATIONTYPE as being located in the region of their body REGION.
label: Feels Sensation In Body Region
feelsSensationInBodyRegion

comment: An expression of the form (genlsLinkedArgIsas PRED1 ARG1 PRED2 ARG2 COLLECTION) means that either (1) the collection that is the argIsa value for the Predicate PRED1's ARG1th argument is a sub-collection of the collection that is the argIsa value for the Predicate PRED2's ARG2th value or (2) that the collection that is the argIsa value for the Predicate PRED2's ARG2th argument is a sub-collection of the collection that is the argIsa value for the Predicate PRED1's ARG1th value. Further, the COLLECTION is one of those arguments' constraining collection and, so, is a common sub-collection of both argument's constraining collections.
label: Genls Linked Arg Isas
genlsLinkedArgIsas

comment: An afterslot relating a SKSConnectionSpecification to the name of the database within it that we wish to connect, and to a specific sub-KS.
label: Database Name For SKS
databaseNameForSKS

comment: (relationAllExistsSpec PRED COL1 COL2) means that for every instance, INS1, of COL1, there is some proper subcollection, SPECCOL2, of COL2 such that (PRED INS1 SPECCOL2).
label: Relation All Exists Spec
relationAllExistsSpec

comment: (subcatFrameDependentConstraint FRAME NUM CONSTRAINT) indicates that CONSTRAINT is the PhraseStructureConstraint for the NUM-th dependent in phrases headed by SubcategorizationFrame FRAME. Each dependent of a phrase headed by a given FRAME should be defined by at least one subcatFrameDependentConstraint assertion. In other words, for any given FRAME, if (subcatFrameArity FRAME NUM) is true, then there should be at least NUM subcatFrameDependentConstraint assertions with FRAME as their arg1.
label: Subcat Frame Dependent Constraint
subcatFrameDependentConstraint

comment: (suppliedWithFromThrough PT1 COL PT2 PT3) means that the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 is supplied with instances of the Collection COL from the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2 through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT3 (on their way from PT2 to PT1). Like the predicate suppliedWith (q.v.), suppliedWithFromThrough is very general. In various assertions PT1 might, for instance, be a Cell, a Person, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion; and likewise for PT2. And PT3 might, for example, be a Hose, a Railway, a GeographicalRegion, or a BloodVessel. The range of possible supplies is similarly broad.
label: Supplied With From Through
suppliedWithFromThrough

comment: Rays drawn from some point in arg2 in the direction arg3 intersect with some point of arg1. relativePosition_Vectored is analogous to relativePosition, but uses an instance of UnitVectorInterval where relativePosition cites an instance of #$RelativePositionAttribute.
label: Relative Position Vectored
relativePosition-Vectored

comment:
A quaternary RuleMacroPredicate (q.v.) that can be used to state that a given binary predicate stands in a certain numerical relation with respect to two collections. (relationExistsMaxAll BINPRED COL1 COL2 N) means that for any instance INST of COL2, there are at most N instances of (INST(1), ..., INST(N)) of COL1 such that (BINPRED INST(i) INST) holds (for 1 <= i <= N). This is equivalent to (and can thus be used in effect as shorthand for) the more complex form: 
  (implies
    (isa INST COL2)
    (thereExistAtMost N ?INST-I
      (and
        (isa ?INST-I COL1)
        (BINPRED ?INST-I INST)))).
For example, (relationExistsMaxAll physicalParts Hand Finger 1) means that every finger is part of at most one hand. Cf. relationAllExistsMax, and see the shared #$NoteAboutUseOfRuleMacroPredicates.
label: Relation Exists Max All
relationExistsMaxAll

comment: (recommendedURLWithRedirectString AGENT URL AIS) says that it is recommended that the instance of IntelligentAgent AGENT visit the url URL as presented with the abstract information structure AIS (e.g., AIS might be a GIF or a piece of text).
label: Recommended URL With Redirect String
recommendedURLWithRedirectString

comment: A predicate used to state the highest price that a share of a PubliclyHeldCorporation's #$StockClass has traded at on the current day. (stockPrice_High STOCKTYPE PRICE DATE EXCHANGE) means that PRICE is the highest price paid for a share of STOCKTYPE so far on the CalendarDay that temporally subsumes DATE (i.e. the hightest price paid for such a share between that day's market opening and the end of DATE). Before the market opens, and on days the market is closed, the high for the last day the market was open remains in effect. Cf. stockPrice_Close.
label: high price
stockPrice-High

comment:
(startsAfterStartOfInSituationType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE1 SUBSIT-TYPE2) means that in any instance SIT of SIT-TYPE (a specialization of Situation), if instances SIT1 and SIT2 of SUBSIT-TYPE1 and SUBSIT-TYPE2 occur as subsituations, then SIT1 starts after SIT2 starts.

Note that (startsAfterStartOfInSituationType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE1 SUBSIT-TYPE2) does not imply that instances of SUBSIT-TYPE1 or SUBSIT-TYPE2 occur as subsituations of every instance of SIT-TYPE, since SUBSIT-TYPE1 and SUBSIT-TYPE2 may be merely candidate subsituation types of SIT-TYPE (see candidateProperSubSituationTypes).

comment: (interArgCondIsa2_1 PRED INDEP-COL COND-COL DEP-COL) is shorthand for the class of rules that state the following: For every instance INDEP-INST of INDEP-COL, if there is some instance COND-INST of COND-COL such that (PRED COND-INST INDEP-INST) holds, COND-INST will also be an instance of DEP-COL. For example, (interArgCondIsa2_1 anatomicalParts Head_Vertebrate Organism_Whole Vertebrate) -- if an element of Head_Vertebrate is an anatomicalParts of some Organism_Whole, that organism is a Vertebrate.
label: Inter Arg Cond Isa 2 1
interArgCondIsa2-1

comment:
A TernaryPredicate that relates a Set_Mathematical to a Set_Mathematical to a Real0_1. (probabilityOfSetGivenSet SET1 SET2 N) means that the probability of SET1 given only the information that SET2 is N. SET1 and SET2 are subsets of the relevant sample space (see sampleSpace).

Suppose, for example, that the sample space is (TheSet 1 2 3 4 5 6), representing the possible outcomes of rolling a die. Then (TheSet 1) would correspond to the event or proposition that a 1 is rolled, (TheSet 2 4 6) would correspond to the event or proposition that an even number is rolled, etc. Thus, e.g., in this context 

(probabilityOfSetGivenSet (TheSet 2) (TheSet 2 4 6) (QuotientFn 1 3))
says that the probability of a 2 being rolled given only the information that an even number is rolled is 1/3.

Note that the conditional probability of H given E, usually written P(H|E), is by definition, the (unconditional) probability of the intersection of H and E divided by the (unconditional) probability of E. Note also that this is undefined when the (unconditional) probability of E is 0.

See also conditionalProbability, which relates CycL sentences instead of sets.
label: Probability Of Set Given Set
probabilityOfSetGivenSet

comment: A sentence of the form (wordAllHypernymStringsForPOS WORD SET-OF-STRINGS POS) means that a consultation of a WordNetKnowledgeBase using the LexicalWord WORD for the WordNetSpeechPart POS will return the set of strings SET-OF-STRINGS. SET-OF-STRINGS is the union of the all the strings that are associated with all of the hypernyms of WORD for POS.
label: Word All Hypernym Strings For POS
wordAllHypernymStringsForPOS

comment: (specificationVariantInParameterValue VARIANT SPEC PARAMETER VALUE) identifies VARIANT as the instance of ProgramSpecification that is identical to the specification SPEC but for its setting the parameter PARAMETER to the value VALUE.

specificationVariantInParameterValue

comment: '(equivalentRolePlayers_SubSitTypeToSubSitType SITTYPE ROLE1 SUBSITTYPE1 ROLE2 SUBSITTYPE2)' means that in any instance SIT of SITTYPE, where SUB1 and SUB2 are sub-situations of SIT and instances of SUBSITTYPE1 and SUBSITTYPE2, respectively, whatever things play ROLE1 in SUB1 also play ROLE2 in SUB2, and vice versa.

equivalentRolePlayers-SubSitTypeToSubSitType

comment:
A KEFacilitationPredicate and RuleMacroPredicate. (keSuggestionPreds_SpecIns COL1 BINPRED COL2) means that for every known specialization SPEC1 of COL1, it is suggested that there be some instance INS2 of COL2 such that (BINPRED SPEC1 INS2) is known in the knowledge base.

For example,

(keSuggestionPreds_SpecIns FruitOrVegetableFood typicalColorOfType Color)

means that for every known specialization FV-TYPE of FruitOrVegetableFood, it is suggested that there be some instance COLOR of Color such that (typicalColorOfType FV-TYPE COLOR) is known in the knowledge base.

comment: This relation is used to state a measure of the likelihood of an ailment's being transmitted from one type of organism to another. Specifically, (ailmentContagiousWithContactFromTo INFECTION-TYPE TRANSMITTER-TYPE TRANSMITTEE-TYPE LEVEL) means that in a case where there is a PhysicalContactSituation between an instance of TRANSMITTER-TYPE and an instance of TRANSMITTEE-TYPE at a time while the instance of TRANSMITTER-TYPE has an infection of type INFECTION-TYPE, the likelihood that the instance of TRANSMITTEE-TYPE will contract the infection is LEVEL.

comment:
A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgEqualsIsa3_5 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when INDEPENDENT-ARG appears as the third argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the fifth argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, (RELN ARG1 ARG2 INDEPENDENT-ARG ARG4 ARG5...) is semantically well-formed only if ARG5 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL.

For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations. See interArgEqualsIsa for a similar but more general predicate that is quintary, allowing the user to specify the positions of the independent and dependent arguments.
label: Inter Arg Equals Isa 3 5
interArgEqualsIsa3-5

comment: This predicate relates objects according to nearness conventions associated with roles in an event type. (nearForRolesInEventType OBJ1 OBJ2 ROLE1 ROLE2 EVENTTYPE) means that OBJ1 and OBJ2 are near each other with respect to the roles ROLE1 and ROLE2 in an event of type EVENTTYPE. For instance, (nearForRolesInEventType OBJ1 OBJ2 ROLE1 ROLE2 EVENTTYPE) means that were PLAYER1 and PLAYER2 playing ROLE1 and ROLE2 respectively in an EVENT of type EVENTTYPE they would be near each other according to the conventions associated with those roles in that event type. (see nearnessForRolesInEventType). Note that (nearForRolesInEventType OBJ1 OBJ2 ROLE1 ROLE2 EVENTTYPE) doesn't imply that OBJ1 is playing ROLE1 and OBJ2 is playing ROLE2 in an event of type EVENTTYPE but only that they'd be deemed to be near each other, relative to these roles, if they were participating in an event of type EVENTTYPE. For instance, if Person001 is one kilometer from GasStation001 we might assert that (nearForRolesInEventType PersonOO1 GasStation001 transportees toLocation TransportWithMotorizedLandVehicle) but it would not necessarily be simultaneously true that (nearForRolesInEventType Person001 GasStation001 performedBy toLocation Walking_Generic). Also note that while (nearForRolesInEventType OBJ1 OBJ2 ROLE1 ROLE2 EVENTTYPE) doesn't imply that OBJ1 and OBJ2 are participating in an event of type EVENTTYPE it does imply that OBJ1 and OBJ2 are capable of playing ROLE1 and ROLE2 respectively in events of type EVENTTYPE. See nearnessForRolesInEventType for a useful corresponding predicate.
label: Near For Roles In Event Type
nearForRolesInEventType
