inheritRolePlayers-SitTypeToSubSitType

comment: (assertedArg1BinaryPreds_Count COL BIN-PRED N) means that there are N instances INS of COL for which it has been asserted for some VALUE (not necessarily the same for each) that (BIN-PRED INS VALUE). Note that this predicate is itself notAssertible (q.v.), since it must be computed from the state of the knowledge base.
label: counted assertion arg1 binary predicate
assertedArg1BinaryPreds-Count

comment: An instance of InterArgFormatPredicate (q.v.). (interArgFormat4_4 PRED COL FORMAT) means that FORMAT is a Format (q.v.) requirement for the fourth argument-place of PRED when PRED's fourth argument is an instance of COL. That is, with respect to a sentence of the form (PRED ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 ... ARGN) in which ARG4 is an instance of COL, PRED's arg4 position (i.e. the position occupied by the metavariable `ARG4' in the preceding sentence-form) is subject to FORMAT. See Format and its instances for further explanation. Note that interArgFormat4_4 is one of several "degenerate-case" inter-argument format predicates, in which the specified condition and the corresponding format constraint both have to do with the _same_ argument-place of a given predicate.
label: Inter Arg Format 4 4
interArgFormat4-4

comment: A predicate used to map representational systems into CycL. It is used in lieu of synonymousExternalConcept when the system uses strings rather than terms to denote some concept, a common practice in rdf-based representations that treat relations as having 'domains' (whose objects are typically represented using terms of the representation language) and 'ranges' (frequently represented using strings, uninterpreted symbols, numerals, and floats). For example, a system SYS might represent that a particular object OBJ is blue with a triple, 'REF color "blue"' where 'REF' represents OBJ, 'color' represents the color relation, represented in CycL as mainColorOfObject, and the string "blue" represents the color blue. In order to map this example into Cyc, we would add a synonymousExternalConcept assertion associating the SYS terms REF, an interpretationForSystemString assertion associating "blue" with BlueColor, and an assertion of the form (interpretationForPredWithStringInArg mainColorOfObject SYS color 2) where the integer 2 indicates that color takes a string in its second argument.
label: Interpretation For Pred With String In Arg
interpretationForPredWithStringInArg

comment:
A ternary predicate that relates a given edge of a Triangle to the size of the angle (see AngularDistance) opposite that edge. (oppositeAngle EDGE DEGREES TRIANGLE) means that DEGREES is the size of the angle formed by the two sides of TRIANGLE that are not EDGE.

See also angleBetweenEdgesOfObject and #$Angle.
label: Opposite Angle
oppositeAngle

comment: (wordUnitConstraintForNCR RULE INDEXICAL WORD) means that RULE requires its NounCompoundRuleIndexicalTerm_Direct term INDEXICAL to be a form of the LexicalWord WORD. In general, this means that there will a ncRuleConstraint relating rule RULE to the constraint (NCWordUnitConstraintFn INDEXICAL WORD).
label: Word Unit Constraint For NCR
wordUnitConstraintForNCR

comment: A line, LINE is tangent to a curve, CURVE at a point, POINT if and only if both LINE and CURVE pass through POINT with the same direction and slope. In Cyc, this relation is stated as (tangentLineAtPointOnCurve POINT LINE CURVE).
label: Tangent Line At Point On Curve
tangentLineAtPointOnCurve

comment: A SpatialPredicate that relates a pair of bordering spatial things to parts of the border that separates them. (formsBorderBetween BORDER REG1 REG2) means that BORDER constitutes at least part of the border between REG1 and REG2. BORDER may be a surface separating two regions of space, or a curve separating two regions of a surface. REG1 and REG2 may be physical objects, geographical regions, or intangible spatial lines or regions. Note that BORDER need not constitute the entire border between REG1 and REG2. By contrast, the more specialized predicate borderBetweenRegions relates a pair of GeographicalRegions to their entire shared border; see also the corresponding function BorderBetweenFn.
label: Forms Border Between
formsBorderBetween

comment: (intendsByUtterancePeg SPEAKER PEG INTERPRETATION) says that SPEAKER, an instance of IntelligentAgent, intended to refer to INTERPRETATION when introducing the instance of LinguisticExpressionPeg PEG in discourse. For example, (intendsByUtterancePeg #$DaveS #$MyDog-Peg #$Bailey) says that Dave S intended to refer to his dog Bailey when he uttered "my dog." For a version of intendsByUtterancePeg that makes explicit some of the larger context in which the interpreted peg is introduced, see intendsByInUtterancePegContext.
label: Intends By Utterance Peg
intendsByUtterancePeg

comment: The predicate waveSource is used to indicate that a type of wave is travelling between a source and a reception point. (waveSource SOURCE ENDPOINT WAVETYPE) means that there is a WavePropagation of type WAVETYPE propagating between the fromLocation SOURCE and the toLocation ENDPOINT. For example, (waveSource VoiceOfAmerica-Seoul CityOfBeijingChina RadioWave).
label: Wave Source
waveSource

comment: (supplyRateThrough PT1 COL PT2 RATE) means that the instance of PartiallyTangible PT1 is supplied with instances of the Collection COL through the instance of PartiallyTangible PT2 (on their way from their origin to PT1) at the Rate RATE. Like the predicate suppliedWith (q.v.), supplyRateThrough is very general. In various assertions PT1 might, for instance, be a Cell, a Person, a Business, or a GeographicalRegion; and PT3 might, for example, be a Hose, a Railway, a GeographicalRegion, or a BloodVessel. The range of possible supplies is similarly broad.
label: Supply Rate Through
supplyRateThrough

comment: This is a type-constrained version of the primitive role inheritance predicate, #$inheritRole. (inheritRolePlayersOfType SIT-TYPE SUBSIT-TYPE-FROM SUBSIT-TYPE-TO ROLE-FROM ROLE-TO ACTOR-TYPE) means that where SIT is an instance of SIT-TYPE, any actor of type ACTOR-TYPE that plays the role ROLE-FROM in an instance of SUBSIT-TYPE-FROM that is a subSituations of SIT also plays the role ROLE-TO in any instance of SUBSIT-TYPE-TO that is a subSituations of SIT.
label: Inherit Role Players Of Type
inheritRolePlayersOfType

comment: If agent ARG1 uses the item ARG2, then the ease with which that agent can perform instances of ARG3 becomes ARG4.
label: Ease Of Performance With
easeOfPerformanceWith

comment: The corresponding predicate of the function DisambiguationStrategyFromPredAndRewardedArgsFn. A sentence of the form (disambiguationStrategyFromPredAndRewardedArgs STRAT PRED SET-OF-INTEGERS) states that the DisambiguationScoringStrategy STRAT is based on the Predicate PRED and that it will assign scores (or reward) instances of SemanticInterpretationHypothesisMicrotheory that posit meanings (see #$mtFocalContent and pegInterpretation_CycL) that (1) can be proven to enter into the relation expressed by PRED and which fill the Nth argument of that relationship, where N is an element of SET-OF-INTEGERS.
label: Disambiguation Strategy From Pred And Rewarded Args
disambiguationStrategyFromPredAndRewardedArgs

comment: An expression of the form (selectedCycLViaStringRep EVT CYCL STRING) means that during the SelectingSomething EVT, the CycLExpression CYCL was indicated (perhaps without their knowing) via some representation of the CharacterString STRING. For example, if a graphical user interface displays the string 'dog' as the generation for the CycLConstant Dog this relation would hold between that event, the string that is represented in the GUI and Dog.
label: Selected Cyc L Via String Rep
selectedCycLViaStringRep

comment: (typicallyRelnToType PRED SET-OR-COL-1 SET-OR-COL-2) means that typically (i.e., most and some) elements EL-1 of SET-OR-COL-1 are such that there exists an element EL-2 of SET-OR-COL-2 such that (PRED EL-1 EL-2).
label: Typically Reln To Type
typicallyRelnToType
subPropertyOf: Most Gen Quant Reln To Type

comment: The agent ARG1 owes to the agent ARG2 the money (amount) ARG3.
label: Agent Owes Agent Amount
agentOwesAgentAmount

comment: Agent ARG1 is paid (for a debt incurred in event ARG2) at time ARG3 the amount of money ARG4.
label: Payment In
paymentIn

comment: (eMailDataOfTypeToAccountsOfUsersOfSystem AGENT DATA-TYPE SYSTEM) means that AGENT emails data of DATA-TYPE to the accounts of users on SYSTEM.
label: E Mail Data Of Type To Accounts Of Users Of System
eMailDataOfTypeToAccountsOfUsersOfSystem

comment: (dilutedEPSForPeriodByAccountingCOC ORG MONEY TIME COC) means MONEY is the amount earned (i.e. profit) by ORG during TIME per share of stock according to the calculation techniques allowed by the AccountingCOC COC. This is calculated using the diluted number of shares in ORG, which may be higher than the actual number of shares outstanding. The diluted number of shares includes the number of shares that are 'spoken for', through means such as options or warrants to buy stock.
label: Diluted EPS For Period By Accounting COC
dilutedEPSForPeriodByAccountingCOC

comment: (kEInteractionFolderOfUserForTaskWRTConcept AGENT ALLOTMENT THING FOLDER) means that FOLDER is the KEInteractionFolder associated with the IntelligentAgent AGENT, for the task ALLOTMENT, with respect to the concept THING that is relevant to ALLOTMENT.
label: KE Interaction Folder Of User For Task WRT Concept
kEInteractionFolderOfUserForTaskWRTConcept

comment: (uninterestingForArgTypeInReln TYPE RELATION NUMBER) says that for any instance INS of TYPE and any formula FORMULA of the form (RELATION ... INS ...) where INS appears in the NUMBERth argument place of FORMULA, FORMULA is uninteresting. See also uninterestingForArgInReln.
label: Uninteresting For Arg Type In Reln
uninterestingForArgTypeInReln

comment: (istDecreasesSlotValue INDPROP DEPPROP SLOT) means that the value that SLOT takes in the arg2 position for DEPPROP will be less if INDPROP is provable than it will be if INDPROP is not provable.
label: Ist Decreases Slot Value
istDecreasesSlotValue

comment: (consumptionRate PT PRODUCT-TYPE RATE) means that the instance of PartiallyTangible PT consumes instances of the ProductType PRODUCT-TYPE at the Rate RATE. PT might, for example, be a Country or a Business.
label: consumption rate
consumptionRate

comment: (keViewSentences TERM VIEW FORMULA) states that FORMULA is a CycL formula involving TERM which is known to be true, and which describes TERM as seen from a particular VIEW.
label: Ke View Sentences
keViewSentences

comment:
(orthogonalArgIsasLinkedByInDet_Specialization PRED1 PRED1-ARGN PRED2 PRED2-ARGN COL DET) means COL is the collection intersection of two orthogonal collections -- namely, the constraining collections for the PRED1-ARGNth argument of PRED1 and the PRED2-ARGNth argument of PRED2, when those constraining collections are considered relative to the InductiveLogicProgrammingDetermination DET. COL is constructed in the following way:

1. All of the argIsa assertions for the predicates in DET are compiled into a set S.
2. S is then reduced to S'using the function MinCollectionsFn.
3. COL is composed of the two collections in S' that are sub-collections of the constraining collections for the relevant argument positions of PRED1 and PRED2.
label: Orthogonal Arg Isas Linked By In Det Specialization
orthogonalArgIsasLinkedByInDet-Specialization

comment: (aheadWRTTrajectory EVT OBJ1 OBJ2) is true iff OBJ1 lies ahead of OBJ2 along the trajectory of EVT, where EVT is an instance of Movement_TranslationEvent. The trajectory of EVT may be cyclical, or anyway non-linear. Note that neither OBJ1 nor OBJ2 need be objects moving in EVT: for instance, in a trip from Austin to New Orleans this predicate would hold true of, respectively, the trip itself, New Orleans and Austin -- as well as of the trip, New Orleans and Houston.
label: Ahead WRT Trajectory
aheadWRTTrajectory

comment:
An instance of RuleMacroPredicate. 
  (binaryPredicateLicensesSenseExtensionFromPOSToPOS2_1 PREDICATE POS-1 POS-2)
is shorthand for 
  (predicateLicensesSenseExtensionFromPOSInArgToPOSInArg PREDICATE POS-1 2 POS-2 1)
where PREDICATE is restricted to instances of BinaryPredicate.
label: Binary Predicate Licenses Sense Extension From POS To POS 2 1
binaryPredicateLicensesSenseExtensionFromPOSToPOS2-1
Schema Representation Complete
schemaRepresentationComplete
comment: (schemaRepresentationComplete SCHEMA) means that the KB representation of the physical/logical schema SCHEMA is complete, meaning that all necessary information required to register the SKSI removal modules for a knowledge source using this schema has been asserted in the KB. The extent of this predicate is used by afterAddings/afterRemovings designed to update the cost estimate information in the KB in case of modifications to the representations of existing (known to be complete) schemata.

This predicate is used to state a comparison which holds between the referent values of two physical field indexicals. Ground formulas using it usually appear within a rowInSourceClaims sentence which determines the referent value of both indexicals. See also the special case fieldIndexicalsEqual.
label: Field Indexicals Comparison
fieldIndexicalsComparison

comment: The predicate denotationRelatedTo is used to link English words with concepts indirectly related to their meanings. For instance, both #$Wife-TheWord and #$Husband-TheWord are semantically connected to the predicate wife, but the two words do not denote the same relation. If (denotationRelatedTo #$Husband-TheWord CountNoun 0 wife), we know that the word 'husband' somehow relates to wife, but should not be taken to denote it.
label: Denotation Related To
denotationRelatedTo
Type Controls Output Of Type In Event Type
typeControlsOutputOfTypeInEventType

comment: A predicate used to describe the semantics of instances of Graph_CW. (graphRiseDerivedFromRelationArg GRAPH PRED INT) means that the points along the yAxis on the graphical structure of GRAPH represent the values of the INTth argument place for PRED relations encoded in GRAPH.
label: Graph Rise Derived From Relation Arg
graphRiseDerivedFromRelationArg
subPropertyOf: Field Type Derived From Relation Arg

comment: (rankedParseTermForPeg PEG TERM RANK) means that TERM, the initial parser output for the utterance associated with the LinguisticExpressionPeg PEG, has been assigned a rank RANK as a measure of how likely it to be the correct (initial) parse for PEG. See also possibleParseTermForPeg, #$chosenParseTermForPeg, and clarifiedParseTermForPeg.
label: Ranked Parse Term For Peg
rankedParseTermForPeg

comment: (violatesConstraintForNCR NODE RULE CONSTR) means that the SyntacticNode NODE violates the syntactic constraint CONSTR (cf. #$NounCompoundConstrain) for the NounCompoundRule RULE.
label: Violates Constraint For NCR
violatesConstraintForNCR

comment: (inferenceReliesOnInfoStructure TEST-QUERY INFO STRING) holds just in case the query TEST-QUERY requires the information provided by the text string STRING which is a part of INFO. INFO will usually be denoted by DocumentSentenceFn which specifies a particular sentence in a particular NLDocument.
label: Inference Relies On String In Info Structure
inferenceReliesOnStringInInfoStructure

comment:
A ternary TemporalPredicate that is used to state how long one TemporalThing starts after another ends. (startsDurationAfterEndingOf AFTER TIME BEFORE) means that AFTER starts duration TIME after BEFORE ends. That is, the startingPoint (q.v.) of AFTER is after the endingPoint (q.v.) of BEFORE, by an interval of Time_Quantity TIME.

See also startsAfterEndingOf and startsDurationAfterStartingOf.
label: Starts Duration After Ending Of
startsDurationAfterEndingOf

comment: A sentence of the form (candidateNCScoreForRuleWRTThresholds NC-RULE COMPOUND-THRESHOLD COMPONENT-THRESHOLD DATE RESULT SCORE) means that for some (implicit) candidate nc test for RULE which yielded RESULT on DATE, evaluation of RESULT with "minimum hit" threholds of COMPOUND-THRESHOLD and COMPONENT-THRESHOLD produced a score of SCORE.
label: Candidate NC Score For Rule WRT Thresholds
candidateNCScoreForRuleWRTThresholds

comment: (conceptPotentiallyInterestingToForDomainBecause AGENT CONCEPT DOMAIN REASON) means that AGENT may be interested in CONCEPT in the topic DOMAIN because of REASON.
label: Concept Potentially Interesting To For Domain Because
conceptPotentiallyInterestingToForDomainBecause

comment: (ventilationSubsumesOperationOfDuration VENT OP HOURS-DURATION) means that VENT temporally subsumes OP and occurs during the same hospitalization and HOURS-DURATION is the time between the min date of the operating room entry and the max date of the operating room exit for OP.
label: Ventilation Subsumes Operation Of Duration
ventilationSubsumesOperationOfDuration

comment: Like (structureMaps ?Src ?Src-Mt ?Tgt ?Tgt-Mt ?Src-Desc ?Tgt-Desc), except (structureDiffs ?Src ?Src-Mt ?Tgt ?Tgt-Mt ?Src-Desc ?Tgt-Desc) returns axioms that are structurally isomorphic but differ in at least one argument position. structureDiffs thus implements the theory of 'alignable differences'. See also structureMaps.
label: Structure Diffs
structureDiffs
Glf Proxy Link Between In System
glfProxyLinkBetweenInSystem

comment: (sitTypeHasLesserCardinalityWRTSitType SIT-TYPE-1 COLL SIT-TYPE-2 ROLE) holds just in case individuals playing ROLE in situations that are instances of SIT-TYPE tend to be appropriately related to fewer instances of COLL than individuals playing ROLE in instances of SIT-TYPE-2 . For instance, (sitTypeHasLesserCardinalityWRTSitType Cohabitating-Unmarried Rights-Abstract Cohabitating-Married) means that couple who are involved in cohabitation situations who are unmarried tend to have fewer rights than couple who are involved in cohabitation situations who are married.
label: Sit Type Has Lesser Cardinality WRT Sit Type
sitTypeHasLesserCardinalityWRTSitType

comment:
If SPACE is a TopologicalSpace with base set BASE (see baseSetOfTopologicalSpace), SET is a subset of BASE, and SYSTEM is a set of subsets of BASE, then SYSTEM is called a fundamental system of neighborhoods of SET, and we write in CycL 
(fundamentalSystemOfNeighborhoodsOfSet SET SYSTEM SPACE)
if and only if for each neighborhood, NEIGHBORHOOD1, of SET, (see neighborhoodOfSetInTopologicalSpace) there exists a neighborhood, NEIGHBORHOOD2, of SET, that is an element of SYSTEM and is a subset of NEIGHBORHOOD1.
label: Fundamental System Of Neighborhoods Of Set
fundamentalSystemOfNeighborhoodsOfSet

comment: (exploitFaultOfProgramOnSystem AGENT FAULT PROGRAM SYSTEM REP) means that AGENT exploits the FAULT of PROGRAM reported in REP when PROGRAM is running on SYSTEM.
label: Exploit Fault Of Program On System Report Indexed
exploitFaultOfProgramOnSystem-ReportIndexed

comment: (fromFacetGLFArc NODE1 NODE2 SYSTEM ARC) means that ARC is the SOEFacetingArc that links NODE1 to NODE2 in SYSTEM, and that ARC has (InverseBinaryPredicateFn isa) as its semantics.
label: From Facet GLF Arc
fromFacetGLFArc

comment: (roleCardinalityForSituationType SIT-TYPE ROLE EXTENT) means that for any instance, SIT, of SIT-TYPE, if anything plays ROLE in SIT, then the number of things that play ROLE in SIT is within the range EXTENT (that is, the number of things that play ROLE in SIT is between the minimum and the maximum of EXTENT, inclusive--see minQuantValue and maxQuantValue)
label: Role Cardinality For Situation Type
roleCardinalityForSituationType

comment: (fixedSoftwareParameterValueInSoftwareObject PARAM VAL SOFTWARE) states that in the SoftwareObject SOFTWARE, the value of PARAM will be VAL, and SOFTWARE does not provide a mechanism for changing it from that value.
label: Fixed Software Parameter Value In Software Object
fixedSoftwareParameterValueInSoftwareObject

comment: (predicateIsComposedOfThroughArg1Positions COMP-PRED PRED-1 PRED-2) means that the binary predicate COMP-PRED is the composition of the binary predicates PRED-1 and PRED-2 such that if (predicateIsComposedOfThroughArg1Positions COMP-PRED PRED-1 PRED-2), then (COMP-PRED X Z) if and only if there is something, Y, such that (PRED-1 Y X) and (PRED-2 Y Z).
label: Predicate Is Composed Of Through Arg 1 Positions
predicateIsComposedOfThroughArg1Positions

comment: (doOverrunLogFileTypeOfProgram AGENT INFO PROG) means that AGENT overruns the log file for PROG that contains INFO.
label: Do Overrun Log File Type Of Program
doOverrunLogFileTypeOfProgram
Event To Occur
eventToOccur
comment: an event which is already specified in the COA context is to be enabled in the goal context, for example, its preconditions could be achieved or maintained.

A ternary RuleMacroPredicate that is used to state that a given binary predicate holds between all instances of a given collection and a given thing. (relationAllInstance PRED COL THING) means that every instance INST of COL bears the relation PRED to THING such that (PRED INST THING) holds. It is equivalent to (and can thus be used in effect as shorthand for) the more complex form: 

     (implies
          (isa ?INST COL)
          (PRED ?INST THING)) .

For example, '(relationAllInstance maxSpeed GolfCart (MilesPerHour 15))' means that the maximum speed of every golf cart is 15 miles per hour. Cf. relationInstanceAll, and see #$NoteAboutUseOfRuleMacroPredicates.
label: Relation All Instance
relationAllInstance

comment:
A ternary RuleMacroPredicate that relates a predicate to a pair of collections such that each instance of the first (second) collection is related by the predicate to (from) ecsctly one instance of the second (first) collection. Thus, (collRelation PRED COL1 COL2) is true if and only if both of these are true: 
  (relationAllExistsUnique PRED COL1 COL2)

  (relationExistsUniqueAll PRED COL1 COL2)
For example, 
  (collRelationUnique internalParts Thigh Femur)
means that (i) every thigh has or had a unique femur inside it and (ii) every femur is or was inside a unique thigh.
label: Coll Relation Unique
collRelationUnique

comment: (syntacticNodeNthDaughter MOTHER N DTR) means that DTR is the Nth daughter of MOTHER, where the value of N for the first daughter node is 1.
label: Syntactic Node Nth Daughter
syntacticNodeNthDaughter

comment: This predicate specifies the fraction by which a given quantity changes in a given time period. (changesQuantityByFraction TIME THING SLOT FRACTION) means that during TIME, THING's QuantitySlot SLOT changes by FRACTION. TIME is a TemporalThing, and Fraction is a ScalarInterval (which may be positive or negative). For instance, (changesQuantityByFraction (YearFn 1980) SaudiArabia oilExport (Percent 10)) means that in 1980, Saudi Arabia's oil export increased by 10 percent. See also: changesQuantityByAmount, changesQuantityInDirection.
label: Changes Quantity By Fraction
changesQuantityByFraction

comment: (oughtToBe_SitRolePlayerOfType SIT ROLE OBLIGATORY-TYPE) means that at least one object playing ROLE in SIT should be an instance of OBLIGATORY-TYPE. That is, there should be an instance OBLIGATORY-INS of OBLIGATORY-TYPE such that (ROLE SIT OBLIGATORY-INS). Assertions involving this predicate -- which specify what should be the case -- should be made in a normative context, e.g., one that reflects the contents of a particular CodeOfConduct. Usually, SIT will be subject to such a requirement in virtue of satisfying some general description, e.g., one stated in the antecedent of a CycLRuleAssertion.
label: Ought To Be Sit Role Player Of Type
oughtToBe-SitRolePlayerOfType
subPropertyOf: Ought To Be Sit Relation To Type

comment: (symptomOnsetRateForConditionType SYMPTOM AILMENT TIME) says that sympmtoms of type SYMPTOM will typically appear at a Time_Quantity TIME from the start of any instance of AILMENT.
label: symptom onset rate
symptomOnsetRateForConditionType

comment: This pred allows the use of a SubcategorizationFrame with a multi word string. The first three args function as in multiWordString. When the string produced appears with the arg4 SubcategorizationFrame, it is translated into CycL with the arg5 NLTemplateExpression.
label: Multi Word Sem Trans
multiWordSemTrans

comment: (agentPlaysRoleInEventsDuring-Count ROLE AGENT COLL DATE INT) means that the agent AGENT played the role ROLE in exactly INT events that were instances of COLL during the time period DATE.
label: Agent Plays Role In Events During Count
agentPlaysRoleInEventsDuring-Count

comment: (typesHaveRelationInSituationType SIT-TYPE TYPE1 TYPE2 BINREL) means that if instances of TYPE1 and TYPE2 play roles in any instance SIT of SIT-TYPE, then it will hold throughout SIT (see holdsIn) that the instance of TYPE1 will have the relation BINREL to the instance of TYPE2.
label: Types Have Relation In Situation Type
typesHaveRelationInSituationType

comment: (durationRangeForSubSituationType SIT-TYPE SUB-SIT-TYPE MIN-DUR MAX-DUR) means that SUB-SIT-TYPE is a sub-situation type of SIT-TYPE, and that the duration of sub-situations of an instance of SIT-TYPE which are instances of SUB-SIT-TYPE is between MIN-DUR and MAX-DUR.
label: Duration Range For Sub Situation Type
durationRangeForSubSituationType

comment: (translationOfCWToISIn PCW TEXT LANGUAGE) means that TEXT is a translated text of the PropositionalConceptualWork, PCW, into LANGUAGE from the language of its original AbstractInformationStructure.
label: Translation Of CW To IS In
translationOfCWToISIn

comment: A simple event-predicate template. (actorRoles_EPFT EVT-TYPE (ActorPlaysRoleFn ACTOR1 ROLE1) (ActorPlaysRoleFn ACTOR2 ROLE2) ...) means that an instance of EVT-TYPE occurs which is also an instance of (ActorPlaysRoleFn ACTOR1 ROLE1), and (ActorPlaysRoleFn ACTOR2 ROLE2), and so on. In other words, it means an instance of EVT-TYPE occurs in which ACTOR1 is engaged by the relation expressed by ROLE1, and in which ACTOR2 is engaged by the relation expressed by ROLE2, and so on. For example, (actorRoles_EPFT ImposingSanctions (ActorPlaysRoleFn UNSecurityCouncil performedBy) (ActorPlaysRoleFn Iraq maleficiary)) is true iff the UN Security Council imposes (is imposing) sanctions on Iraq.
label: Actor Roles EPFT
actorRoles-EPFT

comment:
A ternary instance of InterArgIsaPredicate (q.v.). (interArgEqualsIsa5_4 RELN INDEPENDENT-ARG DEPENDENT-ARG-COL) means that, when INDEPENDENT-ARG appears as the fifth argument to RELN, a necessary condition for semantic well-formedness is that the fourth argument must be an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL. That is, (RELN ARG1 ARG2 ARG3 ARG4 INDEPENDENT-ARG ...) is semantically well-formed only if ARG4 is an instance of DEPENDENT-ARG-COL.

For an explanation of semantic well-formedness, see CycLExpression_Assertible and its direct specializations. See interArgEqualsIsa for a similar but more general predicate that is quintary, allowing the user to specify the positions of the independent and dependent arguments.
label: Inter Arg Equals Isa 5 4
interArgEqualsIsa5-4

comment: (typeHasQuantityComparedToType THING-1 VAL THING-2 PRED) means that instances of THING-1,tend to have the quantity VAL wrt PRED, when compared to the value that instances THING-2 would have wrt PRED all other things being equal.
label: Type Has Quantity Compared To Type
typeHasQuantityComparedToType
